aariyee: -yey / say: (v) inflate (infaleeyt); fill something with air or gas
aarso: -aarsay I aarsatay: (v) revenge (ri veenji); avenge (aveenji); retaliate (ri-taali-yeeyt) seek or take vengeance for [oneself or another person]
aartilari: -ga: (n) artillery (aar tarleri); large-caliber weapons, such as cannon, howitzers, and missile launchers ~ sida madfac, kanooni ama hawser.
aaryo qaadasho: -qaadashada: (n) outing (aaw-ting); excursion (ikis-keer-shiri); a walk outdoors ~ aariyo qaadasho
aas: -ka: (n) 1. the act or process of burying; burial (beeriyal); funeral (fiyuunaral) ~ duug, xabaal
—aas -ay / tay: (v) 2. place in the ground; bury (beeri) ~ duug, xabaal
3. aas-ku: (n) sunset (san-set). Ex: aasku intuuna madoobaan; before the sunset [before it gets dark]
aasaas: -ka: (n) foundation (fawn-dheey-shin); base, basis, ground, groundwork ~ sal, bilow —aasaas -ay / tay: (v) establish (is taab-liish); set up; found
aasaasi: -ga: (n) 1. essential (i-sen-shel); fundamental (fan-dha-men-tai). 2. inherence or indispensable ~ lama huraan
aasan: -aa: (adj) buried (beeridh); placed in the ground ~ xabaalan ama duugan
aasbiriin: -ka: (n) aspirin (aas-periin). Ex: keniin aasbariin ah; an aspirin tablet
aashuun: -ka: (n) a large, often rounded, water vessel of earthenware ~ ashuun, jalxad
aasnaan: -ta: (n) a condition or state of being buried
-aato: (suffix)-, if she... Ex: hadday jeclaato; if she likes; hadday fiicnaato; ifshe gets better
aawaday: (preposition) for my sake ~ dartay. Ex: waxay u joogeen aawaday; they stayed for my sake
aawadeed: (preposition) for it's or her sake ~ darteed, awgeed
aawadiis: (preposition) 1. for his sake - dartiis, awgiis 2. because of
aaway?: [aawey] (adv) where? (weer); at or in what place?. Ex: Aaway taleefoonkii? where is the telephone?
aawaye?: (adv) [aaweye] where are they? - meeye. Ex: Carruurtii aawaye? where are the children?
aay: -ey / day: (v) [with preposition u] benefit (bene fit)-, derive advantage from something at later time
aayad: -da: (n) koranic verse; an individual verse in the Quran
aayar: (adv) slowly (islowli); taking more time than is usual or necessary — tartiib, qunyar. Ex: Aayar u soco; walk slowly. —Syn: dilatory, leisurely, laggard, deliberate
aayatiin: -ka: (n) 1. fate (feyt); destiny (destani); predetermined events - calaf, aaye, aayo. -Syn:, kismet, lot, portion. 2. future (fiyuujar) - mustaqbal ama mustaqbil
aaye: -aayaha: (n) fate (feyt); predetermined events - see also [eeg] aayatiin
aayo: -aayaha: (n) fate (feyt); predetermined events - see also [eeg] aayatiin
aayo -aayada: (n) 1. stepmother (isteep maadar); the wife of one's father or uncle. 2. aunt (aanti); the sister of one's father - eeddo. 3. u aayo: benefit (bene fit) - see also [eeg] u aay
ab: -ka: (n) forefather (foorfaathar); ancestor (aan ses ter) ~ isir, walcan, sullan
abaabul: -ka: (n) 1. organization (oorgenizeeyshin). 2 -abaabulka: (adj) organizational. Ex: guddiga abaabulka; organizational committee. 3. —abaabul -ay /
abaad: -ay I day: (v) lost (loosti); no longer in the possession for a long time - abaaji. Ex: xoolihii abaaday; the lost livestock
abaahi: -yey: (v) mate (meeyt); pair animals [especially camels] for breeding - u hay, kud
abaaji: -yey / say: (v) lost (loosti); no longer in the possession for a long time - abaad
abaal: -ka: (n) 1. favor (feyver); a gracious or friendly act that is freely granted - asxaan. Ex: abaal ma ii gali kartaa? can you do me afavor? 2. merit (meerit); worth (woorth) ~ mudnaan. Ex: abaalkiisa marsii! give him what he deserves!
abaal ka dhac: -a: (n) ungratefulness (an gareeytfuul nes); lack of gratitude, lack of appreciation - abaaldarro
yimaad: -ay/timaaday: (v) arrive (a-raayv); come (keem). Ex: goormay yimaaddeen? What time did arrive?
yimid: (v) arrived (a-raayvid); come (keem). Ex: tareenkii wuu yimid; the train arrived
yiqiin: (v) knew (niyuu). Ex: af Soomaaliga buu yiqiin; he knew the Somali language
yix: -da: (n) soft hair of the newborn child
yool: -ka: (n) [sport] the finishing line of a race; goal post (gool powst)
Yuhuudi: -ga: (n) a Jewish person; Jew (juu); Hebrew (hib-ruu) - yahuudi
yunbi: yey say: (v) submerge (sab-meerji) in water; plunge (palaanji) into watertiinbi, tiimbi
yunbo: -yunbaday/yunbatay: (v) dive (daay-v); plunge (palaanji) into water tiinbo, tiimbo
yur: 2. Used to frighten away wild animals; shoo (shuu)
yuunifoom -ka: (n) uniform (yuuna-foom). Ex: yuunifoomka askarta; the military uniform

abwaanno.name: Qaamuuska Aasaasi: Ingiriis-Soomaali - Cabdiraxmaan C. Xaashi, Cawil Cali Xaashi [1993]

abandon: /abandhan/abandoning, abandoned; (v) ka tegid aan soo nogod lahayn ama in muddo dheer ah. e.g. You should not abandon your studies.
abandoned: /abandhandh/ (adj) laga guuray (laga haajiray). e.g. Harar was abandoned during the war.
abase: /abeys/ (v) in gof la sharaf rido, ama darajada laga qaado.
abashed: /abashid/ (adj) isku xishood ama isku yaxyaxid. e.g. Sarah looked abashed in the class when she realized her mistake.
abate: /abeyt/abates, abated; (v) 1. yaraato ama gudho. e.g. My illness abated a little. (v) 2. joojin.
abattoir: /abatwar/ (n) goobta xoolaha lagu gowraco, ama xero dhiig.
abbess: /abis/abbesses (n) naagta soorooyinka kaniisadda madaxda u ah.
abbey: /abey/ (n) guryaha kaniisaddu leedahay oo ay soorooyinku degan yihiin.
abbot: /abat/ (n) wadaadka diinta ee madaxda u ah wadaadada kale.
abbreviate: /abbriviyeyt/abbreviates, abbreviating, abbreviated; (v) ereyada oo la soo gaabiyo. e.g. U.S.A. (United States of America).
abdicate: /abdhikeyt/abdicates, abdicating, abdicated; (v) 1. is casilid (v) 2. ka samrid ama ka tanaasulid hawl ama jago. e.g. The minister abdicated his responsibility.
abdomen: /abdhoman/abdomens, abdominal; (n) uusleyda ama calool ku jirta. e.g. The patient is suffering from pain in the abdomen.
abduct: /abdhakt/ abducts, abducting,abducted; (v) afduub (khasab ku kaxaysad ama xoog ku kaxaysasho).e.g. The baby was abducted from his home and held for ransom
aberration: /abarreeshan/ (n) 1. arrin ama hawl sidii loo rabay aan noqon, (n) 2. marin habow (weecsanaan).
abet: /abet/ (v) dambi ama khalad ku gargaarid ama gacan ku siin. e.g. Do not abet your friend's enemy.
abhor: /abhoor/abhors, abhorring, abhorred; (v) karaahiyaysi; necbaysasho. e.g. Mahdi abhors any form of discrimination.
abide: /abaydh/abides, abiding, abided; 1. u dul-qaadasho. e.g. I can't abide an unpunctual person. 2. daa'imid.
abide by: /abaydh baay/ (v) u hogaansanaanta sharci ama heshiis. e.g. You must abide by the law.
ability: /abiliti/abilities; (n) karti ama awood qof wax ku gaban karo. e.g. Ubax studied to the best of her ability.
abject: /abjekt/ (adj) 1. xaalad xun oo niyad jab leh. e.g. the abject situation in the Middle East. 2. aan xurmo lahayn (aan xushmad u qalmin).
ablaze: /ableys/ (adj) 1. holac ama dab meel qabsaday. e.g. Within minutes the buildings were ablaze. 2. iftiin ama dhalaal fara badan.
able: /eybal/ (adj) awoodi kara. e.g. I will be able to visit you this weekend.
ably: /eybli/ (adv) awood buuxda leh. e.g. The President was ably supported by the party members.
abnegation: /agnigayshan/ (n) dafiraad, inkiraad. e.g. The thief's abnegation was unacceptable to the judge.
abnormal: /abnoormal/abnormalities, abnormally; (adj) 1. wax aan caadi ahayn. e.g. She exhibited abnormal behaviour. (adj) 2. naadir.
aboard: /aboordh/(adv) gaadiidka uu qof saaranyahay, sida diyaarad ama markab. e.g. The plane crashed, killing all passengers aboard.
abode: /aboodh/ (n) hoyga qof ku noolyahay. e.g. He took his bride to their new abode.
abolish: /abalish/abolishing, abolished; (v) 1. joojin, mamnuucid, (v) 2. tirtirid. e.g. The government will abolish the death penalty.
abominable: /abaminabal/ (adj) wax aad u xun oo la karaahiyaysto. e.g. Factory workers work in abominable conditions in some countries.
aboriginal: /abarijinal/ (n) dadka asalka ah ee ayagoo meel degan loogu yimaado. e.g. Canadian Indians are aboriginal people.
abortion: /aboorshan/ (n) ilmaha uurka ku jira oo si ula kac ah loo soo rido (la soo xaaqo).
abortive: /abortif/ (adj) 1. dhicisoobey. (adj) 2. lugu guul daraystay. e.g. The police made an abortive attempt to rescue the little girl.
abound: /abowndh/abounds, abounding, abounded; (v) wax tiro badan ama xaddi badan. e.g. The world of science fiction abounds with wonders.
about: /abbowt/ (prep) 1. ku saabsan. e.g. This is a book about Somalia. 2. qiyaastii. e.g. There were about ten students in the class.
above: /abbav/ (prep) 1. ka koreeya, kor. e.g. He lives in the apartment above the store. 2. ka badan.
abrasion: /abreyshan/abrasions; (n) 1. meel gofka jirkiisa diirku ka qaadmay. e.g. There was an abrasion on his thigh. (n) 2. xoqnaan.
abrasive: /abreysiv/ (adj) 1. qofka aan naxariista lahayn oo waji macbuuska ah. e.g. He is an abrasive person. 2. shay adag oo wax lugu nadiifiyo. e.g. He used an abrasive cleanser for the bathtub.
abreast: /abrest/ (adj) 1. dad ama wax is dhinac socda. e.g. Two cars were racing abreast. (adj) 2. ka war hayn. e.g. The press kept abreast of each new development.
abridged: /abrijid/ (adj) wax la soo gaabiyey, buug ama ciyaar oo kale. e.g. This is an abridged version of the book.
abroad: /abroodh/ (adv) 1. dibadda, dal shisheeye, dal qalaad. e.g. I was abroad on holiday. (adv) 2. ku baahid, fidid.
abrupt: /abrapt/abruptly; (adj) 1. wax kadis kuugu dhaca, lama filaan. e.g. The meeting came to an abrupt end. (adv) 2. qof u hadla si qabiidnimo ah oo edeb daran. e.g. I would not have spoken so abruptly if I'd known you were ill.
abscond: /abiskond/ (v) wax si qarsoodi ah loola baxsado, ama qof dhuuntay ama baxsaday. e.g. He absconded with the public funds.
absence: /absansi/absences; (n) maqnaansho. e.g. The class was very noisy during the teacher's absence.
absentee: /absantii/ (n) qofka ka magan meeshii laga rabay inuu joogo. e.g. There were no absentees in the class that day.
absent-minded: / (adj) maqane jooge, qofka kula jooga hadana maahsan. e.g. Some of the students are absent-minded when it comes to remembering their homework.
absolute: /absalut/absolutely; (adj) 1. dhamaystiran (adv) 2. wax aad carrabka ku adkeynaysid in ay sax ama run yihiin. e.g. You're absolutely right about the news.
absolve: /absolv/absolves, absolving, absolved; (v) gof dambi loo haystay lugu waayey, bari ka ah. e.g. The President is absolved from blame and responsibility over the company's loss.
absorb: /absoorb/absorbs, absorbing absorbed; (v) 1. dhuugid ama nuugid. e.g. Plants absorb water through their roots. 2. wax la liqay ama lala wareegay. e.g. small companies are often absorbed by larger ones.
absorbent: /absorbant/ (adj) alaab ama qalab wax nuuga sida isbuunyada.
absorption: /absoorbshan/ (n) 1. nuugitaan, dhuuqis. e.g. the absorption of water by a towel. (n) 2. wax aad danaynaysid (xiisaynaysid). e.g. He has an absorption in his studies.
abstain: /absteyn/abstains, abstaining, abstained; (v) 1. iska deyn wax aad sameyn jirtay, ka caagid. e.g. He will abstain from sleeping for two days. (v) 2. arrin ama doorasho aadan codkaaga ka dhiiban (ka aamustid). e.g. He abstained during the vote.
abstemious: /abstemiyas/ (adj) qofka iska joojiya ama wax yar ka qaata wax naftiisu rabto sida cuntada, cabidda. e.g. He is an abstemious eater.
abstract: /abstrakt/abstracts, abstracting, abstracted; (adj) wax aan la taaban karin.
absurd: /abserdh/absurdity; (adj) aan macquul ahayn. e.g. The government policies are absurd.
abundance: /abandhans/abundant; (n) wax aad u badan, qaraq. e.g. An abundance of food was spread out on the buffet table.
abuse: /abyuus/abuses, abusing, abused; (n) 1. caay ama aflagaado. e.g. She abuses her children. (v) 2. gof inaad ku xad gudubtid. e.g. The patients were physically abused. (n) 3. wax aad si khalad ah u isticmaashid. e.g. Drug abuse is increasing in North America.
abysmal: /abismal/ (adj) wax la liidayo ama aan tayo badan lahayn.
abyss: /abis/ (n) 1. god dheer oo aan guntiisa la gaari karin (n) 2. xaalad baqdin leh sida dagaalka 3aad ee adduunka.
AC: /ey sii/ (n) danabka qulqula ee korontada (alternating current oo la soo gaabiyey).
academy: /akadami/ (n) dugsi tacliin sare oo loogu tala galay waxbarasho gaar ah. e.g. the Lafoole Academy of Arts.
accede: /aksiid/accedes, acceding, acceded; (v) arrin aad gof ku raacdid ama u ogalaatid. e.g. I can't accede to your request.
accelerate: /akselarayt/accelerates, accelerating, accelerated; (v) 1. sheelarayn, karaarsiin. e.g. He accelerated the car. (v) 2. dadajin, ku dhakhsasho.
accelerator: /akselaratar/ (n) sheelare (qalabka lugu istaago si xawaaraha loo kordhiyo).
accent: /aksent/accents, accenting, accented; (n) 1. luqad si duwan loogu dhawaaqo ama loogu hadlo; lahjad. e.g. Hibo has a strong French accent. (n) 2. xarakada lugqad lugu dhigo oo dhawaaga badasha sida tan Carabiga.
accentuate: /aksenjuweyt/accentuates, accentuating, accentuated; (v) carrabka ku adkayn ama hadal la doonayo in muhiimadiisa la muujiyo. e.g. He accentuated the importance of education.
accept: /aksept/ accepts, accepting, accepted; (v) la ogolaado ama la yeelo. e.g. They will accept my advice when it is offered.
acceptable: /akseptabal/ (adj) wax la ogolaan karo ama laysku waafiqi karo. e.g. My idea was acceptable to the company.
acceptance: /akseptans/ (n) aqbalaad ama ogolaansho. e.g. I received my acceptance from the university.
access: /akses/accesses, accessing, accessed; (n) 1. meel jid loo maro. e.g. The access to the garage is through the gate. (n) 2. wax aad awood u leedahay inaad isticmaashid ama ogaatid. e.g. I have access to the computer.
accessible: /aksesable/ (adj) wax la gaari karo, la heli karo ama cid kasta u furan. e.g. Libraries are accessible to the public.
accession: /akseshin/ (n) 1. ku soo biirid ama wax isku darsamay. e.g. the accession of Quebec and Canada. 2. in jago sare qof loo doorto ama uu hanto. e.g. Today is the President's accession.
accessory: /aksesari/accessories; (n) 1. wax siyaada ah sida waxyaabaha baabuurta lugu qurxiyo. e.g. Bracelets and rings are fashion accessories. 2. qofka in dambi la galo gargaara ama qariya. e.g. He is an accessory to the murder.
accident: /aksident/ accidents; (n) 1. shil. e.g. He was injured in a car accident. (adj) 2. wax kadis ku dhacay, lama filaan.
accidental: /aksidental/accidentally, (adj) wax si fursad ah isaga dhacay. e.g. My meeting with him was purely accidental.
accident prone: /aksident paron/ (adj) qofka shilka u nasiibka badan; gacan fudayd.
acclaim: /akleym/acclaims, acclaiming, acclaimed; (v) 1. si fiican loo ammaanay; loo faaniyey. e.g. He was acclaimed for his writing talent. (n) 2. si xamaasad leh loo soo dhaweeyey.
acclimatize: /aklaymatays/acclimatizes, acclimatizing, acclimatized; (v) wax aad qabatintid ama u baratid. e.g. He became acclimatized to the winter.
accolade: /akaleydh/accolades; (n) billad siin sida billad geesinimo ama billad hawl karnimo. e.g. This was the highest accolade he received.
accommodate: /akomadheyt/accommodates, accommodating; (v) diyaafadin (hurdo siin, jiif siin ama guri siin). e.g. He can accommodate up to five guests.
accommodation: /akomodashan/ (n) degaan. e.g. There is no shortage of accommodation in this building.
accompaniment: /akampaniment/ (n) 1. laxanka ama codka muusiga ee hees loo sameeyo. e.g. a piano accompaniment (n) 2. shay wax la raaciyo ama lugu lammaaniyo sida iidaanka cuntada loo raaciyo oo kale.
accompany: /akambani/accompanies, accompanying, accompanied; (v) 1. u wehel yeelid ama raacid. e.g. He will accompany her to the movie (v) 2. wax raacsan wax kale, sida hargabka iyo madax xanuunku isku raacsan yihiin.
accomplice: /akomplis/ (n) qof danbiile gacan siiya. e.g. The murderer's accomplice was arrested.
accomplish: /akomplish/accomplishes, accomplishing, accomplished; (v) wax in lugu guuleysto ama la dhamaystiro. e.g. He had to accomplish his task.
accomplishment: /akomplishment/ accomplishments; (n) 1.xirfad gaar ah (qof hawl gudan kara ama si fiican u yaqaan). e.g. He has great experience and accomplishment. (n) 2. dhammaystir (guul-gaarid).
accord: /akoordh/accords, according, accorded; (n) 1. heshiis ama mucaahado. e.g. the Camp David Accord. (v) 2. guddoonsiin ama in aad gof wax u hibeysid.
accordance: /akoodhans/ (n) ayadoo la tixraacayo ama laga dabqaadanayo. e.g. In accordance with Islamic law, you must pray.
accordingly: /akoodhingli/ (adv) arrin sababsatay arin kale ama darteed u dhacday (sababtaas darteed). e.g. He stole some money and he was arrested accordingly.
according to: /akkooding to/ (prep) marka loo eego ama loo fiiriyo. e.g. According to the evidence, he is guilty.
accost: /akoost/accosts, accosting accosted; (v) qof in aad hadal ku bilowdid ama afka la gashid. e.g. I was accosted by a salesman.
account: /akownt/accounts, accounting, accounted; (n) 1. xisaabinta lacagta. e.g. He prepares his accounts carefully. 2. xisaab ama koonto kaaga furan bangi, shirkad ama dukaan. e.g. bank account.
account (into account): /intu akownt/; (phr) arin in aad xisaabta ku dartid ama ku tashatid. e.g. Take into account that you need to rest.
account for: /akownt fo/; (phr) ka dhigan (le'eg). e.g. Studying accounts for eighty percent of my time.
accountable: /akowntabal/accountability; (adj) ka masuul ah ama xil ka saaran yahay. e.g. He was held accountable for the school riot.
accountancy: /akawntansi/ (n) shaqada xisaabiya-nimada. e.g. He has a diploma in accountancy.
accountant: /akawntant/ (n) xisaabiye. e.g. He is an accountant.
accredit: /akredhit/accredits, accrediting, accredited; (v) 1. in awood aad shaqo ku qaban kartid lugu siiyo (v) 2. in si rasmi ah loogu magacaabo wakiil ama danjire. e.g. He was accredited to a post at the United Nations.
accrue: /akruu/(v) 1. ka dhashay (ka abuurmay). (v) 2. ku siyaadin (ku darid).
accumulate: /akyuumaleyt/accumulates, accumulated, accumulating; (v) isku ururay ama isku tagay. e.g. These items were accumulated over a period of time.
accuracy: /akyarasi/ (n) sax (khalad la'aan). e.g. The newspaper was noted for its accuracy.
accurate: /akyarit/accurately; (n) wax sax ah oo aan khalad lahayn. e.g. an accurate estimate.
accusation: /akyuuseyshan/accusations; (n) dacwo; ashkato. e.g. This is a false accusation.
accuse: /akyuus/accuses, accusing, accused; (v) dacwayn ama eedayn. e.g. He accused him of stealing.
accustom: /akastam/accustoms, accustoming, accustomed; (v) caadaysi, ama u barasho. e.g. My ears are accustomed to this kind of noise.
ache: /eyk/aches, aching, ached; (v) xanuun isdaba joog ah. e.g. My legs ache after that long hike.
achieve: /ajiiv/achieves, achieving, achieved; (v) lib ku dhammayn; guul ku dhammayn. e.g. He achieved his goals.
acknowledge: /aknalij/acknowledges, acknowledging, acknowledged; (v) 1. qirid ama caddayn. e.g. He was acknowledged as the best student. (v) 2. mahad celin. e.g. They will acknowledge receipt of my letter.
acknowledgement: /aknalijment/ (n) 1. mahad celin. e.g. I received their acknowledgement yesterday. (n) 2. qiris ama citiraaf.
acoustic: /akuustic/acoustics; (adj) wax maqal ama shangar ku lug leh sida samaacadaha. e.g. The theatre has good acoustics.
acquaint: /akweynt/acquaints, acquainting, acquainted; (v) barasho ama ogaansho; isbarasho.
acquiesce: /akuwilyas/acquiesces, acquiescing, acquiesced; (v) qof inaad wax ku raacdid ama ka aqbashid. e.g. He acquiesced to the request.
acquire: /akwaayar/acquires, acquiring, acquired; (v) 1. wax aad heshid ama lugu siiyo. e.g. He acquired the information he needed. 2. wax aad kasbatid.
acquirement: /akwayarment/ (n) wax dadaal ama aqoon aad ku kasbatay.
acquisition: /akuwasishan/ (n) wax aad hanatid ama wax aad gacanta ku dhigtid. e.g. the acquisition of land.
acquit: /akwit/acquits, acquitting, acquitted; (v) 1. in dambi gof lugu waayo; beri ka ah. e.g. He was acquitted by the court. (v) 2. hab dabeecadeed gaar ah oo qof u dhaqmo. e.g. He acquitted himself well in the meeting.
acre: /eykar/acres; (n) hektar ama qiyaas dhuleed oo la mid ah 4047 mitir oo isku wareeg ah.
acrid: /aakrid/ (adj) 1. wax kharaar ah ama Wax soo uraya. e.g. The building was filled with acrid smoke. (adj) 2. hadal kulkulul oo xanaaq leh. e.g. That is an acrid attack on government policy.
acrimonious: /akramoniyas/ (adj) hadalka laysku kululeeyo xanaaq dartiis. e.g. There was an acrimonious dispute at the conference.
acrobat: /aakrabat/acrobats; (n) qofka dadka ku madadaaliya in uu sameeyo xarakaad aan la samayn karin. sida qaalmarogadka, bootinta iwm.
acrobatic: /akrabaatik/acrobatics; (adj) ciyaaraha dhibta badan sida qaalmarogadka, bootinta sare iwm. e.g. He can do wonderful acrobatics.
acronym: /akranim/acronyms; (n) ereyo ama magac la soo gaabiyey oo loo sameeyo hal erey oo u taagan sida WHO (World Health Organization)
across: /akroos/ (prep) 1. ka gudbid; gudub u jarid, dhinac. e.g. He walked across the bridge to the city. (adv) 2. wax dhinaca kale saaran sida guri wadada dhanka kale kaga yaal. e.g. She lives in the building across the street.
act: /aakt/acts, acting acted; (v) 1. wax qabasho ama wax falid. e.g. Act quickly before it is too late. 2. sharciga dowladu soo saarto. e.g. the Income Tax Act.
act up: /aakt ap/ (adv) 1. wax aan si fiican u shaqaynayn. e.g. The computer tends to act up. 2. gof si aan caadi ahayn u dhaqma. e.g. The child was acting up in the classrooom.
acting: /aaktin/ (n) ku sii simid ama xil qof kale sii hayn. e.g. He is the acting manager.
action: /aakshan/actions; (n) wax qabad ama dhaqaaq. e.g. The police took serious actions against the offenders.
activate: /aaktiveyt/activates, activating, activated; (v) dhaqaajin ama kicin; socodsiin. e.g. He activated the machine.
active: /aaktiv/actively; (adj) firfircoon ama wax qabad leh. e.g. She is active in her community.
actor: /aaktar/ (n) ninka jilaaga ah; filimada ama riwaayadaha. e.g. He is the best actor in Hollywood.
actress: /akt-ris/ (n) naagta filimada ama riwaayadaha jisha. e.g. She is a beautiful actress.
actual: /aakjuwal/actuality; (adj) xaqiiq ah, run ah ama jira.
actually: /aakjuwali/ (adv) run ahaantii, xaqiiqdii. e.g. Actually, she is not a doctor.
acupuncture: /akyapankjar/ (n) daawayn laysku daaweeyo irbado jirka lugu mudo, gaar ahaan laga isticmaalo wadanka Shiinaha.
acute: /akyuut/ (adj) 1. wax dareen kulul leh ama cadaadis kugu haya. e.g. The illness became more acute. 2. qof fahma furan oo isla markiiba wax fahma. e.g. He is an acute thinker. 3. xagasha ka yar 90 digrii.
A.D: /ey-dhii/ (abbr) waxaa loo isticmaalaa sanadihii ama qarniyadii ka dambeeyey dhalashadii Nebi Ciise. e.g. the year 2500 A.D.
adage: /adhij/ (n) oraah horey dad u yiri. e.g. He reminded me about the old adage, “Time is money”.
adamant: /adhamant/adamantly; (adj) go'aan aan ka nogod lahayn. e.g. They are adamant about studying hard.
Adam's apple: /aadhamis apal/ (n) curta raga dhuuntooda ka soo taagan.
adapt: /adhaapt/adapts, adapting, adapted; (v) la qabsasho ama u barasho. e.g. He is trying to adapt to the new life.
adaptable: /adaaptabal/ (adj) qofka meeshuu tago ama xaaladii cusubba la qabsan kara. e.g. To succeed in your career, you have to be adaptable.
adaptation: /adhapteyshan/ (n) 1. sheeko buug ku goran oo filin laga sameeyey. e.g. The movie adaptation of Robin Hood was quite different from the book. 2. wax sidii hore laga badelo si uu habka cusub ula qabsado. e.g. This animal's adaptation to the different weather conditions is remarkable.
add: /aadh/add up; (v) 1. xisaab isku darid ama isugeyn. e.g. Add together all your expenses. (v) 2. hadal ku siyaadin. e.g. He also added that he will arrive tomorrow.
adder: /aadhar/adders; (n) maska qaniinyada sunta ah leh (mas sumaysan).
addict: /aadhikt/addicts, addicted; (n) qof wax caadaystay oo aan iska joojin karin, sida sigaarka oo kale. e.g. He is a T.V. addict.
addiction: /adhikshan/ (n) caadaysiga la caadaysto waxyaabaha aan layska dayn karin, sida mukhaadaraadka. e.g. an addiction to drugs.
addictive: /adh-dhiktiv/ (adj) wax markii naftaadu u barato aadan ka maarmi karin ama ku qabanya. e.g. Cigarettes are addictive.
addition: /adhishan/additions; (n) 1. isugeynta xisaabta, ku-dar. e.g. Addition is a simple mathemathical operation. 2. hadal aad ku siyaadisid, hadal aad horay u tiri. e.g. In addition to that, I have to pay more.
additional: /adhishinal/additionally; (adj) wax siyaada ama dheeraad ah. e.g. The business needs additional funds if it is to survive.
additive: /aadhativ/additives; (adj) wax wixii lugu daro sii hagaajiya sida dhirta shaaha lugu carfiyo. e.g. food additives.
address: /adres/addresses, addressing, addressed; (n) 1. ciwaan (sida cinwaanka | gurigaaga ama shaqadaada). e.g. I have to make an address change. (v) 2. khudbad jeedin. e.g. The President addressed the nation.
address book: /adres buuk/address books; (n) buuga cinwaanada lugu qorto. e.g. I lost my address book yesterday.
adduce: /adhyuus/adduces, adducing, adduced; (v) wax tusaale ahaan aad u soo bandhigtid. e.g. The student adduced a copy of his exam to support his petition for remarking.
adept: /adhept/ (adj) khibrad ama waaya-aragnimo leh. e.g. He became more adept at his work.
adequate: /adhakwit/adequately, adequacy; (adj) ku filan, deeqa. e.g. The supplies are adequate.
adhere: /adh-hiyar/adheres, adhering, adhered; (v) 1. isku xirid laba shay ama isku dhajin. e.g. Adhere the picture to the wall. (v) 2. addeecid ama taageerid. They will adhere to the treaty.
adherent: /adh-hiyarent/ (n) raaciye (taageere u ah , sida xisbi, madaxweyne iwm).
adhesive: /adh-hiisiv/ (adj) wax ku dhagaya sida koollada, xabagta, balaastarka iwm. e.g. We need adhesive tape to fasten the papers together.
ad hoc: /adh-hok/ (adj) guddi loo abuuray xaalad gaar ah in wax looga qabto. e.g. The police set up an ad hoc task force.
adjacent: /adjeysant/ (adj) ku xiga, dhinac yaal, ku naban.
adjective: /aajaktiv/adjectives; (n) sifo; kalmad tilmaamaysa ama wax ka sheegaysa magaca.
adjoin: /adjooyn/adjoins, adjoining, adjoined; (v) wax isku xiriirsan ama isku xig xiga. e.g. The living room adjoins the kitchen.
adjourn: /adhjern/adjourn, adjourning, adjourned; (v) hakin; maxkamad ama shir la hakiyey oo dib loo bilaabi doono. e.g. The trial was adjourned until tomorrow.
adjudged: /ajaajidh/ (v) loo aqoonsado ama lugu xukumo. e.g. He was adjudged a criminal.
adjournment: /ajeerniment/ (n) hakin lugu sameeyo hawl socotey. e.g. The adjournment lasted for two hours.
adjudicate: /ajuudikeyt/adjudicates, adjudicating, adjudicated; (v) xukumida (sida dambiile la xukumay oo kale). e.g. The panel adjudicated the case.
adjunct: /aajankti/adjuncts; (n) 1. wax la xirlira ama ku lug leh wax kale oo laga maarmi karo. (n) 2. kalmad ama kalmado jumlad dheeraad ku ah. e.g. This word is an adjunct to the sentence.
adjust: /ajast/adjusts, adjusting, adjusted; (v) isku hagaajin ama isku toosin. e.g. Please adjust the radio volume.
adjustable: /adjastabal/ (adj) wax laysku hagaajin karo ama laysku toosin karo. e.g. This television set is not adjustable.
ad-lib: /ad-liib/ (adv) hadal ama qoraal aan horay loo soo diyaarin. e.g. The commentator's ad lib remark was in poor taste.
administer: /adhminastar/administers, administering, administered; (v) maamulid. e.g. He administers the investment fund.
administrative: /adhminastreytiv/ (adj) hawlaha maamulka la xiriira. e.g. The administrative work is handled in this office.
administrator: /adminastreytar/administrators; (n) maamule, isuduwe ama maareeye. e.g. She is the system administrator.
admirable: /adhmarabal/admirably; (adj) wax ama gof ammaan mudan ama loo qushuuci karo. e.g. The service at the hotel is admirable.
admiration: /adhmirayshan/ (n) qushuuc, bogis. e.g. He had enormous admiration for his parents.
admire: /adhmaayar/admires, admiring, admired; (v) qushuucid ama u bogid. e.g. He admires the math professor.
admirer: /adhmayrar/admirers; (n) qofka wax ka hela ama u qushuuca. e.g. He is an admirer of her work.
admission: /adhmishan/admissions; (n) ogolaansho. e.g. They were granted admission to the country.
admit: /adhmit/admits, admitting, admitted; (v) 1. girid, la girto. e.g. They admit that they committed the crime. (v) 2. loo ogolaado. e.g. He was admitted to the meeting.
admittance: /adhmitans/ (n) ogolaansho ama qof loo fasaxo inuu meel soo galo. e.g. They obtained admittance to the convention centre.
admixture: /adhmiksjar/ (n) 1. isku dar, isku qas. 2. milan (wax la isku qasay).
admonish: /adhmanish/admonishes, admonished, admonishing; (v) u digid, ka waanin ama kala talin. e.g. The teacher admonished the students for their poor work.
adolescence: /adholesans/; (n) muddada u dhaxaysa ciyaalnimada ilaa qaan-gaarnimada. e.g. He had a great time during his adolescence.
adolescent: /adholesant/adolescents; (n) qof ku jira sanooyinka qaan-gaarnimada (xilliga u dhaxeeya 13-16 sano). e.g. He behaves like an adolescent.
adopt: /adhapt/adopts, adopting, adopted; (v) 1. ilmo ama cunug aadan dhalin oo aad korsato. e.g. Sarah is willing to adopt more children. (v) 2. la qabatimo (ra'yi ama wax la caadaysto). e.g. I had to adopt the new method of learning.
adorable: /adhoorabal/ (adj) wax aad loo jeclaysto ama laga helo gaar ahaan caruurta ama xayawaanka. e.g. She is an adorable little girl.
adoration: /aadhareyshan/ (n) qof ama wax jacayl fara badan iyo tixgelin wayn aad u haysid. e.g. He told me about his adoration for her.
adore: /adhoor/adores, adored, adoring; (v) 1. qof aad jeceshahay oo aad ka dambaysid ama tixgelisid. e.g. He adores his father. (v) 2. caabudid. e.g. We only adore the Creator.
adorn: /adhoorn/adorns, adorning, adorned; (v) 1. wax qurxin ama wax sharraxid. e.g. a house adorned with pictures. (v) 2. dib u habayn.
adornment: /adhoornment/ (n) waxyaabaha wax lugu qurxiyo ama lugu sharraxo. e.g. adornment such as make-up and jewellery.
adrenalin: /aadrenalin/adrenaline; (n) dheecaan ama hoormoon jirka qofku dhaliyo markuu xanaaqo, cabsado ama farxo. e.g. Watching football gets his adrenalin pumping.
adrift: /adrift/ (adj) 1. doon ama wax iska sabbaynaya oo aan cidna wadin (adj) 2. wax marin habowsan ama aan ujeeddo cad lahayn.
adroit: /adrooyt/adroitly; (adj) ku fiican, xariif ku ah ama ku horeeya. e.g My nephew is quite adroit at making model airplanes.
adulate: /adhyaleyt/adulation; (v) qof wax uusan ahayn aad ku faanisid (u af-macaanin). e.g. He adulated her, which made her uncomfortable.
adult: /aadhalt/ (adj) qof weyn; hanaqaad ama taabagal ah. e.g. He spent all his adult life in the countryside.
adulterate: /adhaltareyt/adulterates, adulterating, adulterated; (v) barxid, wax la barxay oo biyo lugu daray ama biyo-biyood laga dhigay. e.g. To adulterate milk with water.
adultery: /adhaltari/ (n) sino, siiba sinaysiga qofka xaaska ah. e.g. He committed adultery.
advance: /advaansi/ (n) horusocod; horumarin. e.g. An advance in medical technology is always welcome.
advancement: /adhvaansiment/ (n) horukac ama dallacaad. e.g. You have an opportunity for personal advancement in this company.
advantage: /adhvaantij/advantag-es; (n) 1. wax faa'iido gaar ah qof u leh. e.g. Having a professional diploma can be a big advantage. 2. qof awood yaridiisa aad ka faa'iidaysatid. e.g. I should take advantage of his foolishness.
advantageous: / advaanteyjas/ advantageously; (adj) faa'iido leh, macaash laga heli karo. e.g. The businessman is in a very advantageous position.
advent: /aadvent/ (n) wax soo baxay ama wax cusub oo lasoo saaray. e.g. the advent of computers.
adventitious: /adventishas/ (adj) dhacdo ama xaalad si fursad ah isaga dhacday; ama si kKadis ah. e.g. Her knowledge of this confidential information was somewhat adventitious.
adventure: /adhvenjar/adventures; (n) tacabur, biimo. e.g. He enjoys adventure.
adventurer: /adhvenjarar/adventurers; (adj) 1. qofka khatar ama tacaburka jecel. e.g. a courageous adventurer (n) 2. qofka jecel khayaano inuu ~ wax ku hantiyo.
adventurous: /adhvenjaras/adventurously; (adj) 1. qofka jecel waxyaabo cusub oo khatar leh inuu isku dayo ama tijaabiyo. (adj) 2. qofka jecel meelo cusub inuu u safro si uu khibrad cusub uga helo. e.g. He was a adventurous an explorer.
adverb: /aadhverb/adverbs; (n) ereyga ficilka ama falka wax ka sheega; fal-gargaare ama fal-kaab. e.g. I read slowly.
adversary: /aadhvarseri/adversaries; (n) qof ama waddan tartan idin ka dhexeeyo ama aad dagaalsan tihiin, mucaarad. e.g. During the campaign, his political adversary was the youth leader.
adverse: /aadhvers/adversely; (adj) go'aan , xaalad ama arrin dantaada ka soo horjeeda ama aan kuu roonayn; wax kuu daran. e.g. Inflation has an adverse effect on every individual.
adversity: /adhveersiti/adversities; (n) xaalad aad u adag, nasiib darro ama dacdarro. e.g. His childhood was filled with adversity.
advertise: /adhvartays/advertises, advertising; advertised; (v) 1. xayaysiin (v) 2. iidheh ka bixin, jago ama hawl bannaan. e.g. My computer had been advertised on television.
advertisement: /adhvartaysment/ advertisements; (n) iidheh ama xayaysiis. e.g. an advertisement for the new product.
advertiser: /adhvartaysar/advertisers; (n) cidda ama shirkadda wax loo xayaysiinayo.
advice: /adhvays/ (n) talo siin; arrin kala talin. e.g. She followed her mother's advice.
advisable: /adhvaysabal/ (adj) layskula talin karo; caqli gal ah; kuu fiican. e.g. It's advisable to go to your doctor.
advise: /adhvays/advises, advising, advised; (v) la talin; sax u sheegid ama u tilmaamid. e.g. He advised me not to drive while it's raining.
adviser: /adhvaysar/ (n) la taliye. e.g. He has been a political adviser for ten years.
advocate: /adhvakeyt/advocates, advocating, advocated; (v) 1. wax si cad aad u taageertid ama aad ku doodid in la sameeyo. e.g. Mandela advocates human rights. (v) 2. qareen, looyar.
aeon: /eyan/ (n) waqti aad u dheer oo aan la qiyaasi karin.
aerial: /eeriyal/ (n) fiilo ama bir dhuuban oo awood u leh inay gudbiso ama soo qabato hirarka raadyaha (t.v. anteena).
aerodrome: /eeradrom/ (n) meel saldhig iyo dayactir diyaaradeed ah.
aeronautics: /eeranootikis/ (n) cilmiga lugu barto diyaaradaha samayntooda iyo naqshadayntooda. e.g. He has extensive knowledge of aeronautics.
aeroplane: /eerapleyn/ (n) dayuurad. (dayaarad). e.g. He travelled to London by aeroplane.
aerosol: /erasool/aerosols; (n) dhalo ama weel lagu cadaadiyey waxyaabaha la buufiyo, sida dhalooyinka barafuunka iyo qalabka kaloo wax lagu carfiyo. e.g. a product sold in aerosol form.
afar: /afar/ (adv) ka fog. e.g. She saw me from afar.
affable: /aafabal/ (adj) qof la fahmi karo ama furfuran; bulshay ah. e.g. She was always affable with my cousin.
affair: /affeer/affairs;(n) l.arrin. e.g. I don't want to know about his affairs. (n) 2. gaabsi (sinaysi). e.g. She had an affair with her boss.
affect: /affekt/affects, affecting, affected; (v) 1. wax ku saameeya ama ku dareen galiya. e.g. Inflation will affect every one. (v) 2. wax yeelleeya ama cudur ku rida. e.g. Smoking affects your health.
affectation: /affekteyshan/affectations; (n) dabeecad aan dhab ahayn oo layska yeelyeelo. e.g. His affectations are ridiculous.
affection: /affekshan/ (n) u dabacsanaan qof ama xayawaan; jeclaan; u roonaan. e.g. She looked at him with affection.
affectionate: /affekshanit/affectionately; (adj) qof si macaan aad ula dhagantid si jacaylkaad u haysid aad u muujisid. e.g. His touch was affectionate.
affidavit: /affadheyvit/affidavits; (n) dhaar qoraal ah in waxaasi run yihiin, haddii loo baahdana maxkamad lugugu soo taagi karo. e.g. She signed a sworn affidavit in front of the court.
affinity: /affinati/affinities; (n) 1. wax ama qof aad ka heshid ama ku soo jiita. e.g. I have this tremendous sense of affinity with the place. (n) 2. xididnimo; qaraabada xaga guurka. e.g. There are relatives by birth and by affinity. (n) 3. waxyaabo isu eg ama is shabbaha. e.g. There are many affinities between Canadian and American English.
affirm: /affeerm/affirms, affirming, affirmed; (v) 1. xaqiijin. e.g. She affirmed that she was innocent. (v) 2. shaac ka qaadid, addeecid ama taageerid. e.g. He affirmed the new policy of the government.
affirmative: /affermativ/ (adj) ku raacid, ku waafiqid. e.g. He always gives an affirmative response.
afflict: /affilikt/afflicts, afflicting, afflicted; (v) jirro saamaysay, ama xanuun ku habsaday. e.g. He is afflicted with rheumatism.
affluent: /aafluwant/affluence; (adj) nolol heer sare ah; qaninimo; barwaago ku noolaansho. e.g. He is one of the affluent young professionals in the city.
afford: /affoordh/affords, affording, afforded; (v) awoodi kara; yeeli kara. e.g. I can't afford to buy a car.
affront: /affrant/affronts; affronting; affronted; (n) cay bareer ah, cambaarayn, jareexayn. e.g. It was an affront to her dignity.
afield: /afiildh/ (adv) ka fog hoyga ama meesha la degan yahay.
afire: /afaayar/ (adj) gubanaya; dab dul saaran. e.g. The building was set afire.
afloat: /aflowt/ (adv) 1. sabbaynaya; heehaabaya (biya dushood ama hawada) (adj) 2. shirkad ama ganacsi aan faa'iido badan samayn laakiin isbixin karta.
afoot: /afuut/ (adv) 1. u diyaar nogosho (adj) 2. hawl socota ama qorsheheeda lugu jiro. e.g. There is dirty work afoot.
aforementioned: /afoormenshinedh/ (adj) horay loo sheegay; horey loo yiri.
afraid: /afreydh/ (adj) baqanaya; cabsanaya; welwelaya. e.g. I am afraid to swim.
african: /aafrikan/ Africans; (n) dadka ku nool ama ka yimaada afrika gaar ahaan kuwa madoow. e.g. Somali is an African language.
after: /aaftar/ (prep) ka dib; ka bacdi ama ka gadaal. e.g. He arrived just after the meeting.
after-care: /aafter-keer/ (n) 1. daawaynta qofku markuu isbitaalka ama xabsiga ka soo baxo. (n) 2. baanasho.
after-effect: /aafter-ifekt/ after- effects; (n) wax-yeellayn; wax markay dhacaan waxyeelo leh. e.g. a drug with no after-effects.
aftermath: /aafter-maath/ (n) arrin ama wax dhacay natiijadood. e.g. People are still suffering the aftermath of war.
afternoon: /aaftar-nuun/ afternoons; (n) galabnimo (wakhtiga u dhexeeya duhurkii iyo makhribkii). e.g. The sun is hottest in the afternoon.
after-shave: /aafter-shayv/ (n) dareere udgoon oo raggu marsadaan markey garka iska xiiraan.
after-taste: /aafter-test/ (n) dhadhanka afka ku hara cuntada ama cabbida ka dib.
afterthought: /aafterthoot/afterthoughts; (n) wax aad tiraahdid ama sheegtid goor dambe adigoon ka fiirsan (ka fakarin).
afterward: /aafterwardh/afterwards; (adj) arrin horey u dhacday dabadeed wax dhaca; waxaas ka bacdi. e.g. She became ill and died soon afterward.
again: /ageyn/(adv) mar kale; mar labaad. e.g. Can you try again in half an hour?
against: /agenist/(prep) 1. ka soo hor jeeda; lid ku ah ama ka dhan ah. e.g. I am against having a picnic on Friday. (prep) 2. ku tiirsan; dhinaca ku haya ama cadaadinaya. e.g. Do not lean against the door.
age: /eeyj/ages, aging, aged;(n) 1. da' (inta qof jiro). e.g. She is ten years of age. 2. qof ama wax kale oo da'weyn. e.g. This building is for the aged people.
ageing: /eyjing/(adj) gaboow, duq ah. e.g. an ageing teacher.
ageless: /eyjles/(adj) 1. qof da'qarsi leh. e.g. an ageless actor. 2. waqti ama da' aan la qiyaasi karin.
agency: /eyjansi/agencies;(n) wakaalad ama wakiil. e.g. She works for an employment agency.
agenda: /ajenda/agendas;(n) waxyaabaha looga hadlayo shir ama kulan; waxyaabaha la qabanayo. e.g. What is the next point on the agenda?
agent: /eyjant/agents;(n) qof shirkad ama dowlad wakiil u ah. e.g. I would like to phone my agent in London about the situation.
age-old: /eyj-oldh/(adj) wax in badan soo taxnaa; soo jireen ahaa. e.g. There is an age-old custom in Somalia.
aggravate: /aggraveyt/aggravates, aggravating; aggravated;(v) 1. xaalad xumayd oo aad ka sii dartid, sii xumayn ama sii qasid. e.g. He aggravated the situation. 2. ka xanaajin. e.g. His speeches always aggravate me.
aggregate: /agegrigeyt/aggregates;(n) isku dar, wadar. e.g. He spent an aggregate of ten years in different jails.
aggression: /aggreshan/(n) dagaal gardaro ah bilaabid. e.g. It is not acceptable to commit an act of aggression against your neighbour.
aggressive: /aggresiv/aggressively, aggressiveness;(adj) gardaran ama dagaal badan. e.g. He was the only aggressive speaker in the meeting.
aggressor: /aggresar/aggressors;(n) qof ama waddan dagaal gardaro ah bilaaba.
aggrieved: /agegriivid/(adj) ka xumaansho ama ka cabasho caddaalad darro lagu sameeyey. e.g. She felt aggrieved because she didn't get araise.
aghast: /agaast/(adj) murugo naxdin leh. e.g. She was aghast about the murder.
agile: /aajil/agility;(adj) 1. aad u dhakhsa badan; fudfudud. e.g. the dancers's agile movements. 2. qof maskax furan; si dhakhsa ah wax u fahma.
agitate: /aajateyt/agitates, agitating, agitated;(v) 1. kicin ama baraarujin shacuurta dadweynaha. e.g. He is going to agitate for better conditions for prisoners. 2. isku buugqid; isku dhex yaacid ama welwel ku abuurid. e.g. I don't like to agitate him at this moment.
agitator: /aajateytar/agitators; (n) qofka dadka dareenkooda ama shucuurtooda kiciya. e.g. a political agitator.
agnostic: /aagnastik/agnostics; (n) qof aaminsan inaan la sugi karin jiritaanka eebbe .
ago: /agow/(adv) waqti tagey; waqti ka hor. e.g. I was in Paris five years ago.
agog: /agag/(adj) wax aad u hanwayn tahay oo aad sugaysid inaad ogaatid. e.g. The announcement left the city agog.
agonize: /aaganays/agonizes, agonized, agonizing;(v) 1. wax aad ku wareersan tahay; aad ka fakarsan tahay. e.g. He is agonizing over how to solve this problem. 2. ciqaab; dilliin xanuun badan. e.g. The jailers agonized the prisoners.
agony: /aagani/agonies; (n) xanuun aad u daran maskaxda ama jirka intiisa kale saameeya (sakaraad).
agree: /agrii/agrees, agreeing, agreed;(v) ku raacid; ku waafiqid. e.g. I agree that it is a good solution.
agreeable: /agriiyabal/(adj) wax fiican; laysku raaci karo ama macquul ah. e.g. The idea is agreeable to me.
agreement: /agriimant/ (n) heshiis; wax laysla ogolaaday ama laysku raacay. e.g. This agreement should be cancelled.
agriculture: /aagrikaljar/ (n) beer ama cilmiga beeraha. e.g. This area is suitable for agriculture.
aground: /agrowndh/ (adj) quusid; sida markab ama doon_biyo liqeen. e.g. The ship ran aground.
ague: /aajii/ (n) xummadda malaariyada ama qofka kaneecadu cunto.
ah: /aa/ (inter) (informal) haah ama waayahay oo kale ayaa loo isticmaalaa. e.g. Ah, yes, I remember.
aha: /aaha/(inter) (informal) oraah la isticmaalo markaad wax fahantid ama heshid waxaad raadinaysay. e.g. I had a good book here somewhere. Aha, here we are.
ahead: /aheedh/(adv) hore, xaga hore, madaxa hore; hor marin. e.g. Look ahead while you are driving.
aid: /eydh/aids, aiding aided;(n) 1. gargaar. e.g. overseas aid for the developing countries. (v) 2. gacan siin, caymin. e.g. She will aid anyone who needs her help.
aide: /eydh/(n) kaaliye; qofka gof kale shaqaduu qabto ka caawiya.
AIDS: /eeydhis/ cudur dilaa ah oo jirka — ka dhammeeya unugyada gofka ka difaaca cudurada (Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome).
ail: /eeyl/ailing;(v) 1. jirrasho, xanuunsasho. e.g. This medicine is good for what ails you. (v) 2. dhibid, kadeedid. e.g. What ails you?
ailment: /eeylmant/ailments;(n) jirroaim fudud ama xanuun sahlan. e.g. Childern often have minor ailments.
aim: /eeym/aims, aiming, aimed;(v) 1. ujeeddo, muraad, qasdi. e.g. He is aiming to be a doctor. 2. shiishid, ku abbaarid gori ama buntukh. e.g. You should aim your gun at the target.
aimless: /eeymlis/aimlessly;(adj) ujeeddo la'aan, macna darro. e.g. aimless violence.
air: /eer/airs, airing, aired;(n) hawo, hawada sare. e.g. The air temperature is now 60 degrees celsius.
airborne: /eerboorn/(adj) 1. hawada sare heehaabaya ama bidaya. e.g. The kite was airborne in seconds. 2. hawada sare la xiriira. e.g. airborne troops.
air-conditioned: /eer-kondhishinidh/ (adj) qaboojiye leh; mashiinka hawada qaboojiya leh. e.g. She works in an air-conditioned office.
aircraft: /eerkraft/(n) | dayuurad, diyaarad. e.g. Two aircraft were shot down in the battle.
aircraft carrier: / aircraft carriers;(n) markabka dagaalka ee diyaaradaha qaada ayna ka duulaan/degaana.
airfield: /eerfiildh/airfields;(n) garoon yar oo diyaaraduhu caga dhigtaan kana duulaan.
air hostess: /eer-hostes/air hostesses;(n) gabar diyaaradda rakaabka saaran u adeegta ama u khidmaysa.
airless: /eerless/(adj) hawo yar ama neecaw ku filan aan lahayn. e.g. an airless room.
airline: /eerlayn/airlines;(n) shirkad iska leh diyaaradaha dadka qaada. e.g. Saudi Airline is the best airline in the Middle East.
airmail: /eermeyl/(n) habka warqadaha loogu diro hawada (diyaaradaha iwm) e.g. an airmail envelope.
airplane: /eerpleyn/(n) diyaarad, (dayuurad). e.g. That was his first flight in an airplane.
airport: /eerpoort/(n) garoon dayuuradeed, gagi dayuuradeed, ama madaar. e.g. We landed at the airport in London.
air raid: /eer reydh/air raids;(n) diyaarad ku rushayn ama ku dukhayn (ku weerarid).
air terminal: /eerterminal/air terminals;(n) dhismo ama meel dadka diyaaradda raacaya ku nastaan ama ku sii sugaan duulimaadkooda. e.g. The passengers are still waiting in the air terminal.
air traffic control: / (n) dadka ku shaga leh in ay hagaan diyaaradaha, (sida khadkay qaadanayaan iwm).
airwaves: /eerwayvis/ (n) hirarka raadyaha ama T.V. wax u tabiya.
airy: /eeri/ (adj) 1. hawo neecaw badan leh. e.g. an airy theatre. 2. wax aad fududeysatid ama sahlatid. e.g. He greeted him in an airy way.
aisle: /ayal/aisles; (n) dariiq yar oo dhex mara kuraas lugu fariisto oo saf ah ama iskifaale wax la saarto. e.g. Please clear the aisles.
ajar: /ajaar/ (adj) albaab balagan ama in yar ka furan. e.g. She left the door ajar.
akimbo: /akimbo/ (adj) marka qofku gacmaha dhexda ku haysto. e.g. He stood with his arms akimbo.
akin: /akin/ (adj) 1. isku qoys ah, qaraaba ah. 2. wax is shabbaha, isu eg.
alacrity: /alaakrati/ (n) si xiisa leh hawl u qabasho; xamaasad. e.g. The waiter moved with alacrity because he perceived they were big tippers.
a la mode: /alamood/ (adj) habkii ugu dambeeyey u samaysan; noocii ugu dambeeyey; casri ah.
alarm: /alaarm/alarms, alarming, alarmed; (n) 1. qaylo ama shanqar digniin ama baraarujin leh. e.g. The sound of the fire alarm disturbed her. 2. feejignaan welwel leh. e.g. She looked alarmed after the fire.
alarmclock: /alarm_klok/alarm clocks;(n) saacadda dadka hurdada ka toosisa.
alarmist: /alarmist/alarmists;(n) qofkii ama wixii digniin been ah bixiya. e.g. It is not good to be an alarmist.
alas: /alaas/(inter) haaday (calaamad ama wax cadeynaya murugo, walwal ama shallayto). e.g. There is, alas, a shortage of food in this area.
albatross: /albatroos/albatrosses;(n) 1. shimbir badeed 2. wax ku xayira ama kaa hor istaaga wax aad samayn lahayd.
albeit: /oolbiit/ (conj) hase ahaatee; inkastoo. e.g. There is still a chance, albeit a very small one.
albino: /albayno/albinos; (adj) xayawaan ama qof kulligiis wada cad. e.g. an albino bird.
album: /aalbam/albums;(n) 1. buug masawirada lugu aruuriyo. e.g. My sister has one big album of photographs. 2. saxanka muustikada.
alcohol: /alkahol/(n) aalkolo. e.g I never drink alcohol.
alcoholic: /alkaholik/alcoholics;(n) aalkoliiste, khamriyacab daran. e.g. He has been an alcoholic for ten years.
alert: /alert/alerts, alerting alerted;(adj) digtoon, feejigan; diyaar ah. e.g. This building has an alert security guard.
algebra: /aaljabra/(n) xisaabta aljabrada (waxaa la isticmaalaa, xarfo tiro u taagan).
alibi: /aalabaay/alibis;(n) 1. bariinimo (ka maqnaanshaha meel dambi ka dhacay ama lugu galay). e.g. his alibi for the night of the robbery. 2. cududaar, raalli galin khalad dhacay. e.g. He provided no alibi for his absence.
alien: /eyliyan/aliens;(n) laaji, shisheeye ama qof waddan kale u dhashay. e.g. an illegal alien crossing the border.
alienate: /eyliyeneyt/alienates, alienating, alienated;(v) 1. qof aad xumaantiisa raadisid ama ka cadhaysiisid. 2. dad ka go'id ama ka dhex bixid; kali noolaansho.
alight: /alayt/alights, alighting, alighted;(adj) 1. gubanaya, holcaya ama iftiimaya. e.g. This building has been set alight. (v) 2. ka soo dagid baabuur ama tareen oo kale; ka degid. e.g. to alight from a bus.
align: /alaayn/aligns, aligning, aligned;(v) 1. isku saf noqosho ama isku xulufo. 2. saf gelid ama wax simid; isku toosin. (isku hagaajin).
alike: /alayk/ (adj) isu eg. e.g. Twins always look alike.
alimony: /aalamoni/(n) lacagta ama masruufka loo qoro xaaska markii lays furo. e.g. She receives alimony payments from her ex-husband.
alive: /alayv/(adj) 1. nool, nolol leh; naf ku jirto. e.g. She told me that her mother is still alive. 2. jiritaan leh, firfircoon.
all: /ool/ kulli, dhammaan. e.g. They are all going to the meeting.
allay: /alleey/allays, allaying, allayed; dejin qof xanaaqsanaa ama cabsanayey (yarayn). e.g. He tried to allay her fears.
allege: /alleej/alleges, alleging, alleged: (v) qgof dambi lugu eedeeyey laakiin aan weli lugu caddayn. e.g. She alleged that he stole the money.
allegiance: /allijans/ (n) daacad u noqosho ama taageersanaan; addeecsanaan. e.g. How can we win the allegiance of the people?
alleluia: /aallaluya/ (inter) erey masiixigu u isticmaalaan inay ilaahooda ugu mahad celiyaan (kaniisadda).
allergic: /allerjik/ (adj) alarjiyo (jirka dadka oo wax qoonsada sida daawada, hawada ama cunto). He is allergic to meat.
allergy: /aallarji/allergies; (n) qofka markii wax gaar ah jirkiisu diido ama uu ku jirrado sida cunta qaarkeed ama daawada. e.g. He has an allergy to milk.
alleviate: /alliiviyeyt/alleviates, alleviating, alleviated; (n) yarayn ama dhimid dhibaato ama xanuun horay u jiray (wax ka qabad). e.g. We want to help alleviate the country's drug problem.
alley: /aalli/alleys; (n) surin; dariiq ama wadiigo yar oo dhismayaal ama meel kale dhex marta.
alliance: /allaayanis/alliances; (n) isbahaysi; gaashaanbuur. e.g. a military alliance.
allied: /allaayid/ (adj) midoobid ama is gaashaan buursi. e.g. allied forces.
alligator: /aallageytar/alligators; (n) bahal weyn oo maraykanka laga helo oo yaxaaska u eg.
allocate: /aallakeyt/allocates, allocating, allocated, allocation; (v) u qoondayn, u qorshayn ama ugu tala gelid. e.g. This money was allocated for school expenses.
allot: /allat/allots, allotting, allotted; (v) -qayb u siin; u qorshayn, u xaddidid. e.g. A fixed time is allotted for each person.
allotment: /allatment/allotments; (n) 1. qayb u helid 2. dhul yar oo wax lugu beerto.
allow: /allaw/allows, allowing, allowed; (v) u ogolaansho ama u fasixid. e.g. We decided not to allow smoking.
allowable: /allawabal/ (adj) wax la fasaxay ama faraha laga qaaday, la ogolaaday.
allowance: /allawansi/allowances; (n) lacag luguu siiyo arin darteed, gunno. e.g. the family allowance for single mothers.
all right: /ool rayt/ (adj) 1. hagaagsan ama macquul ah; fiicnaan. e.g. She was feeling sick, but she is all right now. 2. waa hagaag ama waa “okey” All right, what is next?
all-round: /ool-rawnd/ (adj) all-rounder, all-rounders; qof waxyaala badan ku fiican; xirfado badan yaqaan. e.g. an all-round student.
allude: /alluudh/alludes, alluding, alluded; (v) hadal maldihid ama sarbeebid; dul marid.
allure: /alluur/alluring; (n) wax ku soo jiita ama ku xiisa galiya. e.g. the allure of gold and jewels.
allusion: /alluushan/allusions; (n) si dadban wax ugu sheegid ama u dulmarid.
ally: /allaay/allies, allying allied; (v) is bahaysi, isku dad ama isku koox. e.g. our courageous ally.
almighty: /oolmayti/ (adj) awood oo dhan leh; lahaansho aan qiyaas lahayn (magac kale oo ilaah loo yaqaan). e.g. the mercy of the almighty God.
almost: /oolmoost/ (adv) ku dhawaad; ku sigtay; qiyaastil. e.g. Aways spent almost four years in Harlem.
aloft: /alooft/ (adv) wax kor u kacsan ama hawada sare ku laalan (jira). e.g. balloons flying aloft.
alone: /aloon/ (adv) keli ama keli ahaansho. e.g. She wanted to be alone.
along: /aloog/ (prep) 1. dhinac socda ama la bar-bar ah. e.g. along the river side. (adv) 2. wehelin, la socosho. e.g. Ali walked to school along with his friends. 3. dhanka hore (horay).
alongside: /aloongsayd/ (prep) 1. dhinaca isku haya; dhinac socda. e.g. There was a bookstore alongside the theatre. 2. gacmaha is haysta ama iscaawinaya (isla shaqayn kara).
aloof: /aluuf/aloofly, aloofness; (adv) 1. ka yara fog ama ka durugsan. e.g. He stands aloof from other people. (adj) 2. qof xirxiran ama dabeecad qallafsan. e.g. She has an aloof personality.
aloud: /alawdh/ (adv) hadal ku dhawaaqid; kor u dhihid. e.g. You should not speak aloud in public.
alphabetical: /aalfabetikal/alphabetically; (adj) wax laysugu xijiyo sida xarfuhu isugu xigaan. e.g. The words were arranged in alphabetical order.
alpine: /aalpayn/ (adj) 1. wax buuraha dhaadheer ku lug leh 2. dhirta buuraha dushooda ka baxda.
already: /oolredhi/ (adv) mar hore, durbaba (jaa). e.g. She had already left.
also: /oolso/ (adv) waliba ama sidokale; isla markaasna. e.g. Her name is also Deeqa.
alter: /ooltar/alters, altering; altered, alteration; (v) badelid ama isbadelid; wax ka bedelid.
altercation: /ooltarkeyshan/ (n) isku qaylin, ilaaqtan, muran qayla badan leh.
alternative: /oolternativ/alternatively; (adj) wax bedeli kara wax kale ama badal u nogon kara. e.g. People are still looking for an alternative solution.
although: /ooldoo/ (conj) inkastoo. e.g. Although I am sick, I have to go to work.
altitude: /aaltatiyuud/ (n) sare ama sarreeya marka badda laga cabbiro. e.g. Airplanes fly at high altitudes.
altogether: /ooltugethar/(adv) wadajir, dhammaamba, gabiba, kulligoodba; guud ahaan. e.g. I will get $400 a week altogether.
altruism: /altrusam/altruistic; (n) qof aan danayste ahayn ama dadka si daacad ah ula dhaqma; dadka u roon. e.g. His altruism was well- known in the community.
aluminium: /alyuminiyam/ (n) jaandi; macdan bir ah oo laga sameeyo dhariyaasha, fiilooyinka korontada, dayactirka diyaaradaha iwm. e.g. an aluminium frying pan.
always: /oolweys/ (adv) had iyo jeer; mar kasta. e.g. I always go to the library.
/ey em/ (abbr) waqtiga u dhexeeya saqda dhexe ilaa duhurkii 12:00 A.M. e.g. I got up at 9:00 A.M. this morning.
amalgamate: /amaalgameyt/(v) amalgamates, amalgamating, amalgamated; isku darsamid, isu tagid ama hal mid noqosho. e.g. These two companies amalgamated ten years before.
amass: /amaas/amasses, amassing, amassed; (v) isku rasayn ama isku ururin. e.g. When she amassed enough money, she decided to open a business.
amateur: /aamajar/(n) 1. qofka ciyaar(isboorti) ama hawl kale hiwaayadahaan u qabta 2. gof barbarad ah(khibrad aan lahayn).
amaze: /ameys/amazes, amazing, amazed; (v) la yaabid; filan-waa. e.g. She was amazed that I was going to London.
amazement: /ameeysment/ (n) amakaag; u qaadan waa; cajaa'ib. e.g. Ali stood up in amazement.
amazing: /ameysing/amazingly; (adj) wax kaa yaabiya isla markaasna kaa farxiya ama aad ka heshid. e.g. Cairo is an amazing city.
ambassador: /ambaasadar/ambassadors; (n) danjire, safiir ama ambaashatoor. e.g. He is the American Ambassador in London.
amber: /aambar/(n) 1. canbar (bir jaalle iyo maroon isku jir ah oo laga sameeyo luulka). e.g. a dark amber ring 2. midabka huruudda ama jaallaha ah. e.g. The traffic lights continuously switch from green to amber and then red.
ambience: /ambiyens/ (n) bay'ada aad ku nooshahay; hab nololeed ka aad ku dhex jirtid.
ambiguity: /aambagyuwati/ambiguities; (adj) macna badan leh; aan la hubin macnaha, siyaalo badan loo fasiri karo. e.g. There are many ambiguities and contradictions in his speech.
ambiguous: /ambigyuwas/ambiguously; (adj) hadal siyaaba badan loo fahmi karo ama aan caddayn; aan macna sugan lahayn. e.g. The meaning of the story was ambiguous .
ambition: /aambishan/ambitions; (n) hammad, hiyi, laab ku hayn; ku fakarid, higsasho. e.g. My ambition is to be a doctor.
ambivalent: /ambivalent/ambivalence; (adj) caaridsan, kasoo horjeeda. e.g. The government seems ambivalent about its policy toward refugees.
amble: /aambal/ambles, ambling; ambled; (v) laafyood, si raaxa leh u socosho, si dhib yar u socosho ama xarraga leh. e.g. She ambled home through the village.
ambulance: /aambiyalans/ (n) baabuurka gqafilan ee lugu qaado dhaawaca; aanbalaas.
ambush: /aambush/ambushes; ambushing, ambushed; (v) gaadid, (weerar kadis ah ama dhabar jabin). e.g. The enemy was successfully ambushed and defeated.
amen: /eymen/(inter) kalmad la macna ah aammiin oo dadka masiixiga ah yiraahdaan markey ducaysanayaan. e.g. Everyone said amen after the prayer.
amenable: /aminabal/amenably; (adj) loo riyaaqi karo, la ogolaan karo ama macquul ah. e.g. My son was amenable to whatever I said.
amend: /amendh/amends, amending, amended; (v) dib u saxid ama dib u hagaajin.
amendment: /amendhment/amendments; (n) sixid ama hagaajin; wax ku darid ama wax ka badelid qoraal hore ama sharci qornaa. e.g. We made a few amendments to the agreement before signing it.
amenity: /amenati/amenities; (n) meel ama wax lugu raaxo qaato, sida garoon ciyaareed, baar, barkad dabaal iwm e.g. Luxury hotels offer amenities for relaxation and enjoyment.
American: /amerikan/americanism; (n) maraykan (qof maraykan ah, wax Maraykan lugu sameeyey ama laga leeyahay). e.g. She has an American accent.
amiable: /eymiyabal/amiably/ (adj) dabeecad fiican ama qalbi xaaran. e.g. I like her amiable manner.
amicable: /amikabal/amicably; (adj) si saaxiibtinimo leh. e.g. We are trying to solve the problem in an amicable way.
amiss: /amis/ (adv) wax ka khaldan yihiin; okey aan ahayn; khalad ah. e.g. Something went amiss with the agreement.
amity: /amiti/(n) saaxiibtinimo laba qof ama laba waddan.
ammonia: /amoniya/(n) amooniya (beys ama dareere aan midab lahayn oo qarmuun).
ammunition: /aamyanishan/ (n) 1. rasaas ama saanad. 2. kiis ama arin qof lugu soo oogi karo ama lugu qabsan karo.
amnesty: /aamnasti/ (n) cafis guud. e.g. The Egyptian government declared an amnesty for political prisoners.
among: /amaang/amongst; (prep) ku dhex jira ama dhexdooda. e.g. She was among her friends.
amoral: /eymoral/amorality; (adj) qof khalad iyo sax aan kala jeclayn; aan waxba dan ka lahayn.
amorphous: /amoorfas/ (adj) wax aan qaab lahayn ama isku dhex daadsan. e.g. an amorphous cloud.
amount: /amawnt/amounts, amounting, amounted; (n) 1. tiro ama caddad. e.g. I was surprised by the amount of money I had to pay. (v) 2. isku xisaabin ama xisaab. e.g. I have to pay all my bills, which amount to $1000.
amphibian: /aamfibiyan/amphibians, amphibious; (n) xayawaanka berri biyoodka ah sidaraha.
ample: /aampal/amply; (adj) wax kugu filan iyo waliba dheeraad; ku filan kana badan; kifaayo ah. e.g. She had an ample amount of time to prepare.
amplifier: /aamplafaayar/amplifiers; (n) qalab elektroonig ah oo raadyaha iyo samaacadaha codkooda lugu kordhiyo, (xoojiye).
amplify: /aamplafaay/amplifies, amplifying, amplified; (v) 1. siyaadin ama xoojin. (sida codka ama awoodda kor loo qaado raadyaha, samaacadaha iwm). e.g. The signals of this radio should be amplified. 2. faahfaahin fikrad ama gqoraal. e.g. He amplified his ideas later on.
amplification: /aamplafikeyshan/ (n) 1. faahfaahin ama fududayn. 2. xoogsiin ama siyaadin.
amputate: /aampiyateyt/amputates, amputating, amputated; (v) jirka waax ka mid ah oo la gooyo ama la jaro sida gacan ama lug. e.g. His doctor had to amputate his arm.
amputation: /aampiyateyshan/ (n) waax ama qayb jirka ka mid ah goyn (jarid). e.g. According to Islam, punishment for theft is amputation of the hand.
amuse: /amyuus/amuses, amusing, amused; (v) madadaalin, ka farxin ama maaweelin. e.g. He amused the children by telling them funny stories.
amusement: /amyuusment/amusements; (n) 1. farxad gelin, madadaalo ama maaweelo. e.g. Everybody smiled in amusement. 2. hab ama wax waqtiga lugu dilo, waqtiga oo farxad kugu dhaafa (maaweelo darteed). e.g. The. radio was on all day long for their amusement.
an: /an/ (deter) waxaa laga hor mariyaa kalmadaha Ingiriisiga ee shaqalka ka bilowda ama u dhawaaqa eg sida 'a'
anachronism: /anaakranism/anachronism, anachronistic;(n) wax duug ah, da' weyn ama aan casri ahayn.
anaemia: /aniimiya/anemia; (n) dhiig yaraan; unugyada cas ee dhiigu ku yar yahay.
anaemic: /aneemik/anemic; (adj) 1. qofka dhiig yarida qaba 2. qof midabkiisu badalmay ama, diif ka muugato.
anaesthesia: /aanastiisha/ (n) gof in la suuxiyo; suuxin; dareen la'aan.
anaesthetic: /aanastheetik/anaesthetics; anaesthetic; (n) suuxiye (daawo qofka lugu suuxiyo). e.g. This operation can't be done without an anaesthetic.
anaesthetize: /aanasthetays/anaesthetizes, anaesthetizing, anaesthetized; (v) suuxin. e.g. He was anaesthetized during the surgery.
anagram: /aanagraam/anagrams; (n) xarfaha erey ka kooban yahay oo marka la kala qalibo ama lays daba mariyo sameeya erey kale. e.g. “Cat” is ananagram of “act”.
anal: /eynal/ (adj) wax futada ama dabada ku shaqa leh ama ku lug leh.
analogous: /anaalajas/ (adj) isku yara eg ama qaybo iska shabbaha, isku dhigma.
analogy: /anaalaji/analogies; (n) 1. isu ekaan, is shabihid. e.g. There is a close analogy between the two. 2. isbarbar dhigid ama caddayn meel laba wax isaga eg yihiin. e.g. He made an analogy between math and accounting.
analyse: /aanalaays/analyses, analysed; (v) imtixaanid, baarid ama lafagurid. e.g. He analysed the sample of this medicine.
analysis: /anaalasis/analyses; (n) baaritaan ama kala dhig-dhigid. e.g. Your analysis of the situation was very accurate.
analyst: /aanalist/analysts; (n) qofka wax baara ama u kuur gala. e.g. He is a political analyst.
analytic: /aanalitik/analytical; (adj) lafagurid ama baaritaan ku salaysan. e.g. You need an analytical mind to solve this problem.
anarchism: /aanarkism/ (n) fikrad siyaasadeed oo aaminsan in xukuumad aan loo baahnayn, taageertana iskaa wax u qabso.
anarchy: /aanarki/anarchic; (n) sharci la'aan ama nidaam darro; dawlad la'aan.
anarchist: /anarkist/anarchists anarchistic; (n) qofka sharciga ku tunta ama aan sharciga raacin; sharci raac la'aan. e.g. An anarchist believes in no government.
anathema: /anathima/ (n) 1. qof ama wax aad karaahiyaysato; nacayb badan. e.g. Discrimination is anathema to him. 2. cayda, af xumada ama waxyaabaha lugu dambaabo. e.g. Repentance is allowed after you commit an anathema.
anatomical: /anatoomikal/ (adj) wax la xiriira dhismaha jirka ee xayawaanka ama dadka. e.g. All females have the same anatomical features.
anatomy: /anaatami/anatomies; (n) 1. habka dhismaha jirka ee xayawaanka. e.g. the anatomy of a monkey. 2. cilmiga dhismaha jirka. e.g. He is an anatomy teacher.
ancestor: /aansestar/ (n) awoowayaasha qof ku abtirsado, qof tafiirtiis, 2. meeshii wax ka soo unkameen ama ka soo bilowdeen.
ancestry: /aansestari/ancestries; (n) qof abtirsiinyihiis; abkiis iyo awoowgiis; qof asalkiis.
anchor: /aankar/anchors, anchoring, anchored; (v) 1. baroosin (birta markabka ama doonta dhulka loogu xiro si uu wu istaago). 2. meel ku xirid ama silsiladayn.
anchovy: /aanjovi/ (n) kalluun yar oo suugada laga samaysto (dhanaan leh).
ancient: /eynshant/(adj) qadiim ah; waa hore jiri jiray. e.g. ancient Egyptians.
ancillary: /aansaleri/(adj) 1. caawiye guud ama qofka qabta shaqooyinka hoose sida nadaafadda ama xammaaliga iwm. e.g. college ancillary workers 2. siyaado ah.
and: /aandh/ (conj) 1. iyo. e.g. I like my mother and my father. 2. ka dib. e.g. I entered the office and sat down.
androgynous: /adraajanas/ (adj) labeeb ama noole dheddig iyo laboodba ah.
anecdotal: /aanikdootal/ (adj) dhacdo ama sheeko faah faahsan. e.g. The evidence to support his theory was anecdotal, not empirical.
anemometer: /anamometer/ (n) qalab lugu cabbiro xawaaraha dabaysha ama hawada.
anew: /aniyuu/ (adv) cusayb; dib u bilaabid ama wax aad mar kale biloowdid ayagoo cusub. e.g. After a short ceasefire, fighting started anew.
angel: /eynjal/ angels; (n) 1. maalaa'ig, (adj) 2. qofka naxariista badana waa lugu matalaa.
angelic: /anjelik/ (adj) qofka naxariista badan oo aad u fiican.
anger: /aangar/angers, angering, angered; (n) caro, cadho ama xanaaq. e.g. His tone of voice suggested anger.
angle: /aangal/angles, angling, angled; (n) 1. xagal. e.g. a right angle of 90 degrees 2. arrinta meesha aad ka eegtid; aragtidaada. e.g. You should look at it from a different angle.
angler: /aanglar/ (n) qofka kalluunka ama malayga dabta hiwaayad ahaan.
Anglican: /aangelikan/(n) qofka masiixiga ah ee xubin ka ah kaniisadda ingiriiska. e.g. Anglican Church in Canada.
Anglicize: /aanglisays/anglicizes, anglicizing, anglicized; (v) dhaqan, fikrad ama erey lugu badalo mid ingiriiska laga leeyahay; ingirlisiyeyn.
anglo: /aangaloo/ (pref) wax ingiriiska ku lug leh ama waddanka ingiriiska la xiriira. e.g. Anglo-French agreement.
angry: /aangari/angrier, angriest; (adj) caroonaya, caraysan, ama xanaaqsan. e.g. He was angry at me.
anguish: /aangwish/anguished; (n) xanuun aad u daran, gaar ahaan xanuunka maskaxda, maskax xanuun (maskax wareer). e.g. She attended a debate which caused her intense unhappiness and anguish.
angular: /aangyalar/ (adj) xaglo leh, cirifyo leh, xaglaysan. e.g. an angular structure.
animal: /aanamal/ (n) 1. xayawaan. e.g. They used to hunt wild animals for food. (adj) 2. qofka caqliga xun ama caaqa ah.
animate: /aanamit/animates, animating, animated; ((adj) 1. nool, naf ku jirto. e.g. Is the object animate or inanimate? (v) 2. xiisa gelin, firfircooni ama xaraarad u yeelid. e.g. Joy animated his face. (v) 3. kicin, ku dhiirrin. e.g. His actions were animated by revenge.
animated: /anameytidh/ animatedly; (adj) wax dhaqdhaqaaq leh ama xiisa leh. e.g. We had an animated discussion about politics.
animation: /aanameyshan/ (n) 1. filin kartuun leh ama jinijini leh; masawiro leh. e.g. He drew an animation of the story. 2. dhaqdhaqaaq ama xarakaad leh. e.g. He was talking with animation.
animosity: /anamosati/animosities; (n) nacayb ama nebcaysi xoog leh. e.g. South Africa experienced racial and religious animosities.
ankle: /aankal/ankles; (n) canqow, oday-kaboohis (meesha cagta cad iyo lugta isku xirta). e.g. Amal is feeling pain on her ankle.
annex: /annekis/annexes, annexing, annexed; (v) 1. la wareegid (waddan ama dal) xoog lagu qabsaday. e.g. Kuwait was annexed by Iraq in 1990. (n) 2. dhismo ku dhagan dhimso kale ama wax lugu dhejiyey wax kale (lugu darro). e.g. This hall is an annex to the hotel.
annexation: /annekseyshan/(n) xoog ku qabsasho; boobid, qaramayn. e.g. Annexation of Kuwait was unacceptable to the rest of the world.
annihilate: /annayaleyt/annihilates, annihilating, annihilated; (n) 1. baabi'in, xasuugid ama tirtirid. e.g. Human beings could be annihilated if a nuclear weapon is used. 2. ka rayn, jabin ama ka guulaysasho. e.g. The Democratic party was annihilated in the 1990 election.
anniversary: /aannaversari/anniversaries; (n) sannad guuro. e.g. Yesterday was his wedding anniversary.
announce: /annawnsi/announces, announcing, announced; (v) ku dhawaagid ama shaac ka qaadid. e.g. It was announced that the President would address the nation.
announcer: /annawnsar/ (n) qofka xiriiriyaha ka ah raadyaha ama telefishinka (xirlirilye ama wariye). e.g. Ubax is an announcer on American radio.
annoy: /annooy/annoys, annoying, annoyed; (v) ka xanaajin ama ka cadhaysiin. e.g. He annoys her because he calls late in the night.
annoyance: /annooyans/ (n) xanaaq ama cadho. e.g. She felt annoyance with his bad habits.
annual: /aannyuwal/annuals, annually; (adj) sanadle ama wax sannad kasta mar dhaca. e.g. The annual meeting of the United Nations will be held in Geneva.
anomalous: /anaamalas/ (adj) wax sida caadiga ah ka duwan. e.g. These results are anomalous.
anomaly: /anamali/ anomalies; (n) wax sidii loogu tala galay ama ay ahaan jireen ka duwan; aan caadi ahayn, aan xaq ahayn. e.g. His unusually low test score was an anomaly.
anon: anon 1/anoon/ (adv) si dhakhsa leh ama ciyoow. e.g. I will see you anon.
anon 2/anoon/ (abbr) aan la aqoon qoraaga magaciisa “anonymous” oo la soo gaabiyey.
anonymity: /aananimati/ (n) qof magaciis ama aqoonsigiis oo aan la hayn ama aan la sheegin (la qariyo). e.g. the anonymity of the writer.
anonymous: /ananimas/anonymously; (adj) 1. magac la', magaca oo laqariyo ama aan la sheegin. e.g. I received an anonymous letter. 2. caadi iska ah ama aan lahayn wax gaar u ah. e.g. I visited an anonymous little town.
anorak: /anoorak/anoraks; (n) jaakad roobka celin karta oo leh madax-gashi.
another: /anadar/ (pron) mid kale. e.g. Can you get me another cup of water?
answer: /ansar/answers, answering, answered; (v) 1. jawaabid, ka jawaabid, laga jawaabo. e.g. I answered all the questions.(n) 2. jawaab (n) 3. xal ama daawo. e.g. What do you think is the answer for this crisis?
answerable: /aansarabal/ (adj) 1. laga jawaabi karo. e.g. These questions are not answerable. 2. mas'uul ka ah. e.g. Parents are answerable for the actions of the children.
antagonism: /aantaganism/ (n) iska soo horjeeda ama cadow isku ah. e.g. the antagonism between a democracy and a dictatorship.
antagonistic: /aantaganistik/ (adj) qofka ku neceb ama kula dagaalsan. e.g. Some of the students are antagonistic toward the teacher.
antagonize: /aantaganays/antagonizes; antagonizing, antagonized; (v) qof aad dagaalkiisa raadisid ama aad ka xanaajisid, xumaan abuurid. e.g. She antagonizes her father by beating her little sister.
antecedent: /aantasiidant/ (n) 1. hordhac ama wax kale ka horeeya (badanaa u eg) (n) 2. awoowayaashii hore, abtirsiinyo.
antelope: /aantaloop/antelopes; (n) xayawaan deerada u eg oo leh lugo iyo geeso dheerdheer.
antenna: /aantena/antennae, antennas; (n) 1. bir yar oo laga taago raadyaha, T.V. ga ama guryaha si ay hirarka ama mawjadaha warka usoo jiido. (anteeno). e.g. We need an antenna for our T.V. (n) 2. geeso yara fiiqan oo cayayaanka qaarkiis wax ku dareemo. e.g. These insects have very sensitive antenna.
anteroom: /antiruum/ (n) qolka sugidda, nasashada ama qolka barsadda ah. e.g. They were waiting in an anteroom before the meeting.
anthem: /aantham/anthems; (n) hees, muusig ama madiix loogu tala galay wax gaar ah ama dhacda gaar. e.g. I like our national anthem.
ant hill: / ant hills or ant-hill; (n) duddun, duddumo, hoy quraanjadu dhisato.
anthology: /anthalaji/anthologies; (n) isku duwid ama isu uruurin qoraalo dad kale duwan qoreen, oo lugu qoro hal buug. e.g. an anthology of Somali songs.
anthropologist: /anthrapolajist/ qofka barta ama ku takhasusa dadka iyo dhaqamadooda. e.g. He is a Somali anthropologist.
anti: /anti/ (pref) ku lid ah, ka soo horjeeda; ka hortagi kara. e.g. anti-apartheid movements.
antibiotic: /antibayatik/ (n) daawo kiniini, sharoobbo ama irbad ah oo disha jeermiska cudurada (bakteeriya).
anticipate: /aantisapayt/anticipates, anticipating, anticipated; (v) 1. rajayn; sugid wax dhici doona. e.g. I spent more money this month than I anticipated. (v) 2. odorosid ama qiyaasid wax dhici doona hadanaanticipation laysku diyaariyo (laga feejignaado). e.g. I anticipate that it would rain so I will take an umbrella.
anticipation: /aantisapeyshan/ (n) wax si farxad leh aad u sugaysid; aad si weyn u rajeynaysid. e.g. I was looking forward with eager anticipation to receiving her letter.
anticlimax: /aantklaymakis/anticlimaxes; (n) wax adigoo faraxsan kugu qaboojiya farxadda ama sidii aad filaysay aan nogon; niyad jab. e.g. The rain during our picnic was anticlimax.
anti-clockwise: /aantiklakways/ (adv) dhanka saacaddu u socoto maahee dhanka kale u socda. e.g. This machine travels in an anti-clockwise direction.
antics: /aantiks/ (n) 1. majaajillo ama waxyaabo kale oo aan caadi ahayn oo dadka looga qosliyo ama looga yaabiyo. e.g. the antics of the President's policy. 2. fal-foolxun.
antidote: /aantidowt/antidotes; (n) 1. daawo loo adeegsado lidka sunta ama ka hortagga sunta. e.g. Antidotes are necessary to counteract poisons. 2. wax dhibaato jirtay kaa caawiya ama kaa xalliya. e.g. Agriculture could be an antidote for the food shortage.
antipathy: /antipathi/antipathetic; (n) qof ama wax naftaadu karaahiyaysato, nacayb siyaado ah; aadan ka helin. e.g. My former friend feels antipathy toward me.
antiquarian: /antikuwaariyan/ (adj) alaab qadiim ah oo aan saas suuqa looga helin; taariikh hore leh. e.g. My brother owns an antiquarian book shop in London.
antiquated: /antikwaytid/ (adj) wax da' wayn oo aad qadiim u ah. e.g. He strongly believed antiquated ideas about science.
antique: /antiik/antiques; (n) alaab qadiim ah isla markaasna qaali ah. e.g. This old vase is an antique.
antiquity: /antikwati/antiquities; (n) wax taariikh hore leh; raad taariikheed ka muuqdo.
anti-Semitism: /antisematisam/ (n) yuhuud nacaybka; yuhuudda oo la karaahiyaysto.
antiseptic: /antiseptik/ (n) jeermis-reeb (daawo disha jeermiska iyo bakteeriyada). e.g. He washed his face with antiseptic soap.
anti-social: /antisoshal/ (adj) 1. qofka gooni socodka ah; xirxiran. e.g. He has always been an anti-social person. 2. dabeecad dadku dhibsadaan; bulshada u daran.
antithesis: /aantithesis/antitheses; (n) lid ku ah; si toos ah uga soo hor jeeda.
antler: /antlar/antlers; (n) geeso iska dul baxa sida kuwa deerada oo kale.
antonym: /aantanim/ (n) erayga lidka u ah eray kale. e.g. Aged is the antonym of young.
anvil: /aanvil/ (n) dubbe ama birta biraha lugu dul tumo.
anxiety: /aangsaayati/anxieties; (n) arin ama xaalad laga walaaco waxa dhici doona; laga walwalo. e.g. increasing anxiety over inflation.
anxious: /aangshas/anxiously; (adj) ka walaacsan; ka wareersan; ka xun. e.g. He is anxious about his future.
any: /eni/ (pron) 1. walba; kasta. e.g. You can ask any of them. 2. midna; waxna. e.g. I don't want any of these books.
anybody: /enibadhi/ (pron) qof walba; qof kasta. e.g. You can call anybody.
anyhow: /enihaaw/ (adv) si kasta; si walba ha ahaatee. e.g. I have doneanyone my homework anyhow.
anything: /enithing/ (pron) wax kasta, wax walba, waxba. e.g. I don't have anything for you.
anywhere: /eniweer/ (adv) meel walba; meelna. e.g. can't go anywhere.
apart: /apart/ (adv) 1. kala durugsan; kala fog. e.g. My boyfriend and I have grown apart. 2. kala go' san, kala nool ama kala baxsan. e.g. Their relationship began to fall apart.
apartheid: /apartheyd/ (n) midab kala sooc; midab takoor. e.g. apartheid system in South Africa.
apartment: /apartmant/apartments; (n) guri dabakh ah (qol ama qolal degaan oo dabakh ama dhismo weyn ka mid ah). e.g. I pay $1000 for my one bedroom apartment.
apathetic: /apathetik/apathetically; (adj) qof aan waxba dan ka lahayn ama qof raja xun, aan waxba kala jeclayn. e.g. He failed his exam and became apathetic about his future.
apathy: /apathi/ (n) wax aadan ku niyad fiicnayn ama aadan kala jeclayn.
ape: /eyb/ apes, aping, aped; (n) 1. daanyeer aan daba lahayn; goriilla 2. jilid; canjilid ama iska yeelyeelid 3. qof caaq ah; caqlixun.
aperitif: /aperatif/aperitifs; (n) cabbitaan khamri ah oo la cabbo cuntada ka hor.
aperture: /aparjar/apertures; (n) dalool yar ah oo ay wax mari karaan sida daloolka kaamarada oo wax laga eego.
apex: /eypekis/apexes; (n) halka ugu sarraysa; fiinta. e.g. at the apex of his pleasure.
aphrodisiac: /afradisiyak/ (aa) cunto, cabbid ama kiniini, qof ku kacsado ama jeclaysiiya inuu galmoodo.
apiece: /apiis/ (adv) tiro ama qayb is le'eg oo gof kasta loo siiyo si is le'eg. e.g. My mother gave us $200 apiece.
aplomb: /aploomb/ (n) wax aad kalsooni buuxda ku samaysid; kalsooni ku jirto. e.g. He presented his speech with great aplomb.
apolitical: /apalitikal/ (adj) qofka aan siyaasadda jeclayn. e.g. He became apolitical after World War II.
apologetic: /aapolajetik/apologetically; (adj) in aad gof dareensiisid in aad ka xun tahay sida wax u dhaceen ama khalad aad gashay; ka xumaansho. e.g. She was apologetic about her absence at the meeting.
apologize: /apolajays/apologizes, apologized, apologizing, apologise; (v) raalli gelin ama khalad ka soo nogosho. e.g. He apologized for his rudeness.
apology: /apolaji/apologies; (n) raalli gelin samayn; cududaar samayn. e.g. She sent a letter of apology to the manager.
appal: /appool/appals, appalling, appalled, appellant appals; (v) wax aad ka walwashid, aad ka walaacdid ama aad ka xumaatid. e.g. We were appalled to hear this kind of news.
appalling: /appoolling/appallingly; (adj wax walaac leh ama walwal kugu abuuraya; aad iyo aad u xun. e.g. They live in appalling conditions.
apparatus: /aapparaatas/ (n) 1. qalab loogu tala galay in lugu qabto shaqa gaar ah. e.g. I am going to buy some gym apparatus. 2. habka ama nidaamka hawl gaarihi u socoto. e.g. I can't understand the whole apparatus of this company.
apparent: /appaarant/apparently; (adj) 1. si qeexan loo arki karo ama si cadapparition loo fahmi karo. e.g. He committed the crime for no apparent reason. 2. wax aad dareensan tahay ama kuu muuqda laakiin aadan runtooda hubin. e.g. Police are investigating some apparent contradictions.
apparition: /appaarishan/apparitions; (n) khayaali ama wax riyo oo kale aad ku aragtid. e.g. I have seen a strange apparition in the middle of the night.
appeal: /appiil/appeals, appealing, appealed; (n) 1.rafcaan, codsasho dacwadaada dib loo qaado. e.g. She took the appeal to the Supreme Court of Canada. (n) 2. codsi degdeg ah; gof aad sharaftiisa wax ku waydiisatid. e.g. She made an appeal for funds to build a new school. (v) 3. wax ku soo jiita ama aad danaynaysid. e.g. This idea appealed to me.
appear: /appiir/appears, appearing, appeared; (v) muuqasho, la arko, soo bannaan bixid. e.g. A man suddenly appeared from the dark.
appearance: /appiiransi/appearances; (n) 1. muugaal, muugasho. e.g. He likes her appearance. (n) 2. soo bixid. e.g. With the appearance of computers, many people lost their jobs.
appease: /appiis/appeases, appeasing, appeased; (v) xanaaq ka bi'in; aamusin ama qaboojin gof cadhaysnaa. e.g. I will bring him a gift to appease his anger.
appetite: /appatayt/appetites; (n) 1. rabitaanka cunada 2. wax si fiican aad u rabtid ama ugu baahan tahay.
appetizing: /appataysing/appetizer; (adj) wax cuntada kuu fura ama ku jeclaysiiya. e.g. It was an appetizing meal.
applaud: /apploodh/applauds, applauding, applauded; (v) 1. u sacabin; sacab ku taageerid. e.g. The whole community applauded him. 2. si xamaasad leh u soo dhawayn, taageerid. e.g. The recent news will be applauded by everyone.
applause: /apploos/ (n) si xamaasad leh ugu sacab tumid, u sacabin (v) 2. taageerid ama addeecid.
apple: /aappal/apples; (n) tufaax. e.g. It is good for your health to eat one apple a day.
appliance: /applaayansi/ (n) qalab farsamo ama qalab guriyeed sida qaboojiyaha, kariyaha iwm. e.g. Our apartment needs a major appliance such as a washer or a refrigerator.
applicable: /applikabal/ (adj) loo isticmaali karo; ku haboon ama lugu dabakhi karo. e.g This new law is not applicable to overseas students.
applicant: /applikant/applicants; (n) codsade, musharrax. e.g. There is no applicants for this position.
application: /applikeyshan/applications; (n) 1. codsi, arji. e.g. We received 200 applications within two days. 2. isticmaalid ama dabakhaad.
applied: /applaaydh/ (adj) la dabakho ama si ficil ahaan ah loo sameeyo. e.g. applied arts and science.
apply: /applaay/applies, applying, applied; (v) 1. arji u qorasho codsi u gudbin. e.g. He applied to Oxford University. 2. marin, dhayid ama isticmaalid. e.g. You need to apply this cream on your leg. 3. wax ama sharci lugu dabikhi karo ama loo adeegsan karo. e.g. This system will apply to you.
appoint: /appooynt/appoints, appointing, appointed; (v) 1. jago u magacaabid; xil u dhiibid. e.g. He was appointed vice president. 2. wakhti u qabasho, ballamin. e.g. We should arrive at the appointed time.
appointment: /appooyntment/appointments; (n) 1. ballan ama waqti la ballamo, cahdi. e.g. I have an appointment with my doctor. 2. jago u magacaabid. e.g. He received a temporary appointment as manager for the company.
appraisal: /apreysal/appraisals; (n) qiimayn ama wax aad qiyaastid qiimaha uu ku fadhiyo. e.g. an appraisal of used cars.
appraise: /appreys/appraises, appraising, appraised; (v) qiimayn ama fikrad ka bixin. e.g. He appraised his house at $100,000.
appreciate: /apprishiyeyt/appreciates, appreciating, appreciated; (v) 1. maqsuud ( raalli ka nogosho) 2. u mahadnaq.
