apprehension: /aapprihenshan/apprehensions; 1. wax aad ka cabsi qabtid mustaqbalka. e.g. Her apprehension about her future was obvious. 2. fikrad ka qaadasho, fahmid. e.g. I have no clear apprehension of the situation.
apprehensive: /apprihensiv/apprehensively; (adj) qof ka cabsi qaba wax dhici doona. e.g. He was apprehensive about the whole situation.
apprentice: /apprentis/apprentices; (n) qofka u shaqeeya inuu shaqada wax ka barto, xirfad ka barto. e.g. This will be my final year as an apprentice.
apprenticeship: /apprentisiship/apprenticeships; (n) tababar, xirfad barasho. e.g. He is serving his apprenticeship as a mechanic.
approach: /approwj/approaches, approaching, approached; (v) 1. ku soo dhawaansho; ku sii dhawaad. e.g. My wife opened the door for me as I approached. 2. qaabilaad, qof arin aad kala hadashid ama ku soo qaadid. e.g. I wanted to approach the manager with a suggestion. We need a new approach to this problem.
approachable: /approwjabal/ (adj) 1. qof fur-furan ama bulshay ah; si sahlan loola gabsan karo. e.g. She was a very approachable girl. 2. meel dariiq sahlan oo loo maro leh.
appropriate: /approopiriyeyt/appropriates, appropriating, appropriated; (adj) 1. ku haboon; ku fiican; loogu talo galay. e.g. It was an appropriate time to talk about this subject. (v) 2. wax aadan lahayn oo aad qaadatid; xalaalaysatid. e.g. She appropriated the money she borrowed.
appropriation: /approopiryeyshan/ (n) u qoondayn ama u qgorshayn. e.g. The company makes appropriations for different departments.
approval: /appruuval/ (n) ogolaansho, yeelid ama ansixin. e.g. He gave his approval for the treaty.
approve: /appruuv/approves, approving, approved; (v) 1. aqbalid ama yeelid. e.g. I approved his proposal after I examined it. (v) 2. ka maqsuudis ama u guuxid. e.g. My teacher did not approve of my book.
approximate: /appraksameyt/approximates, approximated, approximating; (adj) qiyaas ahaan ama aad ugu dhow. e.g. The approximate value of my car is $4000.
approximately: /appraksameytli/approximation; (adv) qiyaastii, ugu dhawaan. e.g. I have approximately 100 books.
april: /eypril/ (n) Abriil, bisha afraad ee taariikhda miilaadiga. e.g. My sister will be ten next April.
apron: /eypran/aprons; (n) dufan-dhowr (maro dharka laga dul xirto markii wax la karinayo ama la shaqaynayo). e.g. She wore a white apron while she was cooking.
apt: /aapt/aptly; (adj) 1. sida badan, badanaaba; wax damac-sanaan, maaganaan. e.g. Small businesses in big cities are apt to grow fast. 2. ku haboon. e.g. It is an apt examination. 3. fahma badan,maskax furan, xariif ah. e.g. He is an apt pupil.
aptitude: /aptatiyuudh/aptitudes; (n) awood dabiici ah oo xaga aqoonta ah; ku fiicnaan. e.g. She had an aptitude for arts.
aquarium: /akwaariyam/aquaria, aquariums; (n) weel weyn ama meel biyo lugu shubay oo kalluun ama xayawaan kale lugu hayo.
aquatic: /akwaatik/ (adj) 1. xayawaanka ama dhirta biyaha ku nool 2. wax biyo la xiriira.
aqueduct: /akwaadakt/aqueducts; (n) 1. tog ama kanaal biyo ka soo shubmaan; biyo dhac leh. 2. buundo biyo dhac dul marta oo aargooyin leh.
Arab: /aarab/arabs; (n) gof carab ah ama waddan carbeed. e.g. She is an Arab living abroad.
Arabian: /areybiyan/ (adj) wax carab la xiriira ama ku lug leh. e.g. the Arabian desert.
Arabic: /aarabik/ (adj) afka Carabiga ama wax kale oo carab leedahay. e.g. I like to learn the Arabic language.
arable: /aarabal/ (adj) dhul ku haboon bacriminta, beerista. e.g. arable land.
arbiter: /aarbater/ (n) dhex-dhexaadiye, u gar qaade, kala saare. e.g. An arbiter is needed for this kind of dispute.
arbitrary: /aarbatrari/ (adj) 1. go'aan ama fikrad aan sabab ku salaysnayn ama aan si fiican looga fiirsan. - (go'aan layska gaaray). e.g. An arbitrary decision was made.
arbitrate: /aarbatreyt/arbitrates, arbitrated, arbitrating; (v) u gar qaadid ama u gar niqid, kala saarid. e.g. He arbitrated the dispute between his children.
arbitration: /aarbatrayshan/ (n) gar qaadid ama heshiisiin; dhexdhexaadin. e.g. Both sides in the conflict have agreed to go to arbitration.
arc: /aark/ (n) qaanso ama wax sida qaansada u samaysan; dhig.
arcade: /arkeydh/ (n) 1. aargo (dhismo daboolan oo qaanso ama dhig oo kale u dhisan). e.g. a big shopping arcade. 2. goob maaweelo. e.g. video game arcade.
arch: /aarj/ (n) 1. dhismo dariiq ama waddo laga dul dhisay oo sidii qaanso oo kale u dhisan. e.g. I walked through an arch to get to the shopping centre.(v) 2. soo laabid, ama soo qalloocin. e.g. She arched her back.
archaeology: /arkiyolaji/archaecology; (n) cilmiga barashada dadkii hore ayadoo la darsayo waxyaabihii ay ka tageen sida dhismayaasha qadiimka ah.
archaeologist: /arkiyolajist/archaeologists, archaeological; (n) qofka barta cilmiga hab nololeedkii dadkii hore.
archaic: /arkeyik/ (adj) wax ama shay aad u qadiim ah, aad u da' weyn. e.g. Archaic language is found in the Bible.
archbishop: /arshibishop/ (n) wadaadka ugu sarreeya diinta masiixiga ee waddan ama gobol.
arched: /arjid/ (adj) 1. dhismo sida qaansada u dhisan oo daboola dariiq, irid ama daaqad. e.g. the arched structure over the doorway. 2. wax soo laaban ama xoodan. e.g.archeology her arched black eyebrows.
archer: /arjar/archers; (adj) qofka qaansada iyo fallaarta (leeb) wax ku toogta (isticmaala).
archery: /arjari/ (n) cayaar lugu cayaaro qaanso iyo fallaar (lugu shiishtamo).
archetype: /aarjitayp/archetypes, archetypal; (n) tusaale fiican u noqon kara; matali kara.
archipelago: /arkapelajo/archipelagos; (n) dhawr jasiiradood oo yar-yar ah. e.g. the Canadian archipelago of the far north.
architect: /arkatekt/ (n) 1. qofka sawira naqshadaha dhismayaasha. e.g. He is a great architect. 2. qofka wax soo saaara, abuura ama sabab u noqda in waxaasi dhacaan. e.g. He was the real architect of modern arts.
architectural: /arkatekjaral/ (adj) wax ku lug leh ama la xiriira naqshad samaynta ama dhismayaasha. e.g. An architectural award was given to him.
architecture: /arkatekjar/ (n) habka loo sameeyo naqshadaha iyo dhismayaasha.
archive: /arkeyv/archives; (n) ururin ama meel lugu kaydiyo warqadaha iyo warbixinada ku saabsan shirkad, dawlad ama dad gaar ah; (arkiifiyo, xusuus-dhig). e.g. The archives of the company were moved from the headquarters.
arguable: /argiyuwabal/arguably; (adj) muran ka taagan yahay, shaki ku jiro ama caddayn u baahan. e.g. It is an arguable issue.
argue: /arg yuu/argues, arguing, argued; (v) murmid ama doadid. e.g. She always argues with her little sister.
argument: /arg yumant/arguments; (n) muran, dood ama ilaaq. e.g. I agreed with him without argument.
argumentative: /argyumentativ/ (adj) armistice muranlow ama qof dood badan.
arid: /aarid/aridity;(adj) 1. dhul lama dagaan u eg oo aan dhir ka bixi karin (qalalan). e.g. Most of our country is arid or semi-arid. 2. qoraal ama mawduuc aan xiisa lahayn. e.g. I have read an article in the paper which was very arid and boring.
arise: /araays/arises, arising, arose, arisen/araysan/ (v) soo baxay, bilaabmay, dhashay ama soo shaac baxay. e.g. We will request his services if the need arises.
aristocracy: /aarastakarsi/ (n) dabaqadda sare ee bulsho ama dadka magaca dheer ama reer boqor ah. e.g. Saudi arabian aristocracy.
aristocrat: /aristakrat/aristocrats; aristocratic; (n) qof ka dhashay reer magac cheer.
arithmetic: /arithmatik/arithmetical; (n) xisaab fallo (qaybta xisaabta sida kudar, ka jar, kudhufo, u qaybi). e.g. I am good at arithmetic.
arm: /arm/arms; (n) gacan ama wax gacan shabbaha. e.g. He put his arms around the child and kissed him.
armament: /armament/ (n) 1. hub ama qalab ciidan. 2. difaac; kordhin qalabka iyo hubka ciidamada. e.g. Some countries spend more on armaments than on agriculture.
armchair: /armjeer/ (n) kursi raaxa leh oo leh laba meelood oo gacmaha la saarto.
armed: /aarmid/ (adj) qof ama ciidan hubaysan. e.g. She was assaulted by an armed man.
armed forces: / aamid forsis/ (n) ciidamada qalabka sida; hubaysan.
armful: /aarmful/armfuls; (n) gacan muggeed, wax gacan ama labadaba buuxin kara. e.g. She was given an armful of fruits.
armistice: /armastis/armistices; (n) heshiis xabbad joojin, lagana wada hadlo sidii nabad lugu gaari lahaa. e.g. Our ambassador in Ethiopia made an offer of an armistice.
armour: /armar/ (n) gaashaan ama qalab aan xabbadu karin. e.g. He was arrested by a police officer wearing soft body armour.
armoured: /aarmardh/(adj) gaashaaman ama aan xabbadu karin. e.g. armoured cars.
armpit: /aarmpit/armpits; (n) kilkisha ama shakhfasha. e.g. He had an itch in his armpit.
army: /aarmi/ (n) 1. ciidan hubaysan oo tababaran, millatari. e.g. He spent ten years in the army. 2. dad, xayawaan ama wax sidii ciidan isugu xidhan.
aroma: /arooma/aromas; (n) udgoon ama caraf, gaar ahaan midka cuntada (sanuunad). e.g. I bought a coffee with a fine aroma.
aromatic: /aramaatik/ (adj) udgoon badan, aad u carfaya. e.g. This flower is highly aromatic.
around: /arawndh/ (adv) 1.wareegsan. e.g. My house measures 50 metres around. (v) 2. war-wareegid. e.g. Stick around here and I will see you in 15 minutes. (adv) 3. qiyaas ahaan, giyaastii. e.g. He has around $1000 in the bank.
arousal: /arowsal/ (n) dareen kicin; hiyi kac. e.g. She had no feelings of sexual arousal while she was being raped.
arouse: /arows/arouses, arousing, aroused; (v) 1. wax dareenkaaga ama niyadaada kiciya, hiyi kicin. e.g. He told me that he was aroused by her perfume. 2. hurdo ka toosin. e.g. She was aroused from sleep.
/ (abbr) waa “arrives” oo la soo gaabiyey loona isticmaalo marka bas, tareen ama diyaaradi imaanayso.
arrange: /arreynji/arranges, arranged, arranging; (v) 1. habayn, isku duwid ama diyaarin (gorshayn). e.g. Call me tomorrow and we will arrange a meeting. 2. wax la safay ama si habaysan loo dhigay. e.g. I started arranging my books on the shelf.
arranged marriage: / (n) guurka waaridku isku daro labada gof, laysu doono.
arrangement: /arreynjimant/ (n) 1. qorshe samayn; diyaar garayn. e.g. They have made all the arrangements for the meeting. 2. meel ku safid, ku sharraxid.
array: /arrey/arrays, arraying, arrayed; (n) 1. wax tiro badan oo il gabato leh. 2. wax meel lugu sharraxay ama lugu waray si ay dadka u soo jiitaan. e.g. She looked in the window at the array of jewellery.
arrears: /arriiris/ (n) dayn lugugu leeyahay ama baaqi kugu ah oo aadan iska wada bixin. e.g. His account is in arrears.
arrest: /arrest/arrests, arresting, arrested; (v) 1. xirid ama xabsi dhigid. e.g. She had been arrested for possession of drugs. (n) 2. gof ama wax la gqabto ama la joojiyo.
arrival: /arraayval/arrivals/ (n) 1. imaansho ama soo caga dhigasho. e.g. His arrival will be delayed. 2. wax cusub oo hadda dhashey, ilmo oo kale. e.g. Many people lost their jobs with the arrival of the computer.
arrive: /araayv/atrives, arriving, arrived; (v) 1. in aad timaadid, soo caga dhigatid. e.g. She arrived here after midnight. 2. gaarid sida meel, fikrad, go'aan. e.g. It will take two days to arrive at a conclusion.
arrogant: /arragant/arrogantly, arrogance; (adj) cawaandi, qofarrow dadka khilaafa ama si qallafsan ula hadla oo isla weyni ka buuxdo. macangag. e.g. She was arrogant and selfish.
arrow: /aarow/arrows; (n) 1. leeb ama falaadh 2. xarriiq falaadh u eg oo wax lugu tilmaamo ama lugu calaamadiyo. e.g. The one-way sign is marked with an arrow.
arsenic: /arsanik/ (n) sun aad u daran oo dadka disha.
arson: /arsan/ (n) dambiga ah in aad dhismo ama meel kale aad kas u gubtid. e.g. He committed arson.
art: /aart/arts; (n) 1. farshaxan, sawir samayn, wax qurxin; naqshad samayn, (midabayn, rinjiyeyn). e.g. Sarah has a great knowledge of art. 2. waxyaabaha aan cilmiga ahayn sida luqadaha, suugaanta, taariikhda iwm. e.g. He earned a Bachelor of Arts degree. 3. wax ama hawl u baahan khibrad iyo xirfad sare. e.g. I am going to practice the art of writing.
artefact: /artifakt/artifacts, artifacts; (n) waxyaabaha gacanta lugu sameeyo sida sharraxaada ama qalabka farsamada. e.g. a silver artefact.
artery: /artari/arteries; (n) halbowlayaasha dhiiga 2. waddo ama dariiq weyn oo gaadiidku maro.
artful: /aartful/artfully; (adj) 1. qof xeelad ama khiyaamo badan. e.g. the artful tactics of politicians 2. qof xirfad sare u leh ama ku fiican wax gaar ah. e.g. She is the most artful writer in the country.
arthritic: /arthritik/arthritics; (adj) xanuunsan ama bararsan, xubnaha jirka qaar ama kulli. e.g. Her arms ached with arthritic pain.
arthritis: /arthraytis/ (n) xanuunka iyo bararka kala goysyada jirka, sida xaglaha, xusulada, jalaqlayda.
article: /artikal/articles; (n) 1. maqaal, qoraal meel ku qoran. e.g. I have read an article about Somalia. 2. shay ama alaab. e.g. I am selling different articles at low prices. 3. qodob ka mid ah heshiis ama sharci. e.g. an article of the Constitution. 4. shaqal naxwe ahaan, sida “a, an, the”.
articulate: /artikyaleyt/articulates, articulating, articulated; (adj) 1. qof hadal qeexan, hadalkiisu cad yahay. (adj) 2. fikradaada ama dareenkaaga oo aad si qeexan ama cad aad u sheegtid (u gudbisid) (adj) 3. isku-xirid sida baabuur iyo rimoor.
articulation: /artikyaleyshan/ (n) qeexitaan ama gudbin fikradeed ama si aad wax u dareentay (wax u garatay).
artificial: /artafishal/ (adj) 1. aan dabiici ahayn; aan dhab ahayn; wax qof sameeyey ~ dad-samee. e.g. When you read at night, you read by artificial light. 2. iska yeel-yeel wax aan qof u dhalan ama aan dabiici ka ahayn. e.g. She seems happy, but her smile looks artificial.
artillery: /artillari/ (n) 1. madaafiic, hub culus. e.g. They used heavy artillery against their enemy. 2: gaashaandhigga qaybta madaafiicda.
artist: /aartist/artists, artistic; (n) 1. qofka wax sawira ama naqshadeeya. e.g. He is a very talented artist. 2. qofka ku fiican xirfad gaar ah sida fanka ama farshaxanka. e.g. She has been an artist for ten years.
artiste: /artiist/artistes; (n) fannaan; gof heesa, majaajilleeya ama qoob ka ciyaara.
arty: /aarti/artier, artiest, artily, artiness; (adj) qofka xirfad u leh farshaxanka, fanka iwm.
as: /as/ (conj) 1. isla markaasba, markii. e.g. She sang as she worked. (adv) 2. tusaale ahaan. e.g. Some animals, such as dogs and cats, eat meat. (adv) 3. si is le'eg ama si isku mid ah. e.g. She is as tall as her mother. (adv) 4. sidoo kale ama isla sidaas. e.g. Can you run as I do? (conj) 5. sidaas darteed, sababtoo ah. e.g. As he was a good student, he received a reward. (conj) 6. inkastoo. e.g. Tall as Ali is, he is shorter than his brother.
asbestos: /aasbestas/ (n) macdan ama walax aan guban ama aan dabku karin.
ascend: /asend/ascends, ascending, ascended; (v) fuulid ama kor u kicid.
ascendancy: /asendansi/ (n) amar kutaaglayn, xukumid ama ka awood badin. e.g. Whites have ascendancy over the blacks in South Africa.
ascendant: /asendant/ (n) 1. qof ama dad xukunkooda ama awoodooda maamul kor u kacday. e.g. The former president is now in the ascendant. 2. ku amar taaglayn.
ascent: /asent/ascents; (n) 1. fuulitaan, koritaan. e.g. The second ascent took me longer than I expected. 2. dallacaad ama kor u socosho.
ascertain: /asarteyn/ascertains, ascertaining, ascertained; (v) xaqiijin ama hubin. e.g. It is necessary to ascertain if he is still alive.
ascetic: /asetik/ (adj) qofka u nool si xirxiran ama naftiisa xakameeya (ilaaliya) diin awgeed.
ascribe: /askrayb/ (v) sabab u ah ama loo aanaynayo, (wax sabab u ah in wax kale dhaco).
ash: /aash/ (n) dambas, bambas (budada cad ama beeyga ah oo dabka ka harta) xaabo ama sigaar basay ka harta. e.g. cigarette ash.
ashamed: /asheymid/ (adj) ka sheexid ama ka xishood. e.g. She is ashamed to apply for welfare.
ashore: /ashoor/ (adj) xeebta; wax badda ka soo baxay oo xeebta yimid. e.g. The ship came ashore yesterday.
ashtray: /aashtrey/ (n) haash-tariig ama weel yar oo sigaarka lugu damiyo. e.g. Do you have an ashtray?
Asian: /eyshan/asians; (adj) qof ama wax qaaradda aasiya ka yimid ama laga leeyahay. e.g. She is Asian, and her husband is Irish.
aside: /asaydh/ (adv) 1. gees isaga wareejin ama gees iska dhigid. e.g. She threw the books aside. 2. in qof aad wadada u banaysid ama gees uga bayrtid (dhan u wareegid). e.g. Can you move the table aside? 3. hadal gees ula bixid ama la faqid. e.g. She took me aside and told me about her fiance. 4. waxaas ama hadalkaas gees iska dhigoo ama iskaba daayoo. e.g. All jokes aside, he really is a nice person.
ask: /aask/asks, asking, asked; (v) 1. waydiin ama su'aalid. e.g. He asked me too many questions. 2. waydiisasho ama codsasho. e.g. She asked him to wait for ten minutes. 3. casuumid ama meel uga yeerid. e.g. He asked all of us to the party.
askew: /askiyuu/ (adj) wax ama dhar jactadan isku laablaaban, jajaban ama gees u janjeera. e.g. His shirt was askew.
asleep: /asliip/ (adj) hurda, seexday ama hurdo la dhacay. e.g. He fell asleep.
aspect: /aaspekt/aspects; (n) 1. muuqaal ama qaab qof ama shay leeyahay. e.g. aspect of the countryside. 2. il ama meel arin laga eego (aragti). e.g. We need to study various aspects of the plan. 3. meel ama jihada dhismo ama daaqadi u sii jeedo (ku jeedo). e.g. He lives in a house with a southern aspect.
aspersion: /aaspareyshan/aspersions; (n) dhaleecayn, caayid ama cambaarayn. e.g. She cast aspersions on their integrity.
asphyxiate: /aasfiksiyeyt/asphyxiates, asphyxiating, asphyxiated; (v) qof hawadu ama naqasku ku xirmay (ogsojiin waayey) ama jiiday hawo sumaysan oo u dhinta.
aspirant: /aaspaarant/aspirants; (n) qof damacsan ama raba inuu gaaro himilo gaar ah. e.g. an aspirant to the ministry.
aspiration: /aaspareyshan/aspirations; (n) wax aad rabtid inaad gaartid ama meel aad higsanaysid (damac ama gool).
aspire: /aspaayar/aspires, aspiring, aspired; (v) gool qgof doonayo inuu gaaro, damac ama hammad u hayn. e.g. He aspires to become a lawyer.
aspirin: /aaspirin/aspirins; (n) aasbiriin (kiniini madaxa u roon). e.g. My doctor gave me an aspirin for my headache.
ass: /aas/asses; (n) 1. dameer 2. qofka edebta xun ama axmagqa ah. (infl) 3. futada.
assail: /asseeyl/assails, assailing, assailed; (v) 1. cay aad u daran ama cambaarayn, 2. weerarid si rabsha leh, 3. musiibo (dhibaato badan oo hal mar ku haleesha).
assailant: /asseylant/assailants; (n) qofka shirqool ku dila qof kale (gacan ku dhiigle).
assassinate: /assaasaneyt/assassinates, assassinating, assassinated; (v) dilid ama shirqoolid gof muhiim ah (madax ah).
assassination: /assaasaneyshan/ (n) shirqool u dhigid, khiddad ku dilid. e.g. an assassination carried out by a hired killer.
assault: /assoolt/assaults, assaulting, assaulted; (n) 1. weerar kadis ah oo xoog leh. e.g. Our army responded with an assault against the enemy's position. (v) 2. gardaro ku weerarid, af ama addin ~ ku xadgudbid. e.g. He was accused of assaulting his brother. 3. fara-xumayn..e.g. The man was found guilty of making an assault on his stepdaughter.
assemble: /assembal/assembles, assembling, assembled; (v) 1. isku ururid ama isu tagid. e.g. The Arab leaders assembled in Cairo for an emergency meeting. 2. isku xirxirid ama isku rakibid. e.g. This automobile was assembled locally.
assembly: /assembali/assemblies; (n) 1. kulan weyn ama isku ururid. e.g. The Assembly of African-American People in Canada. 2. gole ama guddi loo xilsaaray hawl gaar ah sida sharci dejinta. e.g. The United Nations General Assembly. 3. isku xirxirid ama isku duwid. e.g. the assembly of the parts of an automobile.
assembly line: / assembly lines; (n) nidaamka warshadaha ee qof walba iyo mashiin walba shaqada qaar qabto (qofba gof u dhiibo ama mashiinba mashiin). e.g. She spends eight hours a day on an assembly line.
assent: /assent/assents, assenting, assented; (v) ku raacid ama u ogolaansho sharci, fikrad iwm. e.g. — The general manager did not give his assent of the proposal.
assert: /assert/asserts, asserting, asserted; (v) 1. caddayn ama carabka ku adkayn (si cad u sheegid) 2. qof awooddiisa dadka tusa ama soo bandhiga awooddiisa (isticmaala) 3. ku adkaysasho, ama caddaysasho fikrad, xuquuq iwm. e.g. She asserted that she was innocent.
assertion: /assershan/assertions; (n) 1. caddayn, xaqiiq (si cad u qeexid) 2. awood ama xukun adeegsasho (isticmaalid).
assertive: /assertiv/assertively; (adj) 1. qof ku adag fikradiisa (ma hare) ma quuste. e.g. Ali is an assertive boy, with an opinion on everything. 2. hadal cad (qeexan). e.g. an assertive sentence.
assess: /asses/assesses, assessing, assessed; (v) qumeyn. e.g. I asked her to assess the market value of my house. They met to assess the idea of establishing a community centre.
assessment: /assesmant/assessments; (n) qiimeyn gof, shay (wax) ama xaalad. e.g. We need to have a clear assessment of the situation.
asset: /aasset/assets; (n) 1. raasumaal; wax qiima leh oo aad leedahay. e.g. I have no personal assets. 2. qof ama wax qiimo iyo qaayo ku fadhiya. e.g. Two years experience is an asset for this job.
assiduous: /assiijuwas/ (adj) shago u hagar bixid ama u go'doomid (hawl karnimo). e.g. an assiduous worker.
assign: /assaayn/assigns, assigning, assigned; (v) 1. qof hawl gaar ah lugu qaybiyo (loo diro). e.g. She had been assigned to clean the house. 2. loo qoondeeyo ama loo xilsaaro. e.g. I was assigned a comfortable office to work in.
assignation: /assignayshan/assignations; (n) kulan garsoodi ah, sida gabar iyo wiil is jecel.
assignment: /assaaynment/ (n) 1. shaqo lugugu qaybiyo ama luguu xilsaaro in aad fuliso (qabato). e.g. My first assignment was to assess the company's tangible assets. 2. shaqa guri. e.g. Our teacher gave us a math assignment.
assimilate: /assimaleyt/assimilates, assimilating, assimilated; (v) 1. wax ama fikrad aad si fiican u fahantid ama u dhuuxdid. e.g. Sarah reads many books to assimilate more knowledge. 2. la qabsasho, dhexgelid ama ku milmid dad cusub oo kale sida qaxootiga markay la qabsadaan waddankay tagaan. e.g. Canada has assimilated a lot of people from all over the world.
assist: /assist/assists, assisting, assisted; (v) caawin ama gargaarid (gacan siin). e.g. He assists his son with payment of tuition fee.
assistance: /assistans/(n) caawimaad ama gargaar. e.g. She thanked me for my assistance.
assistant: /assistant/assistants; (adj) kaaliye ama caawiye. e.g. He is an assistant manager.
associate: /assooshiyeyt/associates, associated, associating; (v) 1. isku xirid ama isu keenid laba qof ama laba shay. e.g. Christians associate giving presents with Christmas. 2. isku xirnaan ama isku koox (isu urur) noqosho. e.g. He is associated with a law firm. 3. rafiiq la noqosho (saaxiib ka dhigasho). e.g. Do not associate with bad boys. (adj) 4. xubin aan xuquuq buuxda lahayn. e.g. He is an associate member.
association: /assoosiyeyshan/associations; (n) 1. urur hal ujeeddo wada leh 2. xiriir, isku xirnaan, ku lug lahaan. e.g. He has ended his association with that company.
assorted: /assoortidh/assortment;(adj) kala nooc-nooc ah; kala du-duwan. e.g. a bag of assorted candies.
assume: /assiyuum/assumes, assuming, assumed; (v) 1. u qaadasho ama u fakarid (u malayn). e.g. He assumed that the bus would be on time. 2. mas'uuliyad qaadid (xukun qaadid). e.g. He assumed power in 1960.
assumption: /asampshan/ (n) 1. malayn; si u qaadasho. e.g. He made a false assumption. 2. xukun la wareegid.
assurance: /ashuuransi/ (n) 1. ballanqaad. e.g. He gave his assurance that the problem would be corrected. 2. kalsooni. e.g. She spoke with assurance. 3. caymis.
assure: /ashuur/assures, assuring, assured; (v) 1. ballanqaadid ama hubanti bixin. e.g. This car is in good condition, I can assure you.
assuredly: /ashuuridhli/ (adv) hubaashii ama xaqiiq ahaan. e.g. He would assuredly be back in two weeks.
astonish: /astonish/astonishes, astonished, astonishing; (v) aad u yaabid (amakaagid), yaab leh. e.g. She is astonished that I can do this job.
astonishment: /astonishmant/ (n) yaab, amakaag. e.g. He looked at him with astonishment.
astound: /astawndh/astounds, astounding astounded; (v) la yaabid ama u qaadan waa (wax aad la yaabtid lama filaana kugu noqday). e.g. We were astounded that such a thing could happen.
astray: /astrey/ (adv) marin habaabsan, waddada saxda ah ka weecsan. e.g. He is my best friend; he won't lead me astray.
astride: /astraydh/ (prep) lugaha ka kala ridasho ama kala fogayn sida fardo fuulka. e.g. I like to ride my horse astride.
astringent: /astirinjant/ (n) 1. dhiig-joojiye ama wax jirka qalajiya. (adj) 2. wax ama qof aad dhaleecaysid (cambaaraysid). e.g. He directed his most astringent attacks at me.
astrologer: /astrolajar/astrologers; (n) faaliye ama qof wax-sheega. e.g. I will never go to astrologers again; they are liars.
astrology: /astrolaji/astrological; (n) cilmi falaga (xiddigaha oo laga faaliyo). e.g. Some people still believe in astrology.
astronaut: /astranoot/astronauts; (n) cir bixiyeen ama qof u tababaran dayax gacmeed wadid ama raacid.
astronomer: /astroonamar/astronomers; (n) gofka ku takhasusa cilmiga xiddigiska iyo meerayaasha sare.
astronomical: /astranamikal/ (adj) 1. wax xaddi badan ama sicir cirka ku shareeran (badan). e.g. an astronomical price 2. wax ku lug leh cilmiga xiddigiska.
astronomy: /astraanami/ (n) cilmiga xiddigiska ama meerayaasha sare. e.g. He studied astronomy.
astute: /astiyuut/astutely; (v) qof maskax badan (qof ku wanaagsan ~ fahmidda dabeecadaha iyo xaaladaha adag, ama xariif ku ah). e.g. He is an astute politician.
asylum: /asaaylam/asylums; (n) 1. magan-galyo siyaasadeed (magan-galyo siin). e.g. There are more refugees in the world seeking political asylum. 2. meesha dadka © waalan lugu xannaaneeyo. (maanakoobiyo).
asymmetrical: /asimmatrikal/ (adj) wax ama shay laba qaybood ama laba dhinac oo kala duwan (kala gadisan) leh.
ate: /eyt/ (v) waa cunay (eat oo fal tagay ah). e.g. I ate my lunch already.
atheist: /eythiyist/atheists; (n) diin laawe ama mulxid (ilaah inkirsan). e.g. Do not quarrel about religion with an atheist.
athlete: /athlit/athletes; (n) ciyaar yahan ka qayb qaata tartamada ciyaaraha fudud sida orodada, boodada iwm. e.g. Abdi Bile is a great athlete.
athletic: /athletik/athletics; (adj) 1. ciyaaraha fudud oo ay ka mid yihiin orodka, boodada, qaalma-rogadka iwm. e.g. An athletics competition will be held in Tokyo next year. 2. jir dhisan leh.
atlas: /aatlas/atlases; (n) buug maab ku sawiran yahay (buug joqoraafi meel leedahay lugu sawiro sida joqoraafiga magaalo ama waddan).
atmosphere: /aatmasfeer/atmospheres; (n) 1. hawada dhulka dushiisa ama hawada dhulka ku xeeran. 2. beey'ad ama jawi. e.g. We met in a quiet atmosphere.
atom: /aatam/ (n) 1. saxarka ugu yar ee maatarku ka samaysan yahay ee aan lasii qaybqaybin karin (proton + neutrons + electron) 2. wax aad u yar ama saxar le'eg (ciddi jabkeed). e.g. There's not one atom of truth in what he said.
atom bomb: / (n) atom bombs, atomic bomb; hub aad halis u ah oo laga sameeyo awoodda atamka.
atomic: /aatomik/ (adj) 1. wax ku shaqa leh quwadda atamka 2. la xiriira qaybaha atamku ka kooban yahay (mulukuyuulada atamka) ama atamka laftiisa. e.g. atomic weapons.
atone: /atoon/atones, atoning, atoned; (v) raalli gelin ama dib isu sixid. e.g. Ahmed atoned for his unkindness to Sarah by taking her to the restaurant.
atrocious: /atrooshas/atrociously; (adj) 1. aad u xun ama aad u tayo daran. 2. wax aad u xun oo laga walaaco ama naxdin leh. e.g. His manners are atrocious.
atrocity: /atrosati/atrocities; (n) fal aad u xun oo naxariis darro ah.
attach: /attaaj/attaches, attaching, attached; (v) 1. ku xirid ama ku dhejin; ku xidhnaan. e.g. He attached a note to my letter. 2. ka tirsanaan shirkad, hay'ad iwm. e.g. This Institute is attached to the University of California. 3. la wareegid si sharci ah. e.g. All his properties may be attached by the government. 4. xiriir qota-dheer la yeelasho, aad ula saaxiibid. e.g. He is deeply attached to her.
attache: /attaajee/attaches; (n) 1. ku-qaybsane-safaaradeed. (xubin ku qaybsan hawl gaar ah oo safaaradeed). e.g. He was a military attache at the Somali embassy in Paris.
attache case: / attache cases; (n) samsonayt, shandad yar ama boorso yar oo afar gees ah.
attachment: /attaajmant/ (n) 1. xiriir ama saaxiibtinimo weyn, isjeclaan ama is-addeecsanaan. 2. isku xidhid ama bir wax lugu xidho.
attack: /attaak/attacks, attacking, attacked; (v) 1. weerarid, weerar. e.g. She was attacked by an armed man. 2. dagaal afka ah oo kul-kulul ama qoraal ah. e.g. There was an article in the newspaper which attacks government policies.
attacker: /attaakar/attackers; (n) qofka ama cidda wax weerarta (weerar qaade). e.g. She could not remember what the attacker looked like.
attain: /atteyn/attains, attaining, attained; (v) wax aad heshid ama aad gaartid dadaal badan kadib. e.g. He worked hard to attain his ambitions.
attainable: /atteynabal/ attainment; (n) wax la gaari karo, la heli karo ama la samayn karo.
attempt: /attempt/attempts, attempting, attempted; (v) isku dayid ama tijaabin. e.g. He attempted to pass this exam two times.
attempted: /attempted/ (adj) dambi aad isku dayday oo kaa dhicisoobay. e.g. She was charged with attempted murder.
attend: /attendh/attends, attending, attended; (v) 1. ka qaybgalid (ka xaadirid). e.g. He attends a meeting every day. 2. iskuul galid, iskuul dhigasho. e.g. I attend City College of New York. 3. wax aad si taxadar leh u dhegaysatid ama u qabatid (digtooni leh). e.g. Everyone has to attend to his duty.
attendance: /attendhansi/attendances; (n) ka qayb gelitaan ama xaadirid, joogid. e.g. Attendance is a must at school.
attendant: /attendhant/attendants; (n) 1. qof shaqadiisu tahay inuu dadka (kalyantiga) u khidmeeyo (u shaqeeyo) sida shubaha baasiinka. e.g. He works as an attendant at the gas station. 2. wax kale ku lug leh ama la xiriira.
attention: /attenshan/attentions; (n) digtooni, feejignaan, wax aad si taxadar leh u dhagaysatid, u eegtid ama u samaysid. e.g. She was listening to her mother with close attention.
attentive: /attentiv/attentively; (adj) qof feejigan ama digtoon (maskaxdiisu soo jeeddo). e.g. He is a very attentive student.
attest: /attest/attests, attesting, attested; (v) la xaqiijiyo ama la caddeeyo (xaqiijin).
attic: /aattik/attics; (n) qol ama meel yar oo guriga saqafkiisa laga hoos dhiso oo marmar wax lugu xafido.
attire: /attaayar/attired; (n) dhar, labbis ama dhar xidhasho. e.g. She was dressed in formal attire.
attitude: /attatiyuud/attitudes; (n) 1. siyaabaha qof u dhaqmo ama wax u arko (u fakaro). e.g. I don't like her attitude. 2. qaabka ama sida jirka xubin ka mid ah laga dhigo eg. with his arms flung out in an attitude of surrender.
attract: /attraakt/attracts, attracting, attracted; (v) wax soo jiidasho leh, ku soo jiita ama ku xiiso geliya (sida bir-labta ku soo jiita). e.g. Her appearance did not attract me.
attractions: /attraakshan/attractions; (n) isa-soo jiidasho sida bir-lab oo kale; qof ama wax soo-jiidasho leh ama la caashiqi karo (jinni leh). e.g. Kenya has tourist attractions.
attractive: /attraakitiv/ (adj) wax ku soo-jiidanaya (aad jecleysanayso). e.g. She wore an attractive t-shirt. She is a very attractive young girl.
attribute: /attrabiyuut/attributes, attributing, attributed; (v) 1. sabab u ah ama loo aanaynayo (wax sabab u ah dhacdo ama xaalad). e.g. Some people attribute their success to luck. 2. u aqoonsasho (in qof ama wax, loo aqoonsado wax uu sameeyey, abuuray, helay iwm) 3. sifo (tilmaan). e.g. his physical attributes.
attuned: /atiyuundh/ (adj) 1. la qabsasho — ama u barasho 2. wax maqalkoodu kaa bato ama cod dhagahaagu qabatimaan.
auburn: /oobaran/ (adj) timo kafee ah 0O casaan xiga (guduud iyo kafee isku jira). e.g. I like her auburn hair.
auction: /ookshan/auctions, auctioning, auctioned; (v) 1. xaraashid; (n) 2.auction off xaraash. e.g. I bought my car at an auction.
auction off: / (phr) xaraashid ama sicir jaban ku gadid (ku khaarajin). e.g. All my books were auctioned off.
audacious: /oodheyshas/audaciously, audacity; (adj) 1. indha-adayg ama qof ku dhiirran wax khasaaro uga imaan karto; 2. af-adayg iyo edeb darro.
audible: /oodhabal/audibly; (adj) la maqli karo (cod ama shanqadh dheer ilaa heer la maqli karo). e.g. She spoke in an audible voice.
audience: /oodhiyansi/audiences; (n) dhagayste (sida qof wax daawanaya isla markaasna dhagaysanaya). e.g. The concert attracted a large audience.
audio: /oodhiyo/ (adj) 1. magal la xiriira 2. qalabka wax lugu dhegeysto, luguna duubo. e.g. An audio problem is a sound problem.
audio-typist: / audio-typists; (n) qofka garaaca war cajalad lugu duubay.
audit: /oodhit/audits, auditing, audited; (v) xisaab hubin. (ama xisaabi xil maleh samayn) ; jeegarayn in si sax ah wax loo xisaabay. e.g. I am expecting to be audited this year.
auditor: /oodhitar/ (n) hanti-dhowr ama xisaabiye dabagala ama hubiya in si sax ah wax loo xisaabay. e.g. Once a year an auditor comes to verify the business accounts.
auditorium: /oodhatooriyam/auditoriums (n) 1. meesha ay dhagaystayaashu fariistaan masraxa gudihiisa (fadhi) 2. tiyaatar ama dhismo weyn oo loogu talagalay shirarka ama riwaayadaha. e.g The National Theatre in Somalia had a beautiful auditorium.
auger: /oogar/ (v) galab looxaanta ama dhulka lugu duleeliyo.
augment: /oogment/augments, augmenting, augmented; (v) siyaadin, kordhin ama weeynayn. e.g. She had to augment her income by working seven days a week.
augur: /oogar/augurs, auguring, augured; (v) 1. calaamad ama wax kuu saraadiya wax xun ama wax fiican (jirro ama caafimaad). e.g. A long drought doesn't augur well for a good harvest. 2. qof wax-sheega (faaliya in qof guulaysanayo ama khasaarayo).
August: 1. /oogast/august; (n) bisha siddeedaad ee miilaadiga. e.g. I started this job in August.
august 2/oogast/(n) qof ama shay heer sare ah oo laga danbeeyo (la qadariyo).
aunt: /aant/aunts; (n) eeddo ama habar-yar. e.g. She is my aunt.
au pair: /ow peer/ au pairs; (n) ilmo ama qof dhalin yaro ah oo reer korsado, lugqadana ka barta una shaqeeya (badanaa ajnabi ah). e.g. An au pair from Montreal is living with my family here in Toronto.
aural: /ooral/ (adj) maqal ah (wax maqal ku lug leh). e.g. I must have an aural test done at the doctor's office.
auspice: /oospasis/auspices; (n) hoggaamin ama maamulid; badrooninimo. e.g. an emergency meeting was held under the auspices of the United Nations.
auspicious: /oosbishas/auspiciously; (adj) 1. arrin guul u dhow ama u eg in lugu guuleysanayo (guul saraadin) 2. barwaaqo.
austere: /oosteer/austerity; (adj) 1. wax cad oo aan sharraxaad lahayn sida derbi cad oo kale. e.g. Her room is sober and austere. 2. qof ad-adag ama si xirxiran u nool; nolol heer hoose ah oo aan raaxo lahayn. e.g. His father was a silent and austere man.
Australian: /oostreliyan/ (adj) qof Ustereeliya u dhashay ama shay lugu sameeyey. e.g. My teacher has lived in an Australian city.
authentic: /oothentik/authenticity; (adj) 1. shay ama qoraal asal ah (rasmi ah) (aan koobbi iyo sanifaad midna ahayn). e.g. We have to check if this is an authentic signature. 2. war ama arrin sax ah oo lugu kalsoonaan karo. e.g. authentic Somali culture.
authenticate: /oothentikeyt/ authenticates, authenticating, authenticated; (v) 1. wax la baaray oo la xaqiijiyey inuu run yahay (tasdiiqin). e.g. The news report has to be authenticated before it is released.
author: /oothar/authors; (n) qoraa (qofka wax qora). e.g. Abdullahi is the author of the novel, Ayaan-Daran.
authoritarian: /athoorateeriyan/authoritarians; (adj) kaligi-taliye ama kali-talin. e.g. Some South African governments remain authoritarian.
authoritative: /athoorateytiv/authoritatively; (adj) 1. awood xukun leh; awood maamul leh. 2. cilmi u leh (aqoon fiican u leh maaddo gaar ah). e.g. Authoritative orders came from the commander.
authority: /athoorati/authorities; (n) 1. awood ama xukun; dawlad ama qof dawlad ka socda. e.g. A lot of employees are under his authority. 2. aqoon fiican u yeelasho cilmi gaar ah. e.g. She is an authority on African history.
authorize: /ootharays/authorises, authorizing, authorized; (v) amar ku bixin (ogolaansho) yeelid. e.g. The President authorized him to visit to United States.
authorization: /ootharaseyshan/ (n) ogolaansho rasmi ah ama amar bixin (sida badan waxyaabaha qoran oo saxiixa lugu ogolaado). e.g. You can't have a loan without official authorization from the bank manager.
autobiographical: /ootabay-graafikal/ (adj) goraal la xiriira qoraha taariikh nololeedkiisa.
autobiography: /ootabayagrafi/autobiographies; (n) qof taariikh nololeedkiis uu asagu goro.
autocracy: /ootakrasi/ (n) kali-talin (in qof kaliya taliyo), kali xukumid.
autograph: /ootograaf/autographs, autographing, autographed; (n) qof caan ah saxiixiis. e.g. I have Mohamed Ali's autograph.
automate: /ootameyt/automates, automating, automated; (v) qalab ama wax iskii isu wada (ootomaatik) (aalad is wadda). e.g. Fewer employees are needed in a factory when it is automated.
automatic: /ootamatik/automatics, automatically; (adj) 1. mashiin is wadda ama qalab kale oo si otomaatik ah u shaqeeya. e.g. an automatic machine 2. fal qofka ka dhaca ama uu sameeyo asagoon ka fakarin ama uusan shago ku lahayn. e.g. She gave me an automatic response.
automation: /ootameyshan/automatons; (n) qalab gof oo kale ah (sidii gof u adeega). e.g The time is approaching when human workers may be replaced by automation.
automobile: /ootamobil/automobiles; (n) gaari (baabuur). e.g. Leaning to drive an automobile requires patience.
autonomous: /ootanamas/ autonomy; (adj) madax-bannaani ama qolo iskeed isu xukunta (sida shirkad is-xukunta).
autopsy: /ootapsi/autopsies; (n) baaris lagu ogaado gof sababta iyo siduu u dhintay.
autumn: /ootam/autumns. (n) xilliga ama fasalka dayrta. e.g. I will be going to London this autumn.
auxiliary: /oogsilyari/auxiliaries; (n) 1. caawiye (gargaare); taageero leh. e.g. a nursing auxiliary (adj) 2. siyaado ah ama markii loo baahdo la isticmaalo.
avail: /aveyl/avails, availing, availed; (v) 1. wax ku anfaca ama faa'iido kuu leh. 2. ka faa'tideysi. e.g. Money will not avail you after you are dead.
available: /aveeylabal/availability; (adj) wax ama qof la heli karo (diyaar ah). e.g. There is no money available at this moment.
avalanche: /aavalaanj/avalanches; (n) 1. barafka buuraha geesohooda ka soo daata (baraf badan oo buur hoosteed yaala). e.g. A group of skiers was buried under an avalanche. 2. wax tiro badan oo hal mar kulma (wax xaddi badan sida daadka). e.g. He fielded an avalanche of questions from the students.
avant-garde: /avantgardh/ (adj) aad u hormarsan (aad casri u ah). e.g an avant-garde sculpture.
avarice: /aavaris/ (n) hunguri weyni xaga lacagta, maalka (dhuuninimo ama damac badni).
avaricious: /avaarishas/ (adj) qofka hunguriga weyn ama damaca badan (dhuuniga ah) xaga maalka/lacagta.
avenge: /avenji/avenges, avenging, avenged; (v) ka-aar gudasho (ka aarsasho). e.g. He will do everything to avenge his father.
avenue: /avaniyuu/avenues; (n) 1. waddo weyn oo hareeraha dhir ku leh. e.g. She lives on a quite avenue. 2. hab ama dariiqo hawl loo fuliyo (dariiqad arrin loo maro si loo gaaro). e.g. We explored every avenue to find a solution.
average: /aavrij/averages, averaging, averaged; (n) 1. isku celcelin (isku celcelis). e.g. Your average mark for this semester is 85%. 2. caadi ama dhexdhexaad ah. e.g. An average person makes $300 per week.
averse: /aversi/ (adj) caaridid ama diidid wax aadan doonayn ama aadan jeclayn. e.g. He was averse to fighting.
aversion: /avershan/aversions; (n) necbaansho ama (nacayb xoog leh). e.g. He has an aversion to working on Fridays.
avert: /avert/averts, averting, averted; (v) 1. indho ka jeedin (ka sii jeensasho). e.g. He averted his eyes from the horrible scene. 2. joojin ama is hor-taagid wax aadan rabin inay dhacaan.
aviary: /eyviyeri/ (n) hoy ama meel shimbiraha lugu xannaaneeyo.
aviation: /eyviyeyshan/ (n) cilmiga duuliyanimada iyo diyaarado samaynta. e.g. He is an expert in American aviation.
avid: /eevidh/ (adj) aad u xtisayn (u soo jeedid); niyad fiican u hayn. e.g. Deeqa was an avid reader of love stories.
avoid: /avooydh/avoids, avoiding, avoided; (v) ka hor-tag ama ka fogaansho in wax dhacaan. e.g. I drive carefully to avoid accidents.
avoidable: /avooydhabal/ (adj) laga hortegi karo, laga fogaan karo (layska dhowri karo). e.g. The expenses were not avoidable.
avowal: /avowal/avowals; (n) si cad u qirasho (wax aad caddaysato).
avowed: /avawdh/ (adj) 1. wax qof rumaysan yahay ama ku ad-adag yahay. e.g. He is an avowed black rights activist. 2. wax aad caddaysid ama shaaca ka qaadid.
avuncular: /avaankiyalar/ (adj) qof aad u beer jilicsan (aad u dabeecad fiican una naxariis badan). e.g. I like his avuncular manner.
await: /aweyt/awaits, awaiting, awaited; (v) la sugo (sugid); wax ku sugaya mustaqbalka oo dhici doona. e.g. She has awaited your coming for two days.
awake: /aweyk/awakes, awaking, awoke, awaken; (v) 1. hurdada oo laga tooso (toosid). e.g. I awoke from a deep sleep. 2. soo jeedid (qof aan hurdin). e.g. He was awake all night.
awaken: /aweeykan/awakens, awakening, awakened; (v) 1. hurdo ka toosid. e.g. He was awakened by the fire alarm. 2. ku baraarug-sanaan.
award: /awoordh/awards, awarding, awarded; (n) 1. abaal-marin (abaalgud). e.g. The best student was given the highest award. 2. abaalmarid mudnaaneed (qof in wax loo xukumo in la siiyo). e.g. A scholarship is an award for academic excellence.
aware: /aweer/ (adj) 1. aqoonsanaan, yaqiinsanaan, (wax aad dareensantahay). e.g. |am fully aware of my responsibilities. 2. ogaan, ka war-hayn (wax aad ogtahay). e.g. I was not aware of this news.
away: /awey/ (adj) 1. ka fog (fog). e.g. Get away from the fire! 2. maqan. e.g. He is away on a holiday.
awe: /oo/awes, awed; (n) 1. layaab iyo cabsi. 2. wax ama qof kaa yaabiya ama aad u qaadan waydid.
awe-inspiring: / (adj) qof ama wax kaa yaabiya oo aad ku xushmaysid muhiimadiisa, ama cabsi aad ka qabto. (ka dambeyn cabsi ku jirto).
awesome: /oosam/ (adj) cajiib ah oo aan loo qaadan karin ama laga cabsado. e.g. Her achievements are awesome.
awful: /ooful/awfully; (adj) 1.wax aad u xun, aad u liita, fool-xun. e.g. What an awful smell! 2. aad u badan ama aad u wayn.
awhile: /awaayl/ (adv) wakhti yar ku siman. e.g. I will stay awhile in the restaurant.
awkward: /ookwardh/ (adj) 1. sirgaxan (gurracan). e.g. That cupboard is in a very awkward place. 2. dhib badan ama dhib keenaya. e.g. She is in a very awkward situation. 3. yax-yax ama xishood leh (aan habboonayn). e.g. The little girl asked me an awkward question.
awry: /araay/ (adj) wax booskii ama meeshii la rabay aan joogin (sidii loogu talagalay aan nogon). e.g. His hat was blown awry by the wind.
axe: /aks/axes, axing, axed; (n) 1. faas ama gudin (bir wax lugu gooyo). e.g. She chopped the tree with an axe. 2. gooyn, ama kala gooyn.
axiom: /aaksiyam/axioms; (adv) wax ama aragti run ah oo laysku raacay.
axiomatic: /aksiyamaatik/ (adj) hadal ama aragti laysku raacay (run ah oo aan muran ka taagnayn).
axis: /aaksis/ (n) 1. xarriiq dhexda marta (xuddun ah) 2. xarriiqaha joqoraafiga lugu muujiyo.
aye: /aay/ (adv) haah (haye) ; waa yahay (u woodid ama aqbalid). e.g. Aye aye captain.
azure: /aazar/ (adj) midab buluug ah oo barxan (aan tikh ahayn). e.g. The azure sky.
baa: /baa/baas, baaing, baaed;(v) cida idaha ama wixii sida idaha u ciya.
/bii ey/ (abbr) shahaado jaamacadeed oo lugu qaato adabka (arts) ama cilmiga bulshada. e.g. He took a B.A. in languages.
babble: /baabbal/babbles, babbling, babbled; (v) 1. cantar (hantaaticid); hadal ulajeedo cad aan lahayn oo isku dhex yaacsan farxad ama isku buuqsanaan darteed samayn. e.g. He babbled on about this wicked world. (n) 2. hadaaq (sida hadaaga caruurta). e.g. I like baby's babble. (adj) 3. codka biya-dhaca ama daadku sameeyo oo guuxa yar leh.
babe: /beyb/babes; (n) 1. cunug yar (ilmo yar) e.g. What a beautiful babe! (n) 2. magac loogu yeero qofka aad jeceshahay gaar ahaan, xaaskaaga, ninkaaga, iwm. e.g. Do you need any help, babe?
baboon: /baabuun/baboons; (n) nooc daanyeerka ka mid ah oo waji balaaran iyo ilko dhaadheer leh oo ku nool Afrika.
baby: /beybi/ (n) 1. ilmo caruur ah. e.g. My sister had a baby boy. (n) 2. qofka aad jeceshahay sida xaaskaaga. e.g. I like you very much, baby.
babyish: /beybish/ (adj) wax ciyaal-ciyaal ah (ama caruurta ku haboon)
baby-sit: /beybi-sit/baby-sits, baby-sitting, baby-sat; (v) ciyaal hayn inta waalidkood magan yihiin (caruur ilaalin). e.g. I can't find anyone to baby-sit my two kids.
baby-sitter: /beybi-sittar/baby-sitting; (n) caruur ilaaliso (caruur la joogto). e.g. Can you find a baby-sitter?
Bachelor of Arts: /baajalar of aarts/ (n) shahaadada jaamacadda ee adabka (arts) ama cilmiga bulshada.
Bachelor of Science: /baajalar of saynis/ (n) shahaadada jaamacadda gaybta cilmiga ah (B. Sc.).
back: /baak/backs, backing, backed; (n) 1. dhabar. e.g. He was lying on his back. (adv) 2. gadaal (xagga gadaale ama dib). e.g. Please sit at the back of the room. Can I call you back?
back away: /baak aweey/(v) dib-ugurasho (wax aad dib uga noqotid). e.g. He backed away without thinking.
back down: /baak dhawn/(v) is- dhiibid ama ka tanaasulid arin ama dacwad aad horey u samaysay. e.g. We can't convince them to back down.
back off: /baak off/ (v) dib uga nogosho (arin aad ka nogotid). e.g. They decided to back off from their demands.
back out: /baak awt/ (v) ka noqosho (arin aad dib uga nogoto).

dread: /dredh/ (n) 1. cabsi-weyn, baqdin (v) 2. ka baqid, ka cabsasho.
dreamy: /diriimi/ (adj) 1. riyo-ah (riyo oo kale ah) (adj) 2. qof riyo ku nool (dhalanteed ku nool).
dregs: /dregis/ (n) qasharka (qasharka dareeraha oo hoos fariista, ee layska- daadiyo).
dress: /dres/ (n) 1. lebbis, dhar (n) 2. kurdad, canbuur (v) 3. labbisasho, dhar xirasho.

drew: /druu/ (v) eeg draw, waa draw oo fal tagay ah.
dribble: /dribal/ (v) 1. tifqid, sida biyo tifqaya (v) 2. dhareerid (v) 3. bareejayn (bareejeynta kubbadda kolayga) (n) 4. tifiq, dhibic.
drift: /drift/ (n) 1. dhaqaaq ama xoog tamar kale ay wado, sida wax dabayli waddo (n) 2. dulucda (macnaha guud ee hadalka) (v) 3. soo-bitin ama soo-tuurid, sida wax dabayl ama mawjadi wado. e.g. Snow drifted across the road. (v) 4. iska-meeraysi (iska-war-wareegid).
drill: /drill/ (v) 1. qodid, daloolin (v) 2. carbin, tababarid (n) 3. dalooliye (qalab wax lugu dalooliyo ama lugu qodo) (n) 4. laylis; carbis.

drizzle: /drisal/ (n) 1. shuux (tiix) (v) 2. shuuxid (roob shuux ah oo da'a).
droop: /druup/ (v) 1. hicid, hoos-u liicid e.g. The flowers drooped and faded. (v) 2. liciifid.
drop: /drop/ (n) 1. dhibic (v) (n) 2. dhicid, soo-dhicis. e.g. Prices dropped. (v) 3. ku ridid, ku tuurid. e.g. Drop the letter in the mailbox. (v) 4. ka reebid, ka tagid. e.g. He has been dropped from the team for next Sunday's game. (v) 5. booqasho lama filaan ah. e.g. I thought I would just drop in and see how you were.
drop a line: /drop a layn/ (v) wargad u soo qorid. e.g. Drop me a line when you get there.
drop off: /drop of/ (v) 1. yaraansho, dhimid (v) 2. dajin, sida qof baabuur ka daga. e.g. Just drop me off at the corner.
drop out: /drop awt/ (v) 1. iskuul ka saaqidid (n) 2. qofka iskuul ka saaqida.
dropper: /droper/ (n) dhibco (goojo) cabire, tuubbo-yar oo dhalo ah oo lugu qiyaaso daawada joogo ahaanta loo qaato.
drove: /drowv/ (n) 1. raxan (xayawaan ama dad wada-jira) (v) eeg, drive.
drown: /drawn/ (v) garqid, hafasho (v) 2. cod lugu qariyo qaylo ka dheer. e.g. His voice was drowned by the roar of the machine.
drudge: /draj/ (v) 1. qabasho shago dhib badan oo liidata (n) 2. qofka shaqadaas qabta.
drugstore: /drag-istoor/ (n) farmashiye e.g. Go to the drugstore and get some cough syrup.
drunk: /drank/ (n) 1. sarkhaan (vy) 2. cabbay, drink oo fal tagay ah.
dry clean: /dray-kiliin/ (v) dharka oo kiimiko lugu mayro, biyaha baddalkoodii.
dub: /dhab/ (v) 1. ku naanaysid, magac ugu yeerid siiba cay ah (v) 2. cod u samayn, sida filin oo kale (v) 3. koobbi filin ka samayn.
duck out: / (v) u gooyn, ka dhuumasho masuuliyad iwm. e.g. Don't try to duck out of cleaning up the floor.
due: /dhiyuu/ (adj) 1. lugu leeyahay; ku waajibtay (adj) 2. munaasib, habboon (adj) 3. sababid, sabab u noqosho (adj) 4. la-filayo, la rajaynayo (n) 5. xuquuq.
due process: /diyuu-proses/ (n) nidaamka xuquuq dhawrista. e.g. She complained that she didn't get due process.
duke: /dhuuk/ (n) darajada gof laan-dheere ama shariif ah uu qaato. e.g. She married a duke.
dull: /dhal/ (adj) 1. damiin ah, fahmo-daran. e.g. His oldest child is very dull. (adj) 2. liita (xiiso-daran) (adj) 3. aan caddayn; aan dhalaalayn.
dully: /diyuli/ (adv) sidii la-rabey ama goortii la rabay.
dumbbell: /dhambel/ (n) 1. luudi ama bir labada gees culays is-le'eg ku leh, siiba kuwa jir-dhisidda. (n) 2. doqon.
dumbfound: /damfawndh/ (v) dhakafaarid, amakaagid, yaab la hadli waayid. e.g. He was dumbfounded by the news.
dummy: /dhami/ (n) 1. shay dhalanteed ah, sida wax sannifaad ah oo run loo ekeysiiyey. e.g. a dummy gun. (n) 2. jujeeto (mujuruca carruurta lugu aamusiyo) (n) 3. qof u eg, oo dharka lugu soo bandhigo. e.g. a dressmaker's dummy (n) 4. nacas, doqon.
dump: /dhamp/ (n) 1. qashin-qub, dukaafad (v) 2. qashin ku daadin (v) 3. ku daadin (ku qubid).
dumps: /dhampis/ (n) murugo e.g. You are down in the dumps today.
dungarees: /dhangariis/ (n) surweel badanaa jiinis ah oo wata maro ilaa xabadka qarisa oo leh suuman garbaha la gashado.
dunk: /dhank/ (v) 1. ku daarasho (ku dhuugid). e.g. to dunk biscuit in tea (v) 2. maquufid, biyo dhex-gelin suiba in-yar. e.g. He dunked his head in the water.
duplex: /duplekis/ (n) guri laba-dabakh ah, oo jaranjaro xiriiriso.
duplicate: /duplikeyt/ (n) 1. nuqul, koobbi (v) 2. nuqul ka samayn, labo isku-mid ah ka dhigid.
dust: /dhast/ (n) 1. boor, habaas (v) 2. boor ka jafid ama ka nadiifin.
duster: /dhastar/ (n) boor-tirtire (calal iwm, oo boorka lugu tirtiro).
dust-pan: /dhast-paan/ (n) weel qashinka lugu qaado, oo u eg badeelka afkiisa hore.
dwarf: /dworf/ (n) 1. cilin (v) 2. cilin u muuqasho, yaraansho (v) 3. ragaasid.
dynamics: /dhaynamikis/ (n) diinaamiko (cilmiga la xiriira tamarta iyo dhaqaaqa).
dynamite: /dhaynamayt/ (n) qaraxdo awood-badan, oo loo adeegsado qarxinta ceelasha macdanta.
dyslexia: /dhisleksiya/ (n) arag-la'aanta wax-akhriska, qofka akhriska aan karin, oo xarfuhu isaga darsamaan).
early: /eerli/ at the earliest; (adj) hore, goor hore ugu horayn (marka ugu horaysa).
earmark: /iyar-mark/ (v) u qoondayn (ugu talo- gelid). e.g. The money was earmarked for the hospitals.
earn: /eern/ (v) kasbasho dakhli ama wax kale. e.g. How much does she earn per hour in her new job?
earnest: /eernist/ (adj) daacad ah, daacadnimo. e.g. Is the minister in earnest about his desire to negotiate?
earphone: /iyarfoon/ (n) qaybta dhegaha la-saaro, ee qalabka wax lagu dhegeysto.
earshot: /iyar-shat/ (n) xudduuda maqalka ee dhegta (inta dhegtu wax ka maqli karto).
earthenware: /eerthen-weer/ (n) dhoobo ka samaysan. e.g. an earthenware cup.
earthly: /eerthli/ (adj) 1. dunida (adduunyada la xiriira) (adj) 2. suurto-gal ah. e.g. I have no earthly chance of winning.
earthy: /eerthi/ (adj) 1. dhaqan-xun: edeb-daran (adj) 2. dhulka ama ciidda la xiriira.
ease: /iis/ (n) 1. sahal, dhib-yari (n) 2. raaxo; degenaan. (v) 3. roonaanayn khafiifin, dejin. e.g. She gave me some medicine to ease the pain.
easel: /iisel/ (n) fareem alwaax ah oo lugu qabto sabuuradda ama looxad wax lugu sawirayo.
easily: /iisili/ (adj) 1. sahal ah, dhib-yari (adj) 2. shaki-la'aan. e.g. This is easily the best dictionary.
Easter: /iister/ (n) ciidda kiristaanka ee lugu xuso dhimashadii nebi-ciise iyo soo-laabashadiisa.
easy-going: /iisi-goying/ (adj) degan (qof degan oo qun-yar socod ah). e.g. an easy-going young lady.
eater: /iiter/ (n) cunaa. e.g. She is a big eater.
eaves: /iivis/ (n) qararka saqafka ee derbiga ka-soo baxsan.
eavesdrop: /iivis-drop/ (v) dheg-nuugsi (xan-dhegaysi). e.g. He eavesdropped on his parent's discussion.
ebb: /eb/ (v) 1. caaryid (caaryidda biyaha badda). (v) 2. xumaansho, yaraansho. e.g. Her strength was ebbing very fast.
ebony: /eeboni/ (n) 1. nooc alwaax ah, oo madoow. (n) 2. qundi ah (madow).
ebullient: /ibalyant/ (adj) furfurnaan, faraxsanaan. e.g. She is an ebullient mood.
echo: /eekow/ (n) 1. jabaq-celis (cod-noqodka dhismo, buur iwm, oo ay qofka dib ugu soo ceshaan) dayaan. (v) 2. ka daba-dhihid. e.g. She always echoes her husband's ideas.
eclair: /eykler/ (n) keeg dhuuban oo kareem dhexda uga jiro.
eclipse: /iklipis/ (n) 1. qorrax madoobaad ama dayax madoobaad. e.g. the Sun in eclipse (n) 2. hoos-udhac, sida quwad-jabka iwm (v) 3. ka fiicnaansho, oo wax-qabadka qofka kale uu muugan waayo. e.g. He is eclipsed by his brother, who is very famous.
ecology: /ikoloji/ ecological; (n) cilmiga xiriirka noolaha iyo beey'ada (deegaanka).
economic: /ikonomik/ (adj) 1. dhaqaale (dhaqaale la xiriira) (adj) 2. faa'iido leh (dhaqaale ku jiro).

edgewise: /edjiways/ edgeways; (adv) 1. darafka (dhanka geeska ah) (phr) 2. get a word in edgewise (fursad hadal u helid iyadoo qof kale hadlayo). e.g. I could not get a word in edgewise.
edgy: /edji/ (adj) xanaaq-badan (neerfooso ah). e.g. She is in an edgy mood.
edify: /edhafay/ (n) sare u qaadid garaadka ama dhaqganka qofka.
edit: /edhit/ (v) 1. soo-diyaarin iyo isku-dubbaridid buug, joornaal, filin iwm. 2. sixitaan qoraal lugu sameeyo
edition: /idhishan/ (n) daabacaad. e.g. The first edition of this dictionary.
editor: /edhitor/ (n) diyaariyaha iyo isku-dubaridaha joornaal, buug, filin, iwm.
editorial: /edhitooriyal/ (adj) 1. ra'yiga jaraa'idka (qaybta jaraa'idka ee lugu qoro fikradda jariiradu arin ka qabto) (adj) 2. diyaariyaha iyo isku-dubaridaha jariidad iwm.

effect: /ifekt/ (n) 1. natiijo. e.g. A high unemployment rate is one effect of the recession. (n) 2. saamayn (v) 3. dhalin, sababid keenid.
effective: /ifektiv/ (adj) 1. saamaynaya, sidii la rabay wax-utaraya (adj) 2. xaqiiqi ah (ficil ahaan u jira). 3. dhaqan galaya. e.g. The new rules become effective next year
effects: /ifektis/ (n) hanti (siiba hantida gaarka ah ee gof leeyahay).
effeminate: /ifemanat/ (adj) nimow-naag (nin sifooyin naagood leh). e.g. He walks in an effeminate way.
effigy: /efiji/ (n) suurad gof-leeyahay oo gacanta lugu sameeyo. e.g. an effigy of Saddam.
effluent: /efluwent/ (n) bullaacad warshadeed (bullaacadda warshadda ka soo baxda).
effort: /efort/ (n) dadaal. e.g. Little effort has been made to finish this job.
effortless: /efortles/ (adj) sahal, dhib-yari loo qaban karo. e.g. a dancer's effortless motions.
effrontery: /efranteri/ (n) indha-adayg, xishood-darro. e.g. She has the effrontery to use my computer without asking.
effusive: /ifiyusiv/ (adj) af-macaani been ah. e.g. effusive congratulations.
/ii-jii/ (abbr) tusaale (exempli-gratia, oo la soo gaabiyey oo ah laatiin).
ego: /iigow/ (n) gab (han, sida gofku isu-qabo inuu yahay).
egotism: /iigowtism/ (n) anaaninimo, siiba gofka markasta naftiisa kaliya u hadla.
either: /iithar/ (pron) 1. midkood. e.g. He may take either of these books. (adv) 2. sidoo-kale. e.g. He can't read, and I can't either.
ejaculate: /ijaakyuleyt/ (v) 1. biyo-bixid (shahwo bixid) (v) 2. qaylin, siiba qaylada gof galmoonaya.
elaborate: /ilaaboreyt/ (v) sharraxid. e.g. Please elaborate on that last point.
elapse: /ilaaps/ (v) waqti la dhaafo (la gudbo). e.g. A year had elapsed since we met.

elect: /ilekt/ (v) 1. doorasho (la doorto). e.g. The peaple elect their President. (adj) 2. la-doortay. e.g. President elect.
electric: /ilektarik/ (adj) 1. koronto ku shaqeeya, koronto ah. (adj) 2. xiiso badan.
electrical: /ilekterikal/ (adj) koronto la- xiriira. e.g. Abdi is an electrical engineer.

electron: /il-lektran/ (n) elektaroon (saddexda qurub ee atamka midkood ee aan la sii burburin karin)
electronic: /ilektaronik/ (adj) elektaroonig ah (danab ku shaqeeya). e.g. an electronic calculator.
element: /element/ (n) 1. curiye, cunsur (n) 2. in-yar (qurub-yar) (n) 3. aasaaska (asalka) (n) 4. cimilada (jawiga) (n) 5. kul- dhaliye (qaybta korontada ee kulka dhalisa ee ku jirta foornooyinka iwm).
elicit: /elisit/ (v) ka ogaansho, sida akhbaar qof laga soo-saaro. e.g. In ten minutes he elicited all the information from her.
eligible: /elejebal/ (adj) 1. xaq u-leh (adj) 2. munaasib, habboon, la dooran karo.

elusive: /iluusiv/ (adj) 1. baxsan-og, baxsanaya (adj) 2. dhib-badan, oo aan la helin ama la-fahmi karin. e.g. elusive mathematical problems.

embalm: /imbaam/ (v) dhayidda meydka si uusan u qurmin.
embark: /imbark/ (v) 1. markab fuulid, markab ku shiraacasho (v) 2. bilaabid.
embarrassment: /imbaarasment/ (n) waji-gabax, yax-yax (wax laga xishoodo, ceebaal). e.g. She could not hide her embarrassment.
embitter: /imbiter/ (v) calool-xumayn, ciilid. e.g. She was embittered by poverty and loneliness.
emblazon: /imbleyson/ (v) ku naqshadayn ama ku-daabicid, siiba astaan meel lugu daabaco. e.g. t-shirts emblazoned with the name of a school.
embody: /embadhi/ (v) 1. koobid, siiba fikrad hal-meel lugu sookoobo. e.g. Her opinions are embodied in this letter. (v) 2. ka-koobmid, ka kooban.
embrace: /imbareys/ (v) (n) hab-siin, hab. e.g. The two brothers embraced. (v) 2. ka-koobmid, ka kooban (v) 3. rumayn, sida diin kale rumaynteed. e.g. She embraced the Muslim religion.
embryo: /embiriyo/ (n) uur-jiif (ilmaha aan dhalan ee weli uurka ku-jira).
emerald: /emerald/ (n) 1. dhagax cagaar dhalaalaya ah oo qaali ah (n) 2. midabka cagaar-dhalaalaya ah.
emetic: /imetik/ (n) matajiye (sida daawo qofka ka matajisa). e.g. an emetic medicine.
emigrate: /emigreyt/ (v) haajirid, qixid. e.g. He emigrated from Somalia.
eminent: /emanant/ (adj) caan ah (magac-dheer). e.g. an eminent scholar.
emissary: /emaseri/ (n) ergey (qof farriin ama hawl-gaar ah loo diro).
emit: /imit/ (v) stideyn, bixis, sida qaac meel ka-baxa. e.g. A volcano emits lava.
emotive: /imowtiv/ (adj) qiiro abuuraya. e.g. an emotive speech.
emphasis: /emfasis/ (n) xoog-saaris, xoog, adayg. e.g. We sometimes underline words to show emphasis.
emphasize: /emfasays/ (v) xoog-saarid, carrabka ku adkayn. e.g. He emphasized the importance of money.
empire: /empayar/ (n) imbiraadooriyad (waddamo badan oo hal xukuumad hoos yimaada). e.g. the British Empire.
empirical: /impirakal/ (adj) waaqici ah (ku salaysan wax la-qabankaro, ama la dareemi karo). e.g. an empirical theory.
emulate: /emyuleyt/ (v) la-tartamid (in qof laysku dayo in la-gaaro ama laga-badiyo). e.g. She tried to emulate her sister's good manners.
enable: /ineybal/ (v) awood u-siin, karsiin, u-ogolaan. e.g. This dictionary enables you to understand the language.
enamored: /inaamoridh/ (ame) enamoured (bre); (v) caashaqid, jeclaansho. e.g. I was always enamored of the theatre.
encase: /inkeys/ (v) dahaarid, daboolid. e.g. My ID card was encased in plastic.
enchanting: /injaanting/ (adj) farxad leh, farxad-badan. e.g. an enchanting little boy.
enclave: /enkleyv/ (v) dhex-kujir, dhul uu ku wareegsan-yahan dhul kale.
enclose: /inklows/ (v) 1. ku-xirid, ku guda-ridid. e.g. I enclosed a check of $40. (v) 2. ku-meegaarid, ku-wareejin.
enclosure: / (n) 1. deyd, xero (n) 2. lifaaq, wax lugu dhex-riday wax kale ama lugu-lifaaqay.
encroach: /inkrowj/ (v) 1. xaq ka-qaadid (xuquuq ka-qaadid). e.g. This government decision should not encroach on the rights of the citizens. (v) 2. dhul-bursi (dhul aadan lahayn oo aad xaq-darro u qaadato).
encrusted: /inkrastidh/ (adj) dheehan, dahaaran. e.g. a jewel encrusted crown.
encyclopedia: /insayklopiidiya/ (n) buug ama buugag laamaha aqoontoo dhan ama qaarkood ku urursan yihiin ~ abwaan.
end up: /endh-ap/ (v) ku-dhammaansho (waxa qgof ama shay uu aakhirkiisa ku danbeeyo).
endanger: /indheynjar/ (v) khatar-gelin. e.g. He will endanger his life if he smokes.
endear: /indhiyar/ (v) jecleysiin, qiimo u-yeelid. e.g. She endeared herself to everyone.
endeavor: /indhevor/ (v) dadaalid, isku dayid. e.g. If you promise to be nice, I will endeavor to forgive you.
endemic: /endhemik/ (n) cudur meel shaac ku ah. e.g. Malaria is endemic in Somalia.
endorse: /indoorsi/ (v) 1. jeeg-wareejin (jeeg iwm oo gadaal laga saxiixo, si cid kale loogu sarrifo) (v) 2. ayidid ama ogolaansho.
endow: /indaw/ (v) 1. u-hibeyn (v) 2. lugu-manaystay (hibo-loo siiyey, siiba wax dabiici ah, sida quruxda, caqliga iwm). e.g. He was endowed with great intelligence.
endure: /indhyuur/ (v) 1. u-adkaysi (adkaysasho) (v) 2. jirid, waarid. e.g. an enduring peace.
enforce: /infoorsi/ (v) 1. dabbakhid, fulin, sida sharci iwm (v) 2. xoog ku fulin (ku khasbid).
enforceable: /infoorsabal/ (adj) fuli kara, hirgeli-kara. e.g. This act is not easily enforceable.
engage: /ingeyj/ (v) 1. shaqaalay-siin. e.g. He has engaged a new secretary. (v) 2. mashquulin. e.g. This film engaged his attention for hours. (v) 3. weerarid (v) 4. dhex-gelid ama ku-xirmid, stiba biraha.
engaged: /ingeyjidh/ (adj) 1. mashquul ah, mashquulsan (adj) 2. alkuman (guur ku hishiiyey).
engineer: /enjaniir/ (n) 1. injineer (v) 2. khiddad injineernimo ku samayn (v) 3. xeeladayn (khidadayn).
engrossed: /ingarowsidh/ (adj) mashquulsan. e.g. He was engrossed in his book.
engrossing: /ingarowsin/ (adj) soo jiidasho leh, lugu-mashquulayo. e.g. an engrossing dictionary.

fete: /feyt/ (n) 1. meherijaan (n) 2. kulan dad-weyne, oo lacag lugu uruuriyo (v) 3. xaflad ku-maamuusid, soo-dhawayn u samayn.
fetter: /fetar/ (n) 1. dabar, sida silsiladda maxbuuska lugaha looga xiro (v) 2. dabrid, lugaha ka-xirid, siiba silsiladayn.
feud: /fiyuudh/ (n) dirir, colaad, siiba mid laba qoys dhex-marta.
fever: /fiivar/ (n) xummad, qandho. e.g. He is in bed with a very high fever.
few: /fiyuu/ (adj) xoogaa, wax-yar. e.g. I have very few friends.
fez: /fes/ (n) tarbuush, casmali, koofiyad badanaa cas oo dhalada bul madoow ka laalaado, oo laga qaadan jiray turkiya.
fiancé: /fiyaansey/ (n) alkun, khadiib, inanka gabari u-doonan tahay. e.g. Siciid is my fiance.
fiancée: /fiyaansee/ (n) alkun, khadiibad, inanta doonan. e.g. She is my fiancee.
fiber: /faybar/fibre (n) 1. liil, dun-adag, mayrax ama wax qaabkaas leh. e.g. a fiber of wool (n) 2. dabeecad, dabci (n) 3. maaddo dhirta ama miraha laga helo oo dheef-shiidideedu jirka ku adag-yahay.
fickle: /fikal/ (adj) is-bedbeddel badan, sida qof go'aan kiisa ama maankiisu dhakhso isu rog-rogo
fiction: /fikshin/ (n) khayaali, dhalanteed, sida sheeko, filin iwm, oo khayaali ah. e.g. I could not decide whether the story was fact or fiction.
fictitious: /fiktishas/ (adj) khayaal, la-sameeyey, oo aan run ahayn
fiddle: /fidhel/ (n) 1. kaman (aalad muusig) (v) 2. kaman garaacid (v) 3. dheel-dheelid, wax ku-ciyaarid ulajeeddo la'aan (v) 4. been- samayn khayaano, sida lacag khiyaano lugu helo
fidelity: /fadelati/ (n) 1. aaminimo, daacadnimo e.g. Her fidelity to her husband was well-known.(n) 2. sax-ahaansho, khalad-la'aan fidget/fijit/ (v) kuur-kuursasho, kadaalin, dhaq-dhaqaaq iyo kaadsiinyo la'aan.
field: /fiildh/ (n) 1. beer, dhul-beereed (n) 2. garoon, goob (n) 3. majaal cilmi (takhasus cilmi, laan cilmi). e.g. He is in the field of electronics. (v) 4. qabasho, siiba banooniga oo la qabto. e.g. He fielded the ball.
field glasses: /fiildh-galasis/ (n) xoqad, diirad, qalab araga soo dhaweeya
fiend: /fiindh/ (n) 1. ibliis, sheyddaan (n) 2. qofka wax ka-hela, ama wax aad u-jecel. e.g. She is a health fiend.
fiendish: /fiindhish/ (adj) 1. sheydaanimo ah (adj) 2. dhib-badan, aan sahlanayn. e.g. a fiendish plan.
fierce: /fiirsi/ (adj) 1. horor-ah, sida bahal halis ah oo si-daran wax u hujuuma. e.g. a fierce dog.
fiery: /fayri/ (adj) 1. dab ah, naareed (adj) 2. xanaaq badan, kacsan. e.g. She had a fiery temper.
figurative: /figarativ/ (adj) af-maldah (eray ama oraah loo adeegsado si macnaheeda dhabta ah ka duwan, si sawir-maskaxeed ama shabbahaad loo muujiyo) sida: ninku waa libaax (figurative) ninku waa geesi (literary)
figure: /figar/ (n) 1. jirka qofka, jismiga (n) 2. lambar, tiro, god, summadda tirada sida 1, 2, 3. (n) 3. qaab, muuqaal (n) 4. jaantus, sawir jaan- tus ah (n) 5. qof caan-ah (v) 6. citiqaadid, rumaysasho (v) 7. ka qayb qaadasho
figure out: /figar-awt/ (v) soo-saarid, fahmid. e.g. I have to figure out how to do it.
figure eight: /figar-eyt/ (n) qaab-siddeedle, wax lambar siddeed u eg, sida taayga dhuunta lugu xirto
figurehead: /figar-heedh/ (n) 1. madax-weyne ama taliye magac u-yaal ah, oo aan awood lahayn, magac-ahaan (n) 2. jismi ama muuqaal sharraxaad ah, oo markab hortiisa laga dhiso, oo sanam u-eg
figure of speech: /figar of ispiij/ (n) af-maldah (macnaha duwan ee kalmad loo adeegsado si loo muujiyo muuqaal ama is-barbardhig). e.g. I didn't really mean that my father is a lion; it was just a figure of speech.
file: /fayl/ (n) 1. soofe, bir ama shay wax lugu soofeeyo (n) 2. gal (faylka warqadaha lugu rito) (n) 3. saf (kiyuu) (v) 4. galayn (fayl-garayn).
fillet: /filey/ fillet (n) 1. cad hilib ah, oo lafa baxsan. e.g. The fish fillet was cooked perfectly. (v) 2. lafa-bixin
fillings: /faylins/ (n) xanafta ka daadata wax la soofaynayo.
fill out: /fiil awt/ (v) 1. buuxin. e.g. Fill out this form. (v) 2. cayilid.
fill up: /fiil ap/ (v) buuxin, cammirid. e.g. Please fill up the gas tank.
film: /film/ (n) 1. filin (n) 2. filinka wax lagu sawiro. (n) 3. xuub ama wax xaleef ah. e.g. a sheet of flexible film (v) 4. filin qaadid, filin-duubid.
finalist: /faynalist/ (n) geba-gebadii ama kama-dambaystii jooga, sida koox is-reeb-reebkii ugu dambeeyey joogta.
finally: /faynali/ (adv) ugu-dambayntii, aakhirkii. e.g. She finally came to the party.
finding: /faydhin/ (n) 1. qaraar maxkamadeed (n) 2. xaqiiqo ama yiqiin laga soo saaray baaris (natiijo)
fine: /fayn/ (n) (v) 1. ganaax, ganaaxid (n) 2. fiican (adj) 3. aad u-dhuuban. e.g. Do you have a pencil with a fine point?
fine arts: /fayn-artis/ (n) fanka quruxda (curinta wax qaab iyo qurux leh, sida farshaxanka, muusiga iwm)
finicky: /finiki/ (adj) ash-ash badan, qof aan waxba qancin.
finish with: /finish with/ (v) ka-dhammaysi, aan dib-dambe loo isticmaalayn.
fire: /faayar/ (n) 1. dab (n) 2. toogasho, rasaasayn (v) 3. gubid (v) 4. shaqo ka-cayrin, ruqsayn. e.g. Get out! You're fired!
fire escape: /faayar-iskeyp/ (n) jaranjar lugu baxsado kolkii dab dhaco, (meel gubato).
firefly: /fayr flay/ (n) gaaraabbidhaan (cayayaan yaryar oo duulduula oo habeenkii, isagoo u eg dhinbilo yaryar oo dab ah bidhaama) ~ gaaraabbidhood.
fire hydrant: /faayar-haydrant/ (n) tuubada biyaha dabka lagu damiyo laga isticmaalo, oo badanaa waddada geesteeda ku-taal.
fireplace: /faayar-palays/ (n) dab-shidka kullaalka ee derbiga guriga dhexdiisa ah ku-yaal, oo laga isticmaalo dhulalka qaboow.
first class: /ferest-kalas/ (adj) heerka-koowaad, heerka ugu fiican uguna qaalisan ee lugu-safro ama dhanbaal lugu-diro.
first-hand: /ferest-handh/ (adj) gacantii-koowaad ah, sida hadal meeshuu kasoo unkamay laga soo ogaaday. e.g. first-hand news.
first name: /ferest neym/ (n) magaca qofka (magaca-koowaad). e.g. Mr. Said's first name is Abdi-hakim.
fiscal: /fiskal/ (adj) la xiriira maaliyadda, sida canshuur-celinta iwm.
fish out: /fish-awt/ (v) soo-saarid, soo helid. e.g. to fish out a dollar coin.
fishing: /fishin/ (n) kalluunsi, kalluumaysi. e.g. He likes fishing.
fish-monger: / (n) kalluun-gade, qofka ama dukaanka gada kalluunka.
fishy: /fishi/ (adj) 1. kalluun shabbaha, siiba xaga dhadhanka ama urka (adj) 2. been u-eg, shaki ku-jiro
fist: /fist/ (n) calaacasha iyo faraha oo isku-laaban, tantoonyo, tantoomo
fit: /fit/ (adj) 1. le'eg, ku-habboon (adj) 2. caafimaad-qaba, ladan (n) 3. qallal, sarco (n) 4. le'ekaan, jin ku ahaansho. e.g. This shirt is a perfect fit.
fit in: /fit-in/ (v) ku-habboonaansho, waafiqid, la mid-noqosho (v) 2. gelin, ku-ciriiryid
fitting: /fitin/ (adj) 1. habboon, sax-ah (n) 2. jimays, cabbiris. e.g. She is having a fitting for her wedding dress tomorrow.
fix: /fiks/ (v) 1. ku-xirid, ku-dhuujin (v) 2. hagaajin, samayn (v) 3. diyaarin, nidaamin (n) 4. dhibaato, shiddo. e.g. He is in a terrible fix. (n) 5. irbad daroogo ah
fixed: /fiksidh/ (adj) 1. degsan, horay loo dajiyey ama loo nidaamiyey. e.g. fixed price (adj) 2. dhagan, adag, aan dhaq-dhaqaaqayn
fixture: /fiksijar/ (n) 1. alaab guriga ku-rakiban oo aan la dhaqaajin karin. (n) 2. ballan-ciyaareed, oo horay loo dejiyey.
fizz: /fis/fizzy (v) 1. xoorin ama cod xoorin ah samayn, sida kookada (n) 2. xooris, cod xooreed. e.g. This lemonade has lost its fizz.
fizzle out: /fisal-awt/ (v) fashilmid, dhicisoobid, damid. e.g. Our plans to travel abroad fizzled out when we realized how expensive the trip would be.
flag down: /flaag-dhawn/ (v) u-gacan haadin baabuur, si loo istaajiyo. e.g. I flagged down a taxi.
flagon: /flaagon/ (n) jaraafad ama jalamad cabitaanka lugu shubto.
flagship: /flaagship/ (n) maraakiibta dagaalka midka abaanduuluhu la socdo
flail: /fleyl/ (v) rux-ruxid, ku-wal-walaaqid. e.g. His legs flailed in the water.
flair: /fleer/ (n) karti-dabiici ah (hibo dabiici ah). e.g. He has a flair for writing.
flake: /fleyk/ (n) 1. qalbac; cad-yar oo khafiif ah. e.g. corn flakes (v) 2. qalbac-qalbac u-jajabid, qolof-jabid. e.g. His skin is flaking.
flamboyant: /flaamboyanti (adj) soo-jiidad leh, indhaha soo jiidan og. e.g. a flamboyant white dress.
flamingo: /flemingo/ (n) shimbir-badeed xuurka u-eg, kasa qurxoon oo midab casuur ah leh.
flannel: /flannal/ (n) suuf duf-badan, sida kan bustayaasha laga sameeyo
flap: /flaap/ (v) 1. babasho, wax habda dhinaca u babanaya (n) 2. shay meel ka laalaada (laalaad) (n) 3. qas, lab jaahwareer
flare: /fleer/ (n) 1. balal, holac 2. balalid, holcid (v) 3. halaf ka dhigid, goonno ama surweel hoosta laga ballaariyo.
flash: /flaash/ (v) 1. walalac-siin, nal bilig laga siiyo. e.g. Could you stop flashing that light in my eyes? (v) 2. dirid, sida war, farriin iwm (n) 3. bilig, walalac (n) 4. war baahin u idaaco, teleefishin ama telegaraam laga xigto (n) 5. falaashka, ama ifka kaamarada
flash-back: /flaash baak/ (v)(n) dib u-milicsi dhacdo-hore, sida qayb filin ama sheeko ku-jirta oo lays tuso sidii kol-hore wax u dheceen
flashlight: /flaash-layt/ (n) 1. toosh, karbuuno (n) 2. falaashka ama ifisada kaamarada.
flashy: /flaashi/ (adj) dhal-dhalaalaya, badanaa dhalaal aan tayo wehelin. e.g. a flashy car.
flask: /flaask/ (n) 1. tarmuus, falaas (n) 2. dhalo dhuun-dhuuban salkana u ballaaran oo badanaa lugu isticmaalo laabka ama macmalka kiimikada iwm.
flat: /flaat/ (adj) 1. siman, bagafsan (adj) 2. xalleefsan (adj) 3. banjar ah, shaag banjar ah (taayir) (adj) 4. qayaxan, iska-cad. e.g. She gave a flat refusal. (adj) 5. dabacsan, siiba codka muusiga (n) 6. guri-degaan, (adv) 7. go'an (aan saa'id iyo naaqus lahayn).
flatly: /flaatli/ (adv) aslanba, si cad ama qayaxan. e.g. He flatly denied it.
flat rate: /flaat-reyt/ (n) sicir-go'an, qiima-go'an oo aan marna is-bedelin. e.g. Eat all you can, and pay a flat rate of nine dollars.
flatter: /flaater/ (v) 1. ammaanid been-ah (u af-macaanin) (v) 2. ka-badbadin, si-xaqiiqda ka duwan u-muujin (v) 3. ku-faanid
flaunt: /flont/ (v) is-tustusid, halagaa-sheego iyo faan, dadka is-tustusid.
flavor: /fleyvar/flavour (n) 1. dhadhan, lasow. e.g. This tea has a wonderful flavor. (n) 2. jaad, nooc.
flavoring: /fleyverin/ (n) iidaan, wax cuntada lugu daro oo dhadhan uyeela.
fleece: /filiis/ (n) 1. suufka idaha, suufka laga sameeyo dufta idaha. (v) 2. dhicid, maal ka dhicid
fleecy: /filiisi/ (adj) suuf-ah, suufka idaha ka-samaysan ama shabbaha.
fleet: /filiit/ (n) 1. cutub maraakiib ah, oo isku hal abaanduule leh. (n) 2. cutub baabuur ah oo isku hal- maamul hoos yimaada. e.g. A fleet of buses was expected to arrive.
flesh: /flesh/ (n) 1. hilib, jiir, jismi (n) 2. buruqda miraha ee dhexda ku jirta.
flesh and blood: /flesh an-balaadh/ (n) ehel, qaraabada jiir iyo dhiig la wadaago. e.g. I have to help him because he is my flesh and blood.
flex: /fleksi/ (n) 1. soo-laabid, ama dhaq-dhaqaajin muruq ama addin, siiba carbin darteed. (n) 2. kaawo ama fiilo koronto oo laabmi og.
flexible: /fleksabal/ (adj) 1. laabmaya, qalloocsami kara (adj) 2. badbaddalmi kara, la bad-baddali karo
flextime: /fleksitaym/ (n) shaqo shaqaaluhu doortaan waqtiga shaqo bilaabidda iyo dhammaynta
flick: /filik/ (v) 1. ku-dhufasho sahlan oo dhakhso ah (v) 2. dhaqaajin degdeg ah ama kado ah. (n) 3. shaneemo. e.g. I am going to the flicks tonight.
flicker: /filikar/ (n) 1. danbaaburo (dhinbilaha dabka shidan ka boodbooda) (n) 2. boodboodid, si dhakhsa-ah u dhaqa-dhaqaaqid.
flier: /falaayar/flyer (n) qoraal-warqadeed oo ogeysiin ama xayiisiin ah, oo badanaa gacan lugu qaybiyo.
flimsy: /flimsi/ (adj) khafiif ah. e.g. a flimsy dress.
flint: /flint/ (n) 1. dhagax-adag oo dhaliya is-lis dab kolkii bir lugu xoqo. (n) 2. maaddo macdan-adag ah, oo loo adeegsado dab-dhalinta sida garxisada sigaarka lugu shito.
flip: /flip/ (v) 1. hawada u-tuurid, sida shilin hawada loo tuuro, oo dhulka si rog-rogmad ah u soo dhaca. (v) 2. rogid, gaddiyid. e.g. to flip an egg over in the pan.
flip through: /flip-thuruu/ (v) rog-rogid, sida buug la dul-maro. e.g. I flipped through the pages of the book.
flippant: /flipant/ (adj) tix-gelin daran. e.g. a flippant statement.
flipper: /fliper/ (n) 1. addin-dabaaleed, addin fiiqan oo ay leeyihiin xayawaan badeed-ka qaarkood oo ay ku-dabaashaan (n) 2. kab caynkaas u eg oo dabaasha sahasha.
flirt: /flert/ (v) 1. xod-xodasho (siiba is mashashuurin ama soo-jiidasho). e.g. Ismalura flirts with all the boys. (v) 2. is-jecleysiin, sida fikrad lugu fakaro, aanse la goosan. (n) 3. qofka, siiba naagta is-mashashuurta ama damac shukaansi muujisa.
float: /flowt/ (v) 1. sabbayn (v) 2. aasaasid, abuurid (v) 3. sabbaynta sicirka lacageed ee waddan (n) qadar lacag-ah, oo sarrif ahaan meel loo dhigo.
floating voters: /flowting-vowteris/ (n) cod-bixiyayaasha aan xisbi gooni ah u woodin.
flogging: /flogin/ (n) garaacis, siiba jeedal la dhicis, karbaashid
flood: /flaadh/ (n) 1. daad (v) 2. daad-qaadid, fatahmid (v) 3. soo fatahmis, in-badan kusoo gelid. e.g. Refugees flooded from Europe to Canada.
floodlight: /flaadh-layt/ (n) nal if weyn, oo badanaa lugu xiro garoomada ciyaaraha iwm
floor: /floor/ (n) 1. sagxadda dhulka (n) 2. dabaq, dabakh e.g. My apartment is on the first floor. (v) 3. sagxad u samayn (v) 4. jebin, ka-rayn.
flop: /flop/ (v) 1. dhicid, siiba si sirgaxan ama si-xun u dhicid (v) 2. laalaadid, lulasho (n) 3. fashilaad, guul-darro
florid: /flooridh/ (adj) 1. sharraxaad lugu dhoo-dhoobay ama laga badiyey. (adj) 2. waji guduutay ama la-guduudiyey.
florist: /floorist/ (n) ubax-gade, qofka ubaxa uruuriya oo gada.
flotsam: /flotsam (n) badeecadda baddu soo-caariso, oo markab jabay ka daadatay.
flounce: /flawns/ (v) kash-kash u-dhaqaaqid, oo siiba xanaaq muujin ah. e.g. She flounced out of the house in a huff.
flounder: /flawndher/ (v) rafasho, ama fargasho, siiba biyo dhexdood.
flourish: /floorish/ (v) 1. bulaalid, barwaaqoobid, tarmid, badasho (v) 2. muujin, haadin, dadka u-muujin ama tusid (n) 3. is-tustus, hab is-tustus iyo muujin ah wax u-samayn.
flout: /flowt/ (v) ku-tumasho, tixgelin la'aan. e.g. I was surprised that he could flout the law and get away with it.
flow: /flow/ (v) 1. qul-qulid (n) 2. qulqul (qol-qol). e.g. She worked quickly to staunch the flow of blood.
flower pot: / flawar-pat/ (n) weelka-ubaxa, weel ubaxa lugu tallaalo oo uu ka baxo.
flowery: /flaweri/ (adj) ubax-leh, ubax lugu qurxiyey ama shabbaha.
flue: /fluu/ (n) shoolad, dhuun qaaca ama kulka saarta
fluency: /fluuwensi/ (n) faseexnimo (si qeexan oo aan hakad-lahayn loogu hadlo)
fluent: /fluuwent/ (adj) faseex ah, qof luuqad si qeexan oo hakad-la'aan ah ugu hadla. e.g. He is not fluent in Arabic.
fluff: /flaf/ (n) 1. duf, gas (v) 2. duf ka kicin (v) 3. gefid, khalad u samayn.
fluke: /fluuk/ (n) nasiib-badni, biti, wax nasiib iyo fursad ku dhaca. e.g. It was a fluke that She passed her exam.
flunk out: /flank awt/ (infl.)(v) ka saaqidid ama ka cayrin iskuul. e.g. He flunked out of university and went to work as a cashier.
fluorescent: /flooresent/ (adj) 1. if-bixiye (maaddo if-cawiraad ah bixisa kolka koronto dhex marto) (adj) 2. if xoog u dhalaalaya (if cawiraad leh).
fluoride: /flooraydh/ (n) maaddo kiimiko ah, oo u-roon caafimaadka ilkaha.
flurry: /fleri/ (n) 1. dabayl-yar ama baraf si dhakhso iyo kadis ah u socda ama u-dhaca. (n) 2. dareen-guud oo kadis ah. (v) 3. wareerin (jaah-wareerin).
flush: /flash/ (n) 1. biyo-raacis (v) 2. biyo raacin (v) 3. guduudasho, siiba jirka qofka (adj) 4. la-siman, la-heer ah. e.g. The electric socket is flush with the wall. (adj) 5. ka-dharagsan (qani ka-ah)
fluster: /flaster/ (n) 1. jaah-wareer (isku dhex yaacis) (v) 2. wareerin, kicin, qas ku-abuurid.
flute: /fluut/ (n) siin-baar (qalab muusig oo turunbo u eg, oo leh daldaloolo codadka laga-baddalo).
flutist: /fluutist/ (n) qofka ka-dhawaajiya siin-baarta, nooca leh daloolada codadka laga baddalo.
flutter: /flater/ (v) 1. babbasho, sida baalasha shimbiraha iwm (v) 2. isku-dhex yaacid, jaahwareerid, kado ama farxad darteed.
fly: /flaay/flew (v) 1. duulid, haadid, lalid (v) 2. diyaarad ku safrid, ku-duulid (n) 3. dikhsi, duqsi
flying: /flaaying/ (adj) 1. haadaya, duulaya (n) 2. duulitaan, siiba duulitaanka diyaaradda.
flying saucer: /flaaying-sosar/ (n) saxuunta duusha (saxuun duusha oo la citiqaadsan yahay inay ka yimaadeen meere kale).
fob off: /fob of/ (v) ku-dirqin, ku-khaarijin, ku-sii jeedin, sida qof lugu sii-jeediyo wax aan ahayn wuxuu rabay.
focus: /fookas/ (n) 1. barta-bartamaha, (bar-kulmis), sida barta fallaaraha ilayska iwm, lugu aadiyo. (v) 2. xoog-saarid, ahmiyad-saarid, sida bar-tilmaameed diirad lugu eego. (v) 3. ku-aaddin, ku-shiisid. e.g. She forgot to focus the camera.
fodder: /fadher/ (n) raashinka xoolaha, siiba fardaha la siiyo.
fogbound: /fogbawndh/ (adj) ciiryaamo ku xayirmid, ciiryaamo la dhaqaaqi waayid.
foil: /foyl/ (n) 1. seef dhuuban oo badanaa lugu dheelo (n) 2. warqad macdan ka samaysan (n) 3. ka-badalnaan (ka-duwanaansho) (v) 4. ku-fashilmid, ku-jabid, sida khiddad iwm, oo lugu guul darraysto.
foist: /foyst/ (v) ku-dirqin, sida wax aan la rabin oo qof lugu dirqiyo ama la-yeelsiiyo.
