gang: /gaang/ (n) 1. burcad, qawleysato, gaangeystaro (n) 2. baando, koox saaxiibo ah, siiba wada-shaqayn leh.
gangrene: /gaangarin/ (n) qurmista jirka meel ka mid ah, kolka wareegga dhiiggu uu ka go, jirro ama dhaawac darteed.
gangster: /gaangestar/ (n) gaan-geystar, xubin ka-tirsan gaangeystaro ama burcad.
gangway: /gaangwey/ (n) waddo socota oo qaab buundo u-dhisan oo isku-xirta dhulka iyo doon ama markab.
gantry: /gaantari/ (n) dhis bira-ah, oo lugu taakeeyo mashiin culus iwm.
gape: /geyp/ (v) 1. yaabid afka laba taako laga dhigo, amakaag afka lala kala qaado (v) 2. kala-qaadid, kala-furid.
garage sale: /garaaj-seel/ (n) xaraash alaabo duug ah, oo lugu qabto xaafad dhexdeed.
garbage: /gaarbij/ (n) 1. qashin, khashin (n) 2. hadal ama fikrad qurun ah.
garbled: /gaarbaldh/(adj) hadal tashwiish ku jiro, ama xaqiiqda ka weecsan.
garden: /gaardhan/ (n) 1. beer, siiba beerta ubaxa, khudradda iwm ka baxaan. (n) 2. beerta nasashada (jardiino) (v) 3. beer samayn. e.g. She is good at gardening.
gargantuan: /gaargaanjuwan/ (adj) aad u-weyn, siiba wax cunto la xiriira.
garish: /gaarish/ (adj) dhalaal cawiraad ah, dhalaal indhaha u-daran e.g. garish color.
garland: /garlandh/ (n) xirmo wareegsan oo ubax ah, oo surka la gashado, badanaa si guul loo muujiyo.
garnish: /garnish/ (v) 1. qurxin lugu bilo cuntada (n) 2. waxyaabaha cuntada lugu qurxiyo.
garrison: /gaarisan/ (n) 1. ciidan milateri, oo difaac ahaan loo dejiyo magaalo ama qalcad. (v) 2. ciidan difaac u dirid, siiba qalcad ama magaalo loo diro.
gas: /gaas/ (n) 1. walax sida neefta oo kala ah (n) 2. neefta gaaska ah ee tamarta kulka dhalisa, sida gaaska la shito. (n) 3. baasiin (n) 4. gaaska sunta ah, oo aalaaba ciidamadu isticmaalaan.
gas chamber: /gaas-jeymbar/ (n) qol sunta gaaska laga buuxiyo, si noole loogu dilo.
gas mask: /gaas mask/ (n) af-shareer gaas (maas-garo sunta gaaska laga xirto).
gastric: /gaastarik/ (adj) ee caloosha, caloosha la xiriira. e.g. a gastric ulcer.
gastronomy: /gaastronami/ (n) habka cunto karinta ama cuntada fiican.
gate: /geyt/ (n) 1. ganjeello, albaab weyn (n) 2. lacagta ay bixiyaan daawada-yaasha ciyaarta, siiba kubbadda cagta.
gather: /gaathar/ (v) 1. isu-uruurid (v) 2. ogaansho, fahmid. e.g. I gather she will come tomorrow. (v) 3. isku-tolid, siiba tolliin maro laysku uruuriyo.
gauche: /gowj/ (adj) sirgaxan, wax xun, oo aan habboonayn.
gaunt: /goont/ (adj) maliil ah, xayiisi ah cudur ama baahi darteed.
gauze: /gooz/ (n) maro shabaq ah, oo badanaa faashad ahaan loo adeegsado.
gavel: /gaaval/ (n) dubbe-yar, siiba midka qaalligu uu miiska ku garaaco.
gawky: /gooki/ (adj) qofka fiiro-badan ama dhaq-dhaqaaq qaab-darro ah sameeya.
gazelle: /gazel/ (n) golcas (jaad ugaarta ka mid ah oo gol cas).
gazette: /gazet/ (n) jariidad, siiba joornaal ogeysiisyada dawladda lugu soo qoro.
gear: /giir/ (n) 1. marsho, geyr (n) 2. xirmo alaab ama qalab ah, oo wax gaar ah loogu talo galay. (n) 3. dhar, labbis (v) 4. ugu-tala galid, u-qaabayn, u-astayn. e.g. This book is geared to young adults.
gearbox: /giirbakis/ (n) qafiska marshada, halka marshada baabuurka bad-baddasha.
gel: /jel/jell; (v) 1. adkaansho, adayg noqosho (v) 2. waadax-noqosho (n) 3. maaddo jil-jilicsan, oo saliid leh, oo timaha hadba moodadii la rabo ka dhigta.
gelatinous: /jelaatnas/ (adj) jil-jilicsan, maaddo u dhaxaysa adke iyo dareere.
gem: /jem/ (n) 1. jawharad (n) 2. shay ama qof qiima-gaar ah leh.
Gemini: /jemanay/ (n) calaamadda burjiga dadka dhasha inta u dhaxaysa May 21 - June 20.
gender: /jendhar/ (n) jinsi (jaadka qofku yahay, sida dheddig ama lab).
general: /jenaral/ (n) 1. guud (n) 2. janan, jeeneraal (darajo ciidan oo sare).
generalize: /jenaralayz/ (v) guud-ahaan ka-dhigid, wax guud laga dhigo.
generate: /jenareyt/ (v) dhalin, keenid, sida dab, koronto iwm dhalin.
generation: /jenareyshan/ (n) 1. jiil, fac (n) 2. dhalin, sida dhalinta-danabka iwm.
generic: /janerik/ (n) 1. isku-jinsi, isku-jaad ama isku-fir (n) 2. magac ama oraah wax koobaysa, siiba waxyaabaha isku-jaadka ah.
generous: /jenaras/ generously; (adj) 1. deeqsi, sikhi (adj) 2. badan, ka badan intii la rabay. e.g. a generous sum of money.
genial: /jiinyal/ (adj) 1. farxaan ah oo beer-nugul (adj) 2. cimilo fiican, oo noolaha u-roon.
genitals: /jenitals/ genital; (n) saxaax (xubnaha dhalmada iyo halkay ku-yaalliin).
genitive: /jenativ/ (adj) naxwe-ahaan, kalmadda ama oraahda tusisa lahaansho ama asal-ahaansho.
genius: /jiinyas/ (n) 1. cabqari, aad u maskax badan. e.g. Isaac Newton was a genius. 2. xariiftinimo (karaan dabiici ah leh).
genteel: /jentiil/ (adj) ed-boon, siiba si xad-dhaaf ah u dhawrsi-badan.
genuine: /jenyuwin/ (adj) 1. dhab-ah, xaqiiq-ah (adj) 2. daacad ah, run ah.
geology: /jiyolaji/ (n) barashada waxyaabaha dhulku uu ka samaysan-yahay iyo taariikhdooda, sida dhagaxda, ciidda, macdanta iwm.
geometry: /jiyomatri/ (n) joomatari, cilmiga xisaabta ee la xiriira xaglaha iyo xarriiqaha.
geriatrics: /jeriyaatriks/ (n) daaweynta iyo xannaanayta dadka da'da ah.
germ: /jerm/ (n) 1. jeermis (noole ilma-aragto ah, oo cudurada keena) (n) 2. barta-biloowga, sida fikradda biloowga ah.
gerund: /jerandh/ (n) magaca salkiisu yahay falka la-qabtay oo ku dhammaada 'ing' sida building.
gestation: /jesteyshan/ (n) 1. calool ku-qaadidda (calool ku-sidista uur- kujirku intaanu dhalan) (n) 2. shinka ama marxaladaha arini marto ama qaadato.
gesticulate: /jestikyaleyt/ (v) gacmaha iyo faraha dhaq-dhaqaajin, kolka la hadlayo, gacma ka hadlid.
gesture: /jesjar/ (v) 1. dhaq-dhaqaajinta jirka ama gacmaha, si ra'yi ama dareen loo muujiyo (n) 2. fal muujinaya dareenka qofka. e.g. I invited him to dinner as a gesture of friendship.
get: /get/ (v) 1. helid ama u-keenid. e.g. I got a letter from my friend. (v) 2. noqosho, kusoo-bixid. e.g. She is getting old (v) 3. tegid, gaarid. e.g. I got home very late. (v) 4. asiibid, ku-dhicid. e.g. I have got a cold. (v) 5. yeel-siin, ka-qancin. e.g. I got the lawyer to call. (v) 6. fahmid. e.g. I don't get it.
get across: /get-akros/ (v) gudbin, fahansiin, sida fikrad la-gaarsiiyo dad ama qof. e.g. He had difficulty in getting his point across.
get along: /get aloon/ (v) 1. is-fahmid, si saaxiibnimo leh isu-fahmid. e.g. These two girls get along well (v) 2. socodsiin, horumarin. e.g. How are things getting along? (v) 3. tegid, bixid. e.g. She has to be getting along now.
get at: /get at/ (v) 1. gaarid, soo-qabasho. e.g. Put the medicine where the kids can't get at it. (v) 2. u-jeedid, ka-wadid. e.g. I don't understand what you are getting at.
get away: /get-awey/ (v) baxsasho, fakasho. e.g. Two of the prisoners got away.
get away with: /get awey with/ (v) ku bax-sasho, ku-badbaadid dambi iwm. e.g. She thinks she can get away with murder.
get by: /get bay/ (v) ku-noolaansho, is-debirid. e.g. Don't worry, he'll get by.
get down: /get-dhawn/ (v) 1. dhunjin, dejin, dhib ku liqid. e.g. Could you try to get the medicine down? (v) 2. u-soo jeensasho, u-dhaaraansi. e.g. Get down to business. (v). 3. qorid. e.g. Let me get this information down. (v) 4. madluumin, hoos u-dhigid.
get in: /get in/ (v) 1. soo-gelid. e.g. Can I get in? (v) 2. la-doorto, guulaysi jago. e.g. He got in by a small majority. (v) 3. hadal dhex-galin. e.g. Can I get a word in? (v) 4. imaansho. e.g. The train got in late.
get into: /get intu/ (v) 1. galid, dhex-galid (v) 2. barasho ama u-barasho.
get off: /get of/ (v) 1. ka-bixid, dhammayn shaqo oo kale. e.g. When does he get off work? (v) 2. ka-dagid, ka-dhaadhacid. e.g. I must get off the bus. (v) 3. ciqaab ka badbaadin ama u fududayn.
get on: /get on/ (v) 1. socda, ama moodaya. e.g. He is getting on in years. (v) 2. wadid, sii-socosho. e.g. I must get on with my work. (v) 3. fuulid, gaari iwm. e.g. He got on the plane at Nairobi. (v) 4. is-fahmid, saaxiibid. e.g. I get on well with her. (v) 5. dhar xirasho. e.g. Get your coat on.
get out: /get awt/ (v) 1. bixid ama bax. e.g. No one knows how he got out. (v) 2. soo-saarid. e.g. I'll have to get this report out before next week. (v) 3. bixid, sida war dibadda usoo-baxa.
get out of: /get-awt-of/ (v) 1. ka baxsasho, sida shaqo ama masuuliyad oo kale (v) 2. iska-dayn, ka-tagid (v) 3. ka-soo saarid, xoog uga soo saarid (v) 4. ka-helid, ka faa'iidid. e.g. I don't know why people smoke. What do they get out of it?
get over: /get owvar/ (v) 1. ka-caafimaadid, ka-kicid. e.g. She got over her illness quickly. (v) 2. gaarsiin, u-gudbin, fahansiin (v) 3. dhammayn, iska-dhammayn.
get through: /get-thruu/ (v) 1. taleefoon ku helid. e.g. I tried to call you but I couldn't get through. (v) 2. gudbid, dhaafid (v) 3. fahansiin, ka dhaadhicin (v) 4. dhammayn, gaarid hawl iwm (v) 5. ku-baasid imtixaan. e.g. She got through her final exam with no trouble.
geyser: /gaysar/ (n) biyo gantaal ah, oo dhulka ka soo baxa.
ghastly: /gaastli/ (adj) 1. wax laga naxo, ama shoog leh (adj) 2. aad u-xun, liita.
ghetto: /getow/ (n) xaafad ama degmo ay ku nool-yihiin dad fakhriya, ama aan waddaniyiin loo aqoonsan.
ghost: to give up the ghost ~ dhimasho, xijaabasho.
ghost of a: inta ugu-yar, in-yarna.
gibberish: /gibarish/ (n) hadal macna daran, macna-la'aan. e.g. He talks gibberish when he is drunk.
gibbon: /giban/ (n) xayawaan u eg daanyeerka, oo aan sayn lahayn.
giblets: /jiblits/ (n) xubnaha shimbirta ee ay ka mid yihiin beerka iyo wadnaha oo laga saaro intaan la karin ka-hor.
gift: /gift/ (n) 1. hadiyad (n) 2. hibo, sida awood dabiici ah oo qof lugu manaystay. e.g. She has a gift for music.
gigantic: /jaygaantik/ (adj) xad-dhaaf u weyn. e.g. I never realized how gigantic the space shuttle was until I saw it up close.
giggle: /gigal/ (v) 1. qoslid, siiba qosol wirix ah, ama dhikh-dhik ah. e.g. She giggled when the boy asked her if she would like to dance. (n) 2. qosol-wirix, qosol dhikh-dhikh ah.
gilt: /gilt/ (n) shay dhalaalaya, siiba dahab ah. e.g. The gilt on the plates was wearing off.
gimmick: /gimik/ (n) khatal wax lugu soo jiito. e.g. Advertising companies always try to find gimmicks to promote a firm's products.
gin: /jin/ (n) jiin, khamri culus oo aan midab lahayn.
ginger: /jinjer/ (n) 1. san-jabiil, sin-jibiil (n) 2. midabka guduudka iyo kafeega isku jirka ah.
gipsy: /jipsi/ gypsy; (n) qabiil garab rarato ah, oo yurub wareegi jiray.
girdle: /gerdhal/ (n) maro laastiko ka samaysan oo dumarku hoos ka xirto, si ay ugu giijiyaan dibka iyo simaha.
girlfriend: /gerl-freendh/ (n) 1. gabar-saaxiib ah. e.g. She has known her girlfriend for years. (n) 2. saaxiibad (gabadha wiilku la socdo asagoon guursan). e.g. He likes to have a new girlfriend every month.
girl scout: /gerl iskot/ (n) urur gabdhaha u tababara asluubta suuban.
girth: /gerth/ (n) dhumucda, cabbirka dhumucda sida dhumucda geed jirridiis, qof dhexdiis iwm.
gist: /jist/ (n) nuxurka, sida nuxurka ama inta ugu muhiimsan ee hadalka iwm.
give: /giv/ (v) 1. siin, bixin. e.g. Please give me some money. 2. qalloocsamid ama kala-bixid.
give away: /giv-awey/ (v) 1. bixin, hibeyn. e.g. He gave away all his money. (n) 2. kashifaad, wax sir dibadda u soo saara. e.g. She pretended to be poor but her clothes were a dead giveaway.
give back: /giv-bak/ (v) u-celin, dib u siin. e.g. Could you give me back my money?
give in: /giv-in/ (v) is-dhiibid. e.g. The soldiers fought until one gave in.
give out: /giv awt/ (v) bixin, u-qaybin. e.g. Please give out the exam papers.
give up: /giv ap/ (v) 1. quusasho, ka-raja dhigid. e.g. I can't understand this question, so I think I'll give up. (v) 2. joojin, iska-dayn. e.g. You must give up smoking.
given: /givan/ (adj) 1. la-bixiyey, sida wax go'an oo laysa siiyo. e.g. The job must be done within the given time. (prep) 2. ka soo-qaad, haddii laga-soo qaado. e.g. Given that y equals two, y plus two is four.
glamor: /glamar/ glamour; (n) soo-jiidasho, jinniyad, qurux gaar ah.
glare: /gleer/ (v) 1. ku-dhaygagid, siiba indhaha lugu gubo (v) 2. shucaac bixin, iftiin aad u-daran bixin (n) 3. dhaygag indho gubis ah ama xanaaq leh (n) 4. shucaac, ilayska xoogga badan.
glaring: /gleering/ (adj) 1. aad u iftiimaya, shucaac badan ka baxayo (adj) 2. aad u-muuqda, sida khalad iska cad oo kale.
glaze: /gleys/ (v) 1. muraayad gelin, siiba daaqadaha iwm (v) 2. muraayad ku dheehid (v) 3. indhuhu rogmadaan ama caddaadaan. e.g. When the doctor gave him an injection, his eyes glazed and he became unconscious.
gleam: /gliim/ (n) 1. bir-biriq, dhal-dhalaal (v) 2. bir-birid. e.g. The cat's eyes were gleaming in the dark.
glean: /gliin/ (v) isu soo-uruurin, siiba akhbaar si dhib badan lugu soo aruuriyo.
glib: /glib/ (adj) 1. af-miinshaar ah. e.g. The salesman was a glib talker. (adj) 2. hadal sahal loo yiraahdo, oo aan la aamini karin.
glide: /glaydh/ (v) 1. sibiibaxasho, dilin-dilloon (v) 2. diyaarad aan matoor lahayn ku-duulid.
glimmer: /glimar/ (n) 1. kaah, iftiin nuxuus ah. e.g. the glimmer of a candle (n) 2. wax ama saansaan yar. e.g. a glimmer of hope.
gloat: /glowt/ gloatly; (v) ku-digasho, dhib qof gaaray ama ka maqsuudid guul aad gaarto. e.g. He was gloating over my bankruptcy.
global: /glowbal/ (adj) koonka, adduunkoo dhan, caalamka. e.g. The United Nations is a global organization. (adj) 2. wareeg-ah, guud. e.g. I can perhaps devise a global solution that will cover all these problems.
globe: /glowb/ (n) 1. wareegga dhulka, adduunka wareegiisa (n) 2. wax kubbad oo kale ah. (n) 3. guluubka nalka.
globule: /globyul/ (n) dhibic-yar oo dareere ah, siiba dareere dhalaalsan.
gloomy: /gluumi/ (adj) 1. mugdi ah (adj) 2. qof madluunsan, ama wax muruga-leh.
gloss: /gloos/ (n) 1. dhalaal kore (dhalaal dheeh ah) (n) 2. sharax, siiba sharaxa bog ama buug dhammaadkii lugu dhigo.
gloss over: /gloos owva/ (v) dedid, qarin, siiba cillad ama xumaan la daboolo.
glove: /glav/ (n) gacan-gashi (gacan-gashi, la gashado faraha ilaa curcurta oo gacanta looga gaashaamo dhaxanta iwm).
glow: /glow/ (v) 1. kaahid, iftiimid (v) 2. wajiga ka guduudasho, kul, qabow ama qiiro darteed.
glower: /glower/ (v) indho ku-gubid, indho xanaaq leh ku eegid.
glowing: /glowin/ (adj) 1. ammaanaya, sawir ama fikrad fiican ka bixinaya (adj) 2. kaahaya.
glucose: /glukows/ (n) gulukoos, nooc sonkor ah oo jirka qofka tamar siisa.
glut: /glat/ (v) 1. dhereg-dhaafin, in-badan siin (n) 2. qaraq, tira-badan, xaddi-dhaaf.
gnarled: /narldh/ (adj) jilfax-ah (sida geed jirridiis iwm, oo adayg gowtiyo badan noqda, badanaa gabow ama isticmaal dartiis).
gnash: /naash/ (v) ilkaha isku-xoqid, caro ama wal-wal dartiis.
gnaw: /noo/ (v) 1. qan-qaniinid, siiba ilaa laga duleeliyo (v) 2. maskaxda ka xanuujin, shiddo ku beerid. e.g. The feeling that I had forgotten something gnawed at me.
gnome: /nowm/ (n) nin-yar oo foolxun, oo dhulka hoostiisa dahab ku-ilaasha, oo lugu soo qaato sheekooyinka quraafada ah.
go: /goo/ (v) 1. tagid, tag (v) 2. noqosho ama isu-beddelid. e.g. The food will go bad if it is not refigerated. (v) 3. la-dhigo, lugu xafido. e.g. The glass goes in the cupboard.
go about: / (v) gudasho, fulin, samayn. e.g. How do I go about it?
go ahead: / (v) 1. idan-siin. e.g. I asked him not to touch it, so why did he go ahead and touch it anyway. (v) 2. samayn, bilaabid.
go along: / (v) 1. wadid, sida shaqo la wado oo kale. e.g. I like to do the checking as I go along. (v) 2. ku waafiqid, ayidid. e.g. I'll go along with your idea
go around: / (v) 1. wareegid, fidid, sida cudur ama war oo kale (v) 2. la-wareegid, sida cid lala'saaxiibo oo lala war-wareego. e.g. Why does she go around with such bad people?
go by: / (v) 1. gudbid, baasid. e.g. Two cars went by. (2) ku-socosho, ku-dhaqmid. e.g. I can't go by what he says.
go down: / (v) 1. hoos u-dhicid, hoos u-socosho. e.g. The price will go down during the sale. (v) 2. quusid, degid. e.g. Two ships went down in the rough water. (v) 3. diiwaan-gelin qorid.
go for: / (v) 1. weerarid, ataagid. e.g. Our dog went for the mailman's leg whenever she saw him. (v) 2. raadin, jirin. e.g. to go for a job interview. (v) 3. ku dhaqaaqid, doorasho. e.g. Don't hesitate, go for it.
go into: / (v) 1. galid, sida galid meel, arin iwm. e.g. to go into the city. (v) 2. baarid, guda-galid. e.g. Let's go into details now.
go off: / (v) 1. qarxid, ama kor u-qaylin (v) 2. tegid, bixid. e.g. She went off to college yesterday. (v) 3. nicid. e.g. I went off with that man. (v) 4. gam'id ama miyir-beelid. (v) 5. damid. e.g. This light goes off at night.
go on: / (v) 1. ka-dhacaya, ka-socda. e.g. What is going on here? (v) 2. ku sii-wadid, ku sii-socosho. e.g. If she goes on like that, she will lose her friends. (v) 3. daarmid. e.g. The lights go on at 7 o'clock every night.
go out: / (v) 1. bixid, guriga ka bixid siiba madadaalo darteed (v) 2. isla-bixid, waqti wada-qaadasho. e.g. She has been going out with him for two years. (v) 3. socdaalid, meel dheer u-bixid. e.g. Alex went out to the east coast for a holiday. (v) 4. damid, sida dab, nal iwm. e.g. The fire will soon go out.
go over: / (v) 1. fiirin, baarid. e.g. I will go over the list of names and chose one. (v) 2. ku-laabasho, ku-celin (v) 3. baddalasho, sida xisbi, diin iwm. e.g. He went over to the Democrats after their election victory.
go through: / (v) 1. rasmi u ogolaansho, la ogolaado. e.g. After much debate the deal will probably go through. (v) 2. marid, sida dhib soo-marid. e.g. He went through many difficult times in his life. (v) 3. fiirin, baarid. e.g. I went through the questions.
go together: / (v) is-raaca ama isku-fiican. e.g. her dress and accessories go together.
go under: / (v) quusid, degid. e.g. The ship went under during the storm.
go up: / (v) kor u-kicid. e.g. prices go up every month.
go with: / (v) 1. ku-fiican, ku-baxaya. e.g. The tie goes with his shirt. (v) 2. la-socda, badanaa raacsan. e.g. Illness often goes with poverty. (v) 3. is-raaca, laysku gado. e.g. The carpets will go with the house.
go-between: /go-bitwiin/ (n) u-dhexeeye, qofka laba qolo oo aan is-arki karin u dhexeeya oo farriimaha u kala qaada.
goblet: /goblit/ (n) koob cabbitaan oo sal leh, badanaa khamriga lugu cabbo.
going: /gowin/ (n) tagis, bixid. e.g. We shall have a party to celebrate her going.

hint: /hint/ (n) 1. guud-mar, kor-mar (hadal-yar ama baaq aan toos ahayn). e.g. He hinted that he would like a new watch for his birthday. (v) 2. tusmayn, talo-bixin waxtar leh.
hint at: /hint at/ (v) dul-marid bidhaamin. e.g. He hinted at leaving early.
his: /his/ (pron) kiisa (wixiisa). e.g. That is his car.
hiss: /his/ (v) cod xiin la-mid ah samayn. e.g. The cat hissed at the dog.
historical: /histoorikal/ (adj) 1. taariikh la xiriira. (adj) 2. taariikhi ah. e.g. a historical book.
histrionics: /histriyaniks/ (n) qiiro iyo shucuur badan oo badanaa ka badbadis ah. e.g. I am tired of her histrionics.
hit: /hit/ (v) 1. ku dhufasho, garaacid. (n) 2. caan-bixid, sida hees hal mar caan baxda. e.g. The song was a hit at once.
hit-and-run: /hit-an-ran/ (adj) shilka darawalka khaladka lihi uu cararo.
hitch: /hij/ (v) 1. ku-xirid, ama surid. (v) 2. lacag la'aan baabuur ku-raacid. (n) 3. dhibaato-yar. e.g. There had been two technical hitches.
hitch up: /hij-ap/ (v) 1. kor usoo-dhifasho, soo-jiidid. e.g. He hitched up his pants.(v) 2. ku-xirid, ku-callaqid.
hitchhike: /hijhayk/ (v) lacag la'aan baabuur ku raacid (lifti raacid).
hither: /hithar/ (adv) halkaan. e.g. Come hither please. hither and thither/hithar an-thithar/(adv) halkan iyo halkeer.
hive: /hayv/ (n) rugta shinnida (hoyga shinnidu malabka ku samayso).
hoarfrost: /hoorfroost/ (n) dhado (qabowga dhirta iwm, dul fuula xilliga qaboobaha).
hoax: /howkis/ (n) been (been-been). e.g. There was not a bomb in the camp at all; it was just a hoax.
hobnob: /habnab/ (v) la-saaxiibid, siiba qof darajo sare leh.
hobo: /howbow/ (infl)(n) dowdar (qof aan hoy iyo camal toona lahayn oo iska wareega).
hockey: /haki/ (n) 1. xeego (ciyaar kow-iyo-toban qof iyo kow-iyo-toban qof lugu ciyaaro, oo kubbad, ulo iyo laba gool oo isku aaddan lugu ciyaaro). (n) 2. xeegada barafka lugu ciyaaro.
hog: /hoog/ (n) 1. doofaar, siiba khaansiir, shilis ah. (infl) (v) 2. wada-qaadasho, sida cunto iwm oo qof wada cuno.
hold: /holdh/held (v) 1. qabasho, hayn. e.g. Could you hold this box for me? (v) 2. lahaansho ama haysasho. e.g. He holds the office of chairman. (v) 3. diyaarin, qabasho. e.g. We held a meeting.
hold against: /(v) u-qabsasho. e.g. Her refusal to co-operate will be held against her.
hold on: /holdh-on/ (v) sugid, u-kaadin (v) 2. qabsasho. e.g. Hold on to that rope. (v) 3. sii-wadis, ku-sii-wadid.
holder: /holdhar/ (n) 1. qof ama shay wax haya (haysta). e.g. a ticket holder (n) 2. milkiile.e.g. a house-holder.
holding: /holdhin/ (n) hanti, hantida qof haysto, sida guri, saami shirkadeed iwm.
hold up: /holdh-ap/ (n) 1. xayirmid, xannibmid. e.g. I am sorry I am late, I got held up at the house. (n) 2. dhac, siiba dhicis qoryo iwm laysku qabto.
hole: /howl/ (n) 1. dalool. e.g. There is a hole in my pocket. (n) 2. hog, god.
hole up: /howl ap/ (infl)(v) ku-dhuumasho. e.g. They holed up in an old factory.
hollow: /halow/ (adj) 1. bannaan, siiba aan dhexda waxba uga jirin (n) 2. hog ama dhul-godan
hollywood: /holiwuudh/ (n) rugta filin-samaynta ee ku taal Los Angeles.
holocaust: /holikoost/ (n) gumaad, baaba', siiba dab lugu baaba'o.
holy: /hooli/ (adj) barakaysan. e.g. The holy city of Mecca.
homogenize: /homajenays/ (v) isku-jaad ka dhigid, siiba caanaha subagooda si-siman loogu qaybiyo si aysan u kala-qaybsamin.
homonym: /homanin/ (n) isku-dhehmo (laba erey oo isku-dhihid kala macne ah). e.g. The words 'there' and 'their' are homonyms.
honestly: /onistli/ (adv)1. daacaddii, daacad-ahaan. e.g. Honestly, that is exactly what she said. (adv) 2. si-daacad ah.
honey: /hani/ (n) 1. malab. (n) 2. macaane ama macaan. e.g. I love you, honey.
honeymoon: /hani-muun/ (n) ayaamaha hore ee aqal-galka, oo badanaa waqti nasasho la-qaato oo la mid ah toddobaadka arooska ~ shahrul-casal.
honk: /hank/ (v) dhawaaq hoonka gaariga u-eg yeersiin. e.g. As he drove past, he honked the horn.
honor: /onar/(ame) honour (bre) (n) 1. sharaf. (v) 2. maamuusid, xurmayn, sharfid. (v) 3. ballan-fulin, sida lacag qof ballan qaaday oo uu bixiyo. e.g. She honored her debts before she left.
Honorable: /onarabal/ honourable (adj) erey loogu yeero dadka madaxda sare ah oo lugu maamuuso. e.g. Will the Honorable Member please answer the question?
honors: /onaras/ (ame) honours (bre) (n) 1. shahaado jaamacadeed oo buundo-sare ama takhasus gaar ah lugu sameeyey. e.g. He graduated with honors. (n) 2. xaflad-maamuus.
hood: /huudh (n) 1. madax-gashi (daboolka madaxa la gashado ee jaakadda dhaxanta ku-taal). (n) 2. goofanaha gaariga ee hore.
hook: /huuk/ (n) 1. jillaab (jilib, bir yar oo qaroofan oo kalluunka lugu dabo). (n) 2. katabaan, katabaanka dharka la-surto. (v) 3. jillaab ku-dabid. e.g. to hook a fish (v) 4. surid, sida dhar katabaan la suro. 5. get off the hook~ qool ka-saarid, dhibaato ka bixin. 6. by hook or by crook kor iyo hoos (si kasta).
hook up: /huuk ap/ (v) qalab rakibid ama meel ku xirid. e.g. Is the television hooked up?
hooked: /huukidh/ (adj) 1. qaroofan, gan u-eg, e.g. a hooked nose (adj) 2. qabatimay, sida wax qofku u barto ama aad u-jeclaado. e.g. She is hooked on hashish.
hooray: /huurey/ (n) baga (erey la yiraahdo kolkii la farxo ama sidii la rabay wax u dhacaan).
hoot: /huut/ (n) 1. dhawaqa hoonka gaariga. (n) 2. cida guumeysta. (v) 3. dhawaq-dheer yeerin, sida hoon gaari iwm. (v) 4. ku-qaylin, ku fooryid oo diidid ka macna ah. e.g. When she started to sing, we all hooted at her.
hooves: /huuvis/ (n) qoobab, qanjaafulo (waa hoof oo jamac ah).
hop: /hap/ (v) 1. dhakawlayn, hal-lug ku boodid .(v) 2. boodid, ku-boodid. e.g. He hopped on his bicycle.
horde: /hoordh/ (n) ciidaanyo (dad aad u-fara badan iwm). e.g. Hordes of tourists visit Toronto during the summer.
horizon: /harayzan/ (n) ili-kuwareertay (dhulka inta ishu qaban karto, xarriiqda soo koobta ama la moodo in dhulka iyo cirku iska galaan).
hornet: /hoornit/ (n) bahal xoonka u-eg oo qaniinyo kulul.
horny: /hoorni/ (adj) 1. qallafsan, qalleyf ah. e.g. The old factory workers had horny hands. (adj) 2. geesa-leh (adj) 3. kasci-badan, kacsanaya
horoscope: /hooraskowp/ (n) burjiga ama xiddiga qofka oo laga qiyaaso cilmi-falaga oo lugu saleeyo dhalashada qofka. e.g. My horoscope says that I'll become wealthy one day.
horrible: /hoorabal/ (adj) 1. naxdin-leh. (adj) 2. aad u-xun. e.g. What a horrible day.
horrify: /hoorafay/ (v) argagixin, naxdin-gelin e.g. I was horrified by the news.
hors d'oeuvres: /oor-derv/ (n) halaq-jafle (cuntada yar-yar oo raashinka hortiisa la sii-cuno oo lugu sii sugo).
hose: /hows/ (n) 1. tuubbo, siiba dhuun weyn. (v) 2. tuubbo ku waraabin. e.g. to hose the garden (n) 3. sharabaad, sigis.
hosiery: /howshari/ (n) sigisyada iyo dharka kale ee hoos-gashiga ah.
hospitable: /hospitabal/ (adj) diyaafad fiican, maamuus-fiican. e.g. Faa'isa is one of the most hospitable people I know.
hospitality: /hospitaaliti/ (n) marti-gelin (soo-dhawayn, diyaafad-wanaag). e.g. I thanked them for their hospitality.
hospitalize: /hospitalayz/ (v) isbataal dhigid. e.g. He was hospitalized for a month.
host: /howst/ (n) 1. marti-galiye. e.g. While I was in Cairo, my host was a friend I met at last year's conference. (n) 2. xiriiriye-barnaamij. e.g. Here is your host, Abdalla Nuradin. (n) 3. fara-badan, aad u-badan.
hostel: /hostel/ (n) xarun ama xero la dajiyo arday, dhalin-yaro iwm. e.g. a youth hostel.
hostess: /hoostis/ (n) 1. marti-galiso. (n) 2. hoos-tees (gabadha rakaabka diyaaradda u adeegta).
hostilities: /hostilitis/ (n) colaad, dagaal, iska-hor imaad. e.g. The two armies were engaged in hostilities.
hot-blooded: /hat-bladidh/ (adj) 1. kulul, xaraarad ama kacsi-badan. e.g. He is too hot-blooded to keep away from girls for long. (adj) 2. xanaaq-badan
hot dog: / (n) hilib-ridqan oo geedeysan oo rooti la dhex gashado
hound: /hawndh/ (n) 1. ey-duur, siiba midka lugu ugaarto. (v) 2. dhibid ama daba-galid. e.g. She was hounded by the press.
hour: /awar/ (n) saacad. e.g. There are sixty minutes in an hour.
house: /haws/ (n) 1.guri, aqal. (n) 2. gole. e.g. House of Commons (n) 3. on the house ~ bilaash, kharashka ay shirkad ama makhaayadi qabto. e.g. Coffee is on the house.
house arrest: /haws-arrest/ (n) xabsi-guri. e.g. He is under house arrest.
housekeeper: /hawskiipar/ (n) adeegto (xoojiso, qof dumar ah oo lacag ku qaadata ka adeegista guri, huteel iwm).
housekeeping: /haws-kiipin/ (n) 1. adeega iyo maamulka guriga. e.g. housekeeping is part of her job. (infl) 2. maqaasiirta guriga, sida masruufka iwm e.g. I pay the telephone bill out of the housekeeping.
housewife: /hawswayf/ (n) guri-joogto. e.g. She is a housewife.
housing: /hawsin/ (n) 1. guryeyn, dejin. (n) 2. guryo, degaan. (n) 3. qolofka adag ee matoorada iwm oo gaashaanka u-ah.
hove: /howv/ heave; (v) waa heave oo fal tagay ah.
hover: /havar/ (v) 1. heehaabid. (v) 2. war-wareegid, hobsha-hobshayn. e.g. Those kids are always hovering around me.
how: /haw/ (adv) 1. sidee. e.g. How do you read this word? (adv) 2. heerkee. e.g. How do you like it? (infl) 3. how come (sidee ku dhacday, waayo) e.g. How come I didn't get any money?
however: /haw evar/ (conj) 1. si-kasta. e.g. However hard I try, I still can not do it properly. (adv) 2. hase-yeeshee. e.g. I shall stay here; however, you are free to leave if you like.
howl: /hawl/ (n) 1. cabaad, qaylo. (v) 2. cabaadid, qaylin. e.g. The wolves howled all night.
hub: /hab/ (n) 1. bartamaha shaagga. (n) 2. xuddunta ama halka ugu muhiimsan ee arrin ama meeli leedahay.
hue: /hyuu/ (n) midab. e.g. There are flowers of many hues in the garden.
hug: /hag/ (n) 1. hab, haanyo. (v) 2. hab-siin. e.g. At the airport we were hugging and kissing.
huge: /hiyuuj/ (adj) cimlaaq (aad u weyn). e.g. A huge building dominated the skyline.
hullabaloo: /halabaluu/ (n) sawaxan, buuq. e.g. The teacher told the students to stop making such a hullabaloo.
humanism: /hyuumanism (n) rumaysnaanta falsafadda insaaniyadda oo aadanaha u gooni yeeleysa nidaamkooda iyadoon loo noqon caqiido diineed.
humanities: /hyuumaanitis/ (n) barashada adabka aadanaha, sida falsafadda, luqadaha, taariikhda iwm.
humble: /hambal/ (adj) 1. aan kibir badnayn (isla-weyni aan aqoon). (adj) 2. liidata, xun, hooseeya. e.g. a humble job.
humid: /hyuumidh/ (adj) qoyan, sayax ah, sida cimilo hawada ay ku jirto uumi-biyood iwm.
humor: /hyuumar/(ame) humour (bre) (n) 1. maad, kaftan. e.g. She has a good sense of humor.(adj) 2. himmada, niyadda, ama misaajka qofka. e.g. She is always good-humored.
hunch: /hanj/ (n) 1. dareenka qofka (aragtida ama fikradda qofka ee aan sabab ku salays-nayn). e.g. I have a hunch that she will not come. (v) 2. buurid, ama kor u taagid jirka xubin ka mid ah sida garbaha oo kor loo taago.
hunger strike: /hangar-istarayk/ (n) cunto ka-soomis. e.g. The prisoners went on a hunger strike because of the poor conditions in the jail.
hurray: /huurey/hooray; (inter) baga, bagah e.g. You have done it! Hurray!
hurt: /hert/ (v) 1. dhaawicid, wax-yeellayn. (v) 2. xanuujin. e.g. Is that tight shoe hurting you?
hush: /hash/ (n) 1. aamus-naan (v) 2. aamusin. e.g. Hush! Don't wake up the baby.
husky: /haski/ (adj) 1. xabeebsan (xabeeb-leh). (adj) 2. xoog-leh, murqaani ah. (n) 3. nooc eyga ka mid ah.
hussy: /hasi/ (n) faasiqad (qof dumar ah oo anshaxa iyo dhaqan-wanaagga ka leexsan).
hustle: /hasel/ (v) 1. hantaa-takhayn (takhan-tukhayn). e.g. He hustled out of the office. (v) 2. dirqin ama ku-dadajin. e.g. She hustled me into buying a suit.
hut: /hat/ (n) buul (aqal yar oo badanaa qoryo laga dhiso).
hutch: /haj/ (n) takhtad ama qafas hal dhinac shabaq ku-leh.
hydrant: /haydrant/ (n) dhuun dhulka ku rakiban oo biyaha laga jiido kolka dab la daminayo.
hydraulic: /hydrolik/ (adj) ku-shaqeeya cadaadiska biyaha ama dareere kale. e.g. hydraulic brakes
hydraulics: /hydroliks/ (n) barashada biyaha socda ama tamar ka dhalintooda.
hydrofoil: /hydrofoyl/ (n) doon-weyn oo lugo biyaha dhex-gala leh.
hydrophobia: /hydrofobiya/ (n) 1. cudur xoolaha ku dhaca oo waala. (n) 2. cabsi ama biinan ka-qabista biyaha.
hygienic: /hayjenik/ (adj) 1. caafimaad-wanaag keenaya (caafimaad leh). e.g. hygienic conditions. (adj) 2. nadiif (nadaafad-leh.
hymn: /him/ (n) qasiido ama hees diini ah, siiba xamdi-naq eebbe ah.
hypnosis: /hipnowsis/ (n) maddiiddo (waxyaabo qofka lugu sameeyo oo qofka ka dhiga qof wax kasta oo la doonayo la yeelsiiyo).
hypnotize: /hipnatayz/ (v) maddiiddayn. e.g. I was able to hypnotize her into doing things against her own will.
hypodermic: /haypadermik/ (adj) loo adeegsado ama la-xiriira duridda, sida silingaha iwm.
hypothetical: /haypothetikal/ (adj) mala-abaar ah (ka-soo qaad ah ama ku-salaysan aragti-qiyaaseed). e.g. I don't see the point in discussing hypothetical situations; That situation is completely hypthetical.
hysteria: /histeriya/ (n) 1. kac-sanaanta xididada-maskaxda ama shoogsanaanta qofka (n) 2. kac-sanaanta dad-badan, siiba xad-dhaaf ah. e.g. The current hysteria about the shortage of food is getting worse.
I,i: /ay/(pron) 1. aniga. 2. xarafka sagaalaad ee alifbeetada ingiriisiga.
ibis: /aybis/(n) shimbir weyn oo laga helo meelaha biyo galeenka ah iyo cimilada kulul.
ice: /ays/(n) baraf (biyo fadhiya). e.g. Could you give me a cup of water with ice?
iceberg: /aysberg/(n) jabal ama dhadhaab weyn oo baraf ah oo badda ka samaysma (jabal baraf ah).
icicle: /aysikal/(n) barafka usha oo kale ah oo ka soo laalaada saqafka ama darbiyada, xilliga qaboobaha
icing: /aysin/(n) iskujir ka kooban, bur, sonkor iyo ukun oo dusha looga qurxiyo doolshaha am keegga. My mother put icing on his birthday cake.
icy: /aysi/(adj) wax baraf leh ama saa'id u qabow. e.g. Icy roads are dangerous.
ID: /aydhii/ (abbr) aqoonsi (identification, oo la soo gaabiyey). e.g. Before we cash this check we need two pieces of ID.
i'd/: (abbr) 'I had' ama 'I would', 'I should', 'I could' oo la soo gaabiyey. e.g. I'd rather stay home today.
idea: /aydhiya/(n) fikrad ama ra'yi. e.g. Everyone has his own idea. He has very strict ideas about law.
ideal: /aydhiyal/(adj) 1. horyaal ah, aad u fiican ama aad u habboon. e.g. an ideal school 2. wax ku dayasho mudan (tusaale noqon kara) sida qof fikradihiis; fikrad sare. e.g. She is the ideal person for this position.
idealism: /aydhiyalism/(n) fikrad ku salaysan in wax kasta horyaal noqdo ama heer sare. e.g. the idealism of the young generation.
idealist: /aydhiyalist/(n) tusaale sare oo khayaali ah. (falsafadda iwm) ~ fikrad sare oo khayaali ah aaminsan.
idealize: /aydhiyalays/(v) u fakarid ama u sawirasho in wax sida ay yihiin ay ka sarreeyaan.
ideally: /aydhiyali/(adv) sida ugu sarraysa ee wax noqon karaan (sida ugu fiican ama ugu habboon). e.g. Ideally, I would like to be a millionaire.
identical: /aydhentikal/(adj) isku mid (wax meel kasta isaga eg). e.g. They are identical twins.
identification: /aydhentafakayshan/(n) 1. aqoonsi. e.g. The only identification that I have is my passport. 2. qof in la sugo qofkuu yahay. e.g. Identification of the body will take time.
identify: /aydhentafay/(v) aqoonsiin (muujin ama caddayn aqoonsi). e.g. He has no ID to identify himself.
ideology: /aydhiyolaji/(n) ideologies, aydhiyoolojiyad (caqiido, garaad siyaasadeed ama mid bulsho). e.g. Socialist ideology.
idiocy: /aydhiyasi/ idiocies;(n) wax aad u foolxun oo doqonimo ah.
idiom: /idhiyam/(n) sarbeeb (hadal maldahan ama macna kale laga wado).
idiot: /idhiyat/(n) qalbi daciif ama nacas. e.g. He is an idiot.
idle: /aydhal/(adj) idles, idling, idled; 1. shaqa la'aan, dhaqdhaqaaq darro. e.g. He was idle while the machines were down. 2. qof caajiska ah. 3. wax macna darro loo qabto ama aan ujeeddo laga lahayn. e.g. Her idle chatter was annoying.
idol: /aydhol/idols;(n) 1. sanam, (ama ilaah been ah oo gacanta lugu sameeyo) e.g. They made stone idols to worship. 2. qof aad looga daba dhaco ilaa heer laga dambeeyo. e.g. That singer is the idol of many young people.
idyll: /aydhil/idylls, idyllic; (adj) meel farxad iyo baraare loogu nool yahay sida nolosha baadiyaha ee fudud. e.g. It is an idyllic place to live.
if: /if/(conj) 1. haddii (shardi). e.g. I will give you some money if you give me this book. 2. haddaad (ka soo qaad). e.g. You can buy this T.V. if you have enough money. 3. kolkii (haddaadan, haddaysan). e.g. If I'm not here you can smoke.
iffy: /ifi/(adj) aan la hubin, shaki uu ku jiro (wax laba-labo ku jirto). e.g. He was very iffy about what to do.
ignite: /ignayt/ ignites, igniting, ignited; (v) shidid, daarid, hurin. e.g. The wood will not ignite easily because it is wet.
ignition: /ignishan/(n) matoorka meesha uu ka shidmo gaariga, iyo meesha furaha laga geliyaba. e.g. Have you switched the ignition on?
ignominious: /ignaminiyas/ignominiously/(adj) wax ceeb iyo sharaf dhac ah. e.g. He suffered an ignominious defeat in the election,
ignorant: /ignorant/ ignorance; (adj) 1. jaahil (aqoon la') aqoon darro. e.g. He is ignorant because he has never been to school. 2. ogaal la'aan (arrin aadan waxba ka ogeyn). e.g. Some people are ignorant of their rights.
ignore: /ignoor/ignores, ignoring, ignored; (v) iska dhaga tirid, iska maahin, iska-jaahil yeelid (ogaal-diid). e.g. He ignored my question.
ill: /il/ills, illness; (adj) 1. jirran, buka (xanuunsanaya). e.g. She was very ill in the hospital.(n) 2. wax xun oo dhibaato badana waa loo adeegsadaa. e.g. We have to live with the ills of life.
I'll: (abbr) I will ama I shall oo la soo gaabiyey. e.g. I'll go out this weekend.
illegal: /illiigal/illegality; (adj) sharci darro (ka soo horjeeda waxa la ogol yahay). e.g. Drugs are illegal in this country.
illegible: /illejabal/(adj) far ama qoraal aan la akhrin karin. e.g. I found a book with an illegible name on it.
illegitimate: /ilijitamit/illegitimacy;(adj) 1. ilmo aan sharci ku dhalan (garac, wacal) e.g. an illegitimate boy 2. aan sharci ahayn (sharciga khilaafsan). e.g. It was an illegitimate meeting.
illicit: /illisit/illicitly; (adj) sharci darro (sharciga mamnuuc ku ah). e.g. He was arrested for selling illicit drug.
illiterate: /illitarit/ illiteracy;(adj) aan waxna akhrin waxna qorin (ummi). e.g. He is still illiterate.
illness: /ilnis/illnesses;(n) cudur (jirro). e.g. She had a serious illness.
ill-treat: /il-triit/ill-treats, ill-treating, ill-treated; (v) si xun u xannaanayn (daryeelid la'aan). e.g. He ill-treated his animals.
illuminate: /iluumaneyt/illuminates, illuminating, illuminated; (v) 1. iftiimin ama ilaysin. e.g. This candle illuminates the whole house. 2. wax micnahooda aad sii iftiimisid ama sii faahfaahisid.
illusory: /illuusari/(adj) wax run ahaan u muuqda laakiin been ah ama aan jirinba khayaali.
illustrate: /ilastreyt/illustrates, illustrating, illustrated; (v) sharxid ama sifayn leh tusaalooyin iyo sawiro tusmayn. e.g. She illustrated her meaning with well-chosen examples.
illustrious: /illastriyas/illustriously;(adj) qof caan ah (wax gaar ah caan ku noqday)
image: /imij/images;(n) 1. masawir, gaar ahaan muuqaalka aad maskaxda ka sawirato. e.g. He had a very strange image about life in the country.(n) 2. muuqaalka ama sida laga aaminsanyahay qof ama wax. e.g.The prime minister has to improve his image. 3. sanam.
imaginable: /imaajinabal/(adj) la sawiran karo, maskaxda kusoo dhici kara.
imaginary: /imaajaneri/(adj) khayaali (sawir maskaxeed). e.g. an imaginary illness.

imbue: /imbyuu/imbues, imbuing, imbued; (v) ka dherjin ama ka buuxin, fikrad ama dareen gaar ah. e.g. Politicians are imbued with a sense of their own importance.

immaculate: /imaakyalit/immaculately; (adj) nadiif ah, aadna u qurxoon. e.g. Her house is always immaculate.

immediacy: /imiidhiyasi/(n) isla-hadda, dhakhsa ah (arin waqtigeedii la joogo).

immerse: /imers/immerses, immersing, immersed; (v) 1. biyo dhex gelid, quusin (biyo dhex muquufid).(v) 2. wax aad dhex gashid. e.g. He is immersed in his book.

immigrant: /imagranti/immigrants; (n) qofka ka soo haajiray waddankiisii qaxooti, dool. e.g. Somali immigrants are coming to Canada in increasing numbers.

immutable: /immiyuutabal/(adj) aan la bedeli karin. e.g. immutable rules.
impact: /impaakt/(n) 1. raad ku reebid; saamayn (sabab u noqosho).(n) 2. falka ama xooga ka dhasha markii shay uu shay kale ku dhaco.

impartial: /imparshal/impartiality; (adj) eex la'aan ah, si daacad ah u gar qaadaya, dhanna aan raacsanayn. e.g. an impartial judge.

impasse: /impaas/(n) 1. meel aan la dhaafi karin, soo xiran (lama-dhaafaan). (n) 2. arrin dhib badan oo aan meelna loo saari karin.

impeach: /impiij/(v) dambi culus ku soo oogid siiba danbi qaranka laga galo.
impeccable: /impekabal/impeccably; (adj) khalad aan lahayn ama ceeb aan lahayn.
impediment: /impedhamant/ (n) carqalad ama shoobaro hawl curyaamisa. e.g. I can't understand him because he has a speech impediment.
impel: /impel/(v) ku xambaarid; ku dadajin (wax kugu khasba inaad arin ku dhaqaaqdid.
impending: /impendin/(adj) wax degdeg u dhici doona ama (dhakhsa u imaan doona).
imperative: /imperativ/(adj) 1. arin muhiim ah in dhakhso loo qabto (mudnaanta koowaad la siiyo) (adj) 2. lagama maarmaan; aasaasi ah (daruuri) (n) 3. naxwe ahaan (falka amarka bixiya)
imperceptible: /imparseptabal/imperceptibly, imperceptibility; (adj) aad u yar; aan la arki karin (ilma qabato).
imperfect: /imperfikt/imperfectly; (adj) 1. wax aan dhammays-tirnayn (wax aan sax ahayn) (n) 2. naxwe ahaan (fal aan dhammaystirnayn).
imperil: /imperal/imperils, imperiling, imperilled; (v) khatar gelin (la khatar gesho).
impersonate: /impersaneyt/ impersonation;(v) iska yeel-yeelid (qof kale iska dhigdhigid, isku ekaysiin).
impervious: /imperviyas/(adj) aan waxba ka gudbi karin (aan waxba karin). e.g. This material is impervious to water.

implacable: /implaakabal/(adj) aan la dajin karin, (qandhar ah; aan la qancin karin markuu xanaaqo ama wax diido). e.g. He is an implacable opponent.
implant: /impla ant/implants, implanting, implanted; (v) 1. abuurid; (xubin qofka jirkiisa lugu abuuro). 2. fikrad ku abuurid qof maskaxdiis.

implication: /implikeyshan/implications;(n) 1. hadal aan dhab loo muujin, laakiin laga fahmi karo hadal la yiri ama wajiga qofka. (n) 2. dambi ku lug yeelasho: (n) 3. maldahnaan.
implicit: /implisit/implicitly; (adj) 1. maldahan, (hadal dahsoon). e.g. She insulted me implicitly.(adj) 2. si kalsooni leh u rumayn, (aad iyo aad u aaminid). e.g. implicit faith.

imponderable: /impodharabal/ (adj) muhiimadeeda aan la qiyaasi karin (la soo koobi karin).
import: /impoort/(v) 1. soo dejin (alaab dibadda ka soo dejin). (n) 2. shay dibadda laga keenay (eestaro).

impose: /impows/(v) 1. dulsaar (canshuurta ama wixii la mid ah oo qof lugu waajib yeelo). e.g. The government imposed new taxes.(v) 2. ku khasbid ama ku amarsiin qof wax dhib ku ah. e.g. He imposed severe discipline on his children.
imposing: /impowsin/(adj) muuqaal xajmi iyo xoog leh (aad u weyn). e.g. There is an imposing building across the street.
impossible: /imposabal/ (adj) aan suurtagal ahayn (aan dhici karin). e.g. It is impossible to finish this job by tonight.
impostor: /impostar/impostors; (n) qof iska yeela ama iska dhiga qof kale si uu wax u khiyaamo.
impotent: /impotant/(adj) 1. awood darro (hawl qaban waayid) (adj) 2. tabar darro xaga isutegidda ragga iyo dumarka.

impoverish: /impovarish/impoverishes, impoverishing, impoverished;(v) faqri ka dhigid (qof ama dal faqri noqda); fakhrisiin.
impractical: /impraaktikal/(adj) aan la tijaabin karin (wax aan dhab ahaan loo fulin karin).
impregnate: /impregneyt/impregnates, impregnating, impregnated/ (v) 1. shay lugu milo ama la dhex-geliyo shay kale (isku cadaadin)(v) 2. uurayn (rimin)
impress: /impres/impresses, impressing, impressed; (v) 1. wax ama qof aad ka heshid ama la dhacdid. e.g. I was impressed by his manners.(v) 2. arin muhiimadeeda la muujiyo (la caddeeyo).
impression: /impreshan/impressions; (n) 1. sida wax kuugu muuqdaan (qof, shay, iwm), (aragtida ama fikradda aad wax ka qaadatid). e.g. What was your first impression of New York? (n) 2. raad ku reebid (astaan ku reebid). 3. qof kale iska yeel-yeelid.
improbably: /improbabal/(adv) wax aan la filayn inuu dhaco ama rumoobo (aan suurto gal ahayn inuu dhaco).
impromptu: /impromptu/(adj) arin ama ficil loo sameeyo deg-deg iyadoon laga fiirsan oon lugu talagalin.
improper: /impropar/(adj) wax aan habboonayn (aan munaasib ahayn), qalloocan.
improve: /impruuv/ (v) hagaajin (horumarin) (sidii hore ka fiicnayn). e.g. I like to improve my English.
improvise: /improvays/improvises, improvised, improvising; (v) hawl ama ficil aad samaysid adigoon horey usoo-qorshayn ama uga soo fakarin. (fiiro la'aan hawl u qabasho).
impudent: /impyudhant/impudence/ (adj) xishood daran, edeb daran xushmad daran (dabeecad xun). e.g. The impudent child shouted at her mother.
impulse: /impals/(n) rabitaan deg-deg ah (jamasho). e.g. She bought the car on impulse.
impulsive: /impalsiv/ impulsively/ (adj) sal-fudud (qofka asagoon ka fiirsan wax sameeya).
impure: /impyuur/(adj) aan saafi ahayn (wax kale ku qasan yihiin).
in: /in/(prep) 1.naxwe ahaan, meeleeye. 2. gudaha (meel gudeheed tilmaamid). e.g. in the house 3. wakhti dhexdiis. e.g. in July 4. xaalad ama duruuf tilmaamid. e.g. She is in poor health. 5. xiriir ama cilaaqo tilmaamid. e.g. They trust in Allah. 6. saami (ama nisbo tusinaya).e.g. Two in every five are ten. 6. xirfad ama shaqa gaar ah tilmaamaya. e.g. She is in accounting.
inability: /inabiliti/(n) aan awoodin (aan karin). e.g. She does not learn much because of her inability to listen.
inaccessible: /inaksesabal/(adj) wax aan la gaari karin ama ay dhib badan tahay si loo gaaro.
inaccurate: /inaakyurit/(adj) aan sax ahayn (khalad ku jiro); khaldan. e.g I came late because my watch was inaccurate.
inactive: /inaaktiv/(adj) aan dhaqdhaqaaq lahayn (wax iska taagan ama iska fadhiya).
inadequate: /inaadhakwit/inadequately; (adj) aan ku filnayn (aan kaafin karin). e.g. inadequate funds.
inadvertent: /inadhvertant/inadvertently;(adj) kamma' (wax aan kas loo samayn), ulakac aan ahayn (shil ku dhacay).
inane: /ineyn/(adj) wax aan micno ku fadhiyin (macno darro ah).
inanimate: /inaanamit/(adj) aan noolayn (naf-aysan ku jirin), mannoole. e.g. Stone is inanimate.
inapplicable: /inaaplikabal/(adj) aan ku habboonayn (aan ku lug lahayn), aan la xiriirin.
inattentive: /inatentiv/ (adj) aan foojigneyn (aad digtoonayn), maahsan. e.g. He is an inattentive student.
inaugural: /inoogyural/(adj) 1. xaflad furitaan ama khudbo furitaan ah (furitaanka meel ugu horreeya). 2. caleema-saar.

inborn: /inboorn/(adj) waxyaabaha dabiiciga ah ee qofku ku dhasho.
incalculable: /inkaalkyulabal/ (adj) aan caddad lahayn (aan la xisaabi karin).
incapable: /inkeeypabal/(adj) aan la yeeli karin (aan la awoodi karin).

incentive: /insentiv/(n) wixii kugu dhiirri-geliya inaad wax qabato. e.g. Money is being used as an incentive.

inch: /inji/(n) halbeeg lugu cabbiro dhererka, oo le'eg 2.54 sentimitir.

inclination: /inklaneyshan/ (n) rabitaan (danayn) (wixii aad rabtid ama aad niyad u haysid). e.g. I have no inclination to be a doctor.(n) 2. hoo's usoo janjeedhsasho (hoos usoo liicid).

including: /inkluudhin/(prep) lugu daro (uu ku jiro, uu ka mid yahay). e.g. Ten people were dead, including the President.

inclusive: /inkluusiv/(adj) kulli; isku-darka guud (markii lugu darro). e.g. The rent is $500 inclusive of everything.

incoherent: /inkooheerant/(adj) hadal aan naxwe lahayn, hadal aan faseex ahayn (aan la fahmi karin).
incoming: /inkamin/ (adj) imaanaya (soo socda). e.g. the incoming tenants.
incomparable: /inkomparabal/ (adj) aan lays bar-bar dhigi karin (aan laysu qiyaasi karin).
incompatible: /incompaatabal/ (adj) aan wada jiri karin (laba shay ama laba qof oo aan wada joogi karin, kala duwanaanshahooda darteed).
incompetent: /inkombatant/(adj) aan sidii la rabay wax u qaban karin (aan khibrad lahayn). e.g. an incompetent teacher.

inconclusive: /inkonkluusiv/(adj) aan natiijo ka soo bixin. (aan wax go'aan ah laga gaarin). e.g. an inconclusive discussion.
inconsistent: /inkonsistant/(adj) 1. isbed-bedelaya (aan hal si u dhicin); aan joogto ahayn. e.g. Canada's weather is inconsistent. 2. iska hor- imaanaya; is-khilaafaya (kala-hadal).e.g. Those actions are inconsistent with what you said yesterday.
inconvenience: /inkonviinyans/ (n) carqaladayn; (dhibaatayn). e.g. I hope it's not an inconvenience for you to drive me to the bus terminal.
inconvenient: /inkonviinyent/ (adj) keenaya ama abuuraya carqalad, arbush ama dhibaato.
incorporate: /inkoorpareyt/(v) ku darsamay ama la midoobay (wax lugu daray wax kale).
incorporated: /inkoopareytidh/ (adj) shirkad iskeed u madax bannaan sharci ahaan.
incorruptible: /inkorraptabal/ (adj) qof sharciga daacad u ah (aan laaluush iyo sharci darro midna ogolayn).
increase: /inkriis/(v) kordhid; siyaado ama weynaansho. e.g. He wants more money because prices are increasing.
incredible: /inkredhabal/(adj) aan caqli gal ahayn (aan la rumaysan karin).
incubate: /inkyubeyt/(v) cuq (dul fariisadka shimbiruhu ugaxdooda dul fariistaan oo u kululeeyaan tan iyo intay ka dillaacaan).

incumbent: /inkambent/ (adj) waajibaadka qof saaran. e.g. It is incumbent on you to advise your children. 2. qof mas'uul meel ka ah. e.g. the incumbent manager.
incur: /incar/(v) dhib aad gacantaada ku kasbatid (wax aad adigu isu keentid).

incursion: /inkarshan/(n) kusoo duulid iyo qabsasho waddan kale. e.g. Iraqi incursion into Kuwait.
indebted: /indhetid/(adj) 1. u mahad celin. e.g. I am indebted to Ali for his kindness. 2. deyn ku jirid (deyn lagu leeyahay). e.g. His company became indebted to the bank.
indecisive: /indhisaysiv/ (adj)aan go'aan gaari karin (go'aan darro); aan talo u caddayn.
indeed: /indhiidh/(adv) 1. runtii (xaqiiqdii), sidaas oo la hubo. e.g. Did I do the homework? Indeed I did. 2. daran (hadal aad sii xoojineysid). e.g. The weather is very cold indeed.
indefensible: /indhifensabal(adj) wax aad u khaldan oo aan lqo cududaari karin (la difaaci karin).
indefinable: /indhifaaynabal/ (adj) aan la qeexi karin (aan la caddayn karin).
indefinite: /indhefanit/(adj) aan xad lahayn (aan caddayn). e.g. She will be away for an indefinite period of time.
independent: /indhibendanti/ (n) 1. aan cid ama waxba ku tiirsanayn. 2. xor madaxbannaan, isutalis.
index: /indhekis/(n) 1. tusmo alifbeeto ku socota oo buugta ugu dambaysa. 2. hab-xisaabeed lugu miisaamo inta sicirku, ama qiimuhu kor u kacay (ama hoos)~ tusmaynta sicirka. e.g. The cost of living index.
indicate: /indhakeyt/ (v) tusmayn‚ tilmaamid, sida far ku fiiqid ama si kale u muujin.

indict: /indhayt/indictable, indictment; (v) eedayn khalad ama danbi(ku soo oogid si sharci ah).
indifferent: /indhifrant/ indifference; (adj) 1. aan kala jeclayn. 2. aan kale saari-karin (xumaan ama wanaag).
indigenous: /indhijanas/(adj) eeg native/.u dhashay ama asalkiisu ahaa meel ama dal
indignant: /indhignant/indignation; (adj) aad u xanaaqsan (caro aad u daran, dhirfid badanaa caddaalad darro keento).
indiscreet: /indhiskriit/(adj) aan sir iyo taxadar midna lahayn.
indiscriminate: /indhiskrimanit/(adj) aan kala sooc lahayn (aan loo aabba-yeelin). e.g. indiscriminate killing.
indispensable: /indhispensabal/ (adj) aan laga maarmi-karin (daruuri ah), lama huraan ah. e.g. He is an indispensable person for this company.
indisputable: /indhisbiyuutabal/ (adj) aan muran lahayn (aan lasku khilaafi karin, xaqiiq ah).
