indoctrinate: /indhoktraneyt/ (v)barid ama ka dhaadhicin si gaar ah mabda.
indoor: /indhoor/indoors;(adj) aqalka ama dhismaha gudihiisa. e.g. indoor swimming pools.
induce: /indhiyuus/(v) 1. ku boorrin (ku xambaarid in qof wax ku dhaqaaqo), ku qal-qaalin. e.g. I don't know what had induced her to marry a man like that. 2. wax kallifa ama dhaliya inay wax dhacaan (sababa). e.g. Too much food induces sleepiness.
inducement: /indiyuusmant/(n) wax qof ku dhiiri-geliya ama u sahla in uu wax sameeyo. (lacag dhiiri-gelis ah oo kale). e.g. She gave him money as an inducement to leave.
indulge: /indhalj/(v) 1. fasax siin (in qof aad u fasaxdid, wax kasta inuu sameeyo). e.g. She indulges her kids. 2. naftaada oo aad u ogolaatid wax kasta (hawadeeda). e.g. He indulged himself by going out with bad boys.
indulgence: /indhaljans/(n) 1. naftaada oo aad u siideysid wax kasta oo raaxadeeda ah. 2. u fasixid qof kale wixii naftiisu rabto.
industry: /indhastri/industries; (n) 1. warshad. e.g. Japanese industries are growing very fast. 2. shaqo gaar ah (wax soosaar ama hawl gaar ah).e.g. the hospitality industry. 3. shaqo-badni.
ineffective: /inafektiv/(adj) aan waxba tari karin (waxtar aan lahayn).
inefficient: /inafishant/(adj) aan sidii la rabay wax u tari karin.
ineligible: /inelajabal/(adj) aan sharuudihii la rabay buuxin karin (aan xaq u lahayn). e.g. He is ineligible for unemployment insurance benefits.
inert: /inerti/(adj) 1. aan awood dhaqdhaqaaq lahayn (aan nuuxsanayn). 2. aan waxba la falgali karin (kimikada).
inertia: /inersha/(n) xaalad ay walax ku sugan tahay nagaansho ama dhaqaaq ilaa quwad kale ay wax ka badasho (sida marka baabuurka farriinka deg-deg loo qabto quwadda horay kuu tuurta).
inescapable: /ineskeypabal/(adj) aan layska deyn karin (aan laga dhuuman karin), aan laga fursan karin. e.g.inescapable expenses.
inestimable: /inestamabal/(adj) aan la qiyaasi karin (qaali ah). e.g. necklace of inestimable value.
inevitable: /inevatabal/(adj) 1. sina aan loo joojin karin (aan la hor istaagi karin). e.g. This war was inevitable because they could not agree. 2. mar kasta dhaca, jira, ama jooga.
inexcusable: /inekiskyusabal/(adj) aan loo cududaari karin (fal aad u xun oo aan qiil loo sameyn karin).
inexhaustible: /inigsoostabal/ (adj) wax aan waligiis dhammaanayn (aad u tiro badan); caddad badan.
inexplicable: /inikisplikabal/ (adj) aan laga war bixin karin (aan la fasiri karin).
infant: /infanti/(n) cunugu markuu dhasho ilaa intuu aad u yar yahay ~ sabi.
infect: /infekt/(v) 1. qaadid ama qaadsiin (cudur ku dhicid ama ku daarasho). e.g. He is infected with AIDS. 2. saamayn ama gaarid. e.g. Violence is infecting everyone.
infer: /infer/(v) ka fahmid; kala dhexbixid (macnaha maldahan oo aad ka fahantid hadal aad maqashay ama meel ku qoran).
inferior: /infiiriyar/inferiors; (adj) 1. heer hoose ah (hooseeya). 2. qof darajo hoose leh xaga shaqada. e.g. His work is inferior compared with others.
infernal: /infernal/(adj) aad u xun (dab oo kale looga gubanayo ama looga xanaaqayo). e.g. Could you stop that infernal noise?
inferno: /inferno/(n) dab aad u holcaya oo kahatar ah (naar).
infertile: /infertal/(adj) 1. dhul aan carro san ahayn (dhul aan beeridda ku fiicnayn). 2. ma-dhalaysnimo (aan dhali karin, aan waxba bacramin karin).
infidelity: /infachelati/ (n) khayaamo iyo daacad darro labada qof oo isqabta midkood (gaar ahaan qofka suuqa ka qaraabta ama xiriir kale yeesha). e.g. She finally discovered her husband's infidelity.
infinity: /infinati/(n) aan bar dhammaad lahayn (aan xad lahayn).
inflammable: /infleemabal/(adj) guban og (si sahal ah dabka u qabsan og).
inflammatory: /inflaamatori/ (adj) khudbo ama hadal qiiro leh oo dadka shucuurtooda kiciya.
inflatable: /infleytabal/(adj) la buufin karo (aariyo ama neef laga buuxin karo).
inflation: /infleyshan/(n) sicir barar (maciishadda oo kor u kacda).
inflexible: /infleksabal/(adj) aan la qalloocin karin; aan la bed-beddeli karin.
influence: /influwans/(v) 1. ku qalqaalin ama jecleysiin qof kale waxaad adigu rabto (duufsasho). e.g. What influenced you to do this? (n) 2. raad kuyeel asho (ku lug lahaansho ama sabab u noqosho wax la sameeyey). e.g. I didn't want her to influence me in my choice.
influential: /influwenshal/ (adj) qalqaalo badan (awood lugu raaco oo dad lagu kasbado leh). e.g. He is a powerful and influential politician.
inform: /infoorm/(v) war-gelin; war-siin (wax u sheegid). e.g. I informed him about everything.
informal: /infoormal/(adj) aan rasmi ahayn (wax iska caadi ah oo sharci iyo nidaam adag midna aan lugu dabbakhin). e.g. an informal meeting.
informative: /infoormativ/(adj) war badan haya (akhbaar muhiim ah haya).
ingredient: /ingridhiyant/ (n) waxyaabaha shay ama cunto ka samaysan tahay (ka-koobantahay).
inhabit: /inhaabit/ (v) ku noolaan (degid). e.g. Sahara dessert is not inhabited.
initial: /inishal/(n) 1. xarafka magac ka bilowdo. e.g. Ali's first initial is A. (adj) 2. bilowga (hawl ama arrin biloowgeed). e.g. The initial meetings were the base of the last agreement.
initiate: /inishiyeyt/(v) 1. bilaabid. e.g. We have to initiate direct talks with the leaders. 2. gelid ama ku biirid. e.g. He was initiated into the secret society.
inject: /injekt/(v) 1. durid (mudud) (irbad ku durid). e.g. He was injected with new drugs. 2. ku siyaadin (ku darid). e.g. A lot of money was injected into health care.
injustice: /injastis/(n) caddaalad darro (caddaalad, la' aan). e.g. Social injustice is a problem in some countries.
inland: /inlandh/(adj) meesha dalka gudihiisa ah oo ka fog xeebaha iyo xudduudaha.
inlet: /inlet/(n) 1.gacan biya ah, kannaal ama killi. 2. meel wax soo galaan (hawo, baasiin iwm).
inmate: /inmeyt/(n) dadka meel ku xereysan (isbitaal ama xabsi oo kale).
inn: /in/(n) huteel yar oo cunto iyo jiifba leh (albeergo).
innocent: /inasant/(adj) 1. aan dambi lahayn. 2. sirmaqabe daacad ah.
innuendo: /inyuwendo/(n) maldahan, dahsoon (hadal edeb darro ah oo si dadban loo yiraahdo).
input: /input/(n) la galiyo (wax la geliyo shay sida kombiyuutarka iyo qaybaha mashiinka).
inquest: /inkuwest/(n) baaritaan lugu sameeyo meydka si loo ogaado qofku sababtuu u dhintay.
insatiable: /inseyshabal/(adj) aan la dharjin karin (aad u cir-weyn).
insecure: /insikyuur/(adj) 1. cabsi qaba (aan kalsooni qabin). 2. aan nabad qabin (aan badbaadsanayn).
inseparable: /inseparabal/(adj) laba wax oo aad isugu dhow oo aan la kala saari karin (aan kala ahaan karin.
insert: /insert/(v) gelin (dhex-gelin). e.g. She inserted the key in the lock and opened the door.
inshore: /inshoor/(adj) badda xeebta u dhow (badda inta xeebta xigta).
inside: /insaydh/(prep) 1. gudaha. e.g. Don't let him inside.(adj) 2. sir ama arin xogteed. e.g. I'll give you inside information about this matter. 3. inside out ~ dhanka kale u rogan (geddisan). e.g. He put his shirt on inside out.
insider: /insaydhar/(n) qof xog-ogaal ah (arin sirteed og oo ku dhex jira).
insight: /insayt/(n) fahanka ama aragtida (sidaad arin u fahantid).
insist: /insist/(v) ku adkaysi (hadal ama wax aad ku adkeysatid samayntooda). e.g. He insisted that he was right.
insoluble: /insolyabal/(adj) 1. aan la xallin karin (aan xal lahayn) 2. aan milmayn (aan qasmayn).
insolvent: /insolvant/(adj) musallif (aan deyntii lugu lahaa iska bixin karin).
insomnia: /insomniya/(n) qof hurdo la'aan qaba (aan seexan karin).
inspiration: /inspareyshan/(n) 1. niyad-gelin ama dhiirrigelin (wax kugu dhaliya inaad wax hindistid ama samaysid). (n) 2. ra'yi fiican helid (fikrad fiican oo degdeg kuugu soo dhacda). e.g. Some artists get their inspiration from nature.
inspire: /inispayar/(v) 1. ku boorrin; geesinimo gelin (dhiirrin). 2. waxa qof ku dhiirriya inuu wax qoro ama farshaxan sameeyo.
inspired: /inispayardh/(adj) 1. aad xariif u ah (aad u maskax fiican). e.g. He was an inspired artist. 2. qiyaas aad sax u ah (aad mooddid in loo waxyooday). e.g.It was just an inspired guess.
install: /inistool/(v) 1. ku rakibid (shay meel lugu rakibo si loo isticmaalo). e.g. They are installing a washing-machine in the kitchen.2. jago u dhiibid ama u magacaabid (si rasmi ah).
instalment: /inistoolmanti/(n) 1. lacag qayb-qayb loo bixiyo (deyn xoogaa-xoogaa u bixin). e.g. she paid $100 in five monthly instalments. 2. cutub-cutub (buug ama musalsal qayb-qab loo kala qaado.e.g.This is the first instalment of the film.
instance: /inistans/(n) 1. tusaale ahaan e.g. He is a bad boy. For instance, he doesn't respect his father. 2. xaqiiqa ahaan (dhab ahaan).
instant: /inistant/(adj) 1. isla-markiiba (isla-mar qura dhaca ama la sameeyo). e.g. She gave an instant response to my question.
instantly: /inistantly/(adv) dhakhsa leh (isla-markaasba); durbaba. e.g. She was killed instantly.
instead: /inistedh/(adv) beddelkii ay saas ahaan lahayd (halkay saas ka ahaan lahayd), beddel keedii. e.g. He never studies instead, he plays football all day.
instep: /inistep/(n) cagta inta sare ee u dhaxaysa canqowga iyo faraha.
instigate: /inistageyt/(v) bilaabid ama abuurid in wax dhacaan (badanaa dhibaato horseedid).
instinct: /inistinkt/ (n) 1. dareenka qofka, (dareenka qofka wax ku xambaara asagoon ka fakarin). 2. sida qof wax ugu muuqdaan, oo ku salaysan dareenka qofka. e.g Trust your instincts and do whatever you think is right.
instinctive: /inistinktiv/ (adj) wax aad maskaxdaada ka maagto (aad iska samaysay adigoon ka fakarin).
institute: /inistatyuut/ (n) 1. machad ama urur bulsho oo ujeeddo gaar ah leh (badanaa waxbarasho ama baaris cilmiyeed). e.g. British Columbia Institute of Technology (v) 2. bilaabid ama hirgelin wax cusub.
institution: /inistatyuushan/ (n) dhismo weyn oo ah (hay'ad, machad, shirkad, isbitaal, jaamacad iwm). e.g. educational institutions, the institution of marriage, the institution of a new law.
instruct: /inistrakt/(v) 1. wax-barid (wax u sheegid). e.g. My father instructs people how to drive cars.(v) 2. amar siin (farid).e.g. I have been instructed to stay home.
instruction: /inistrakshan/(n) 1. wax barasho (tababar). e.g. Please follow my instructions!(n) 2. tilmaan-bixin (tusid ama u sheegid sidii wax loo isticmaali lahaa). e.g. Read the instructions before you take the medicine.
instructor: /inistraktar/ (n) macallin; bare gaar ahaan macallinka xirfadda, tababare.
insubstantial: /insabstaanshal/ (adj) 1. aan badnayn, adkayn ama daciif ah (aan lugu qanci karin) 2. aan wax weyn ahayn (aan micno lahayn). e.g. Some factories produce insubstantial products.
insufficient: /insafishant/(adj) aan ku filnayn (aan kaafi ahayn); naaqis ah. e.g. She gave him insufficient money.
insular: /insyular/(adj) qof fikrad gaaban (aragti gaaban). fikradiisu xadidan tahay.
insulate: /insiyuleyt/(v) 1. dahaar saarid (ka xijaabid waxyaabaha dabka gudbiya sida korontada oo kale). 2. difaacid; ilaalin (qof ama dad laga ilaaliyo wixii dhibaato u ah.)
insulation: /insyuleyshan/ (n) dahaarid ama xijaabid, ka ilaalin, u diidid inay gudbaan (sida kulka, qabowga, korontada).
insult: /insalt/(v) caytin (qof aad af-lagaadeysid), af-lagaaddo. e.g. You have insulted me by calling me a pig.
insuperable: /insuparabal/(adj) caqabad (wax aan la dhaafi-karin). e.g. insuperable difficulties.
insurance: /inshuurans/(n) caymis (lacagta qofku bixiyo intaan dhib gaarin si markii dhib gaaro lacag loo siiyo). e.g. life insurance.
insure: /inshuur/(v) caymin (caymis gelin). e.g. Have you insured your car yet?
insurgent: /inserjanti/(n) mucaarad, fallaago (dadka ka soo hor-jeeda dowladda waddankooda ee la dagaala). e.g. The insurgent crowd damaged the embassy.
insurmountable: /insarmoontabal/ (adj) aan la xallin karin (aad u adag).
insurrection: /insarrekshan/(n) kicid ama gadoodid (dadka dawladdooda ku kaca oo ka soo hor-jeensada).
intact: /intaakt/(adj) dhawrsan (sidiisii ah, oo aan la waxyeellayn ama aan wax la gaarsiin).
intake: /inteyk/(n) 1. dalool ama meel furan oo ay ka gudbaan waxyaabaha dareeraha ah. e.g. a large intake of water(n) 2. qaadasho, ogolaansho sida iskuul, arday wada aqbala (hal teeram oo kale). e.g. a school's intake of students.
integral: /intagral/(adj) lagama maarmaan ah (aasaasi u ah in waxaasi kaamil noqdaan). e.g. This is an integral part of the story.
integrate: /intagreyt/integration;(adj) 1. isku-darid; midayn (isu keenid ama isku dhajin). e.g. The two regional bus systems were integrated. 2. is-dhexgalid (laba qolo ama laba ummadood oo is-dhexgala xaga dhaqanka, diinta, afka iwm). e.g. They have been in this country for ten years but have never really integrated.
integrity: /integrati/(n) 1. sharaf (qof mudnaan leh). e.g. My mother was a woman of the highest integrity. 2. midnimo (hal ahaansho). e.g. We have to defend our integrity as a nation.
intelligence: /intelajans/(n) 1. maskax fiican leh, caqli badnaan. e.g. She is a person of average intelligence. 2. sirta dowlad ka soo aruuriso cadawgeeda. e.g. American intelligence services.
intelligent: /intelajant/(adj) caqli badan (xariif ah), maskax badan. e.g. She is an intelligent student.
intelligible: /intelajabal/(adj) si dhib yar loo fahmi karo (si fudud loo garan karo).
intend: /intendh/(v) ugu tala gelid, qorshayn (niyad ku hayn). e.g. She intended to catch the early bus, but she didn't get up on time.
intense: /intens/Intensely; (adj) 1. aad u daran (xoog badan). e.g. intense cold 2. qofka ad-adag oo wax kasta dantiisa ka raaca (diritada ah).
intensify: /intensifay/ intensified, intensifying intensifies; (v) xoojin (xoog-saarid). e.g. The police intensified their search for the suspect.
intensive: /intensiv/intensively; (adj) xoog-saarid deg-deg ah (hawl si xoog ah, taxadar leh oo dhakhso ah loo qabto).
intensive care: /(adj) daawayn khaas ah (qofka markii xaalkiisu xun yahay sida loo daaweeyo).
intent: /intent/ (n) ulajeeddo qasad, niyo. e.g. She entered the house with the intent to steal.
intention: /intenshan/(n) niyeysi, wax aad niyeysatay inaad samayso, ujeeddo.
intercede: /intarsiidh/intercession;(v) u shafeecid (u doodid si qof u badbaado).
intercept: /intarsept/(v)joojin (wax ama qof dhexda lugu qabto intuusan meeshiisii gaarin). e.g. The drugs were intercepted at the border.
interchangeable: /intarjeynjabal/ (adj) laysku beddelan karo (lays weydaarsan karo) (laba shay, laba eray iwm).
intercontinental: /intarkontanental/ (adj) qaaradaha oo dhan ka jira (laga isticmaalo). e.g. intercontinental flight.
interest: /intarast/(v) 1. ahmiyad-siin; xiisayn. e.g. Can I interest you in some dessert? (n) 2. maslaxo, dan (faa'iido). e.g. I have an interest in the army. (n) 3. dulsaar (ribo).
interfere: /interfir/(v) faragelin (hawl aad faraha la gashid ayadoon luguu amrin). e.g. Stop interfering in my work!
interference: /intarfirans/ (n) dhabqin am faraha la gelid (hawl socota).
interim: /intarim/(adj) ku meel gaar ah (aan joogto ahayn). e.g. interim president.
interior: /intiriyar/ (n) gudaha (daakhilka). e.g. We decorated the interior of our house.
interloper: /intarlopar/(n) qofka iska soo gala meel aan looga baahnayn.
interlude: /intarluudh/(n) waqtiga bareegga la qaato (biririf). e.g. After this interlude, the dancing will continue.
intermarriage: /intarmaarij/ (n) kala guursasho (laba shicib ama laba qolo oo kala-guursada); isdhexgal xagga guurka.
intermingle: /intarmingal/ (v) is-dhexgelid (isku-dhex qasmid). e.g. The police intermingled with the protestors.
internal: /internal/(adj) 1. gudaha ah (dhexdiisa). e.g. Is there any internal damage? 2. waddan gudihiis. e.g. Internal affairs of a country.
internment: /internmant/(n) xirid, xabsi gelin (badanaa siyaasad u xirid).
interpret: /interprit/(v) 1. u turjumid; ka turjumid (laba luuqadood kala turjumid). e.g. Sabaax had to interpret for me. 2. u fasirasho (ka fasirasho). e.g. He interpreted my silence as a refusal.
interpreter: /interpritar/ (n) turjume (turjumaan). e.g. She spoke to me through an interpreter.
interrogate: /interrageyt/ (v) imtixaanid (su'aalo badan weyddiin). e.g. She has been interrogated by the police.
interrogative: /interrogativ/ (adj) leh qaab su'aaleed (hab su'aaleed la xiriira). e.g. an interrogative sentence.
interrupt: /intarrapt/(v) 1. ka dhex gelid, kalagoyn (ka khash- khashid qof hadlaya). e.g. She interrupted the speaker. 2. hawl socotay kala joojin (fadqalalayn).
interruption: /intarrapshan/(n) kala go', hakad gelid (hawl socotay oo in yar joogsata).
interval: /intarval/(n) waqti u dhexeeya laba dhacdo (bareeg; biririf).
intervene: /intarviin/(v) 1. soo dhex-gelid si loo dhex-dhexaadiyo (dad is haysta). e.g. They were fighting until their father intervened. 2. dhabqin (hakin) (hadal ama hawl socotay). e.g. I'll come tomorrow if something doesn't intervene.
interview: /intarviyuu/(n) kulan waraysi ah (is-arag qof lugu waraysto). e.g. I had two job interviews yesterday.
intimate: /intameyt/ (adj) 1. saaxiibtinimo nafta laysu huro (nin iyo naag aan waxba isu diidin oo kale). e.g. She had been intimate with a lot of men. 2. qofka arimihiisa khaaska ah (shakhsiga ah). e.g. I told him the most intimate details of my personal life. 3. faahfaahin lugu ogaaday cilmi baaris. e.g. Ask someone with an intimate knowledge of the city.
introduce: /intradhiyuus/(v) 1. is-barid (laba qof). e.g. He introduced Ali to Fatima. 2. soo ban-dhigid. e.g. He introduced a new bill.
introduction: /intradhakshan/(n) 1. bandhig (soo ban dhigid) 2. horudhac ~ arar, gogoldhig. 3. isbaritaan (laba qof).
introductory: /intradhaktari/ (adj) hordhac (qaybta u horraysa mawduuc ama maaddo). e.g introductory courses.
introvert: /intravert/introverts, introverted; (n) qofka afka-gaaban, xishoodka badan ee kali socodka ah.
intrude: /intruudh/(v) qasid ama dhabqin (meel aan lagaaga baahnayn).
intruder: /intruudhar/(n) qofka dhabqiya ama iska soo gala meel aan looga yeerin (loo ogolayn).
inundate: /inandheyt/(v) fatahma (wax tiro badan oo hal mar meel kusoo wada dhaca), faruurma. e.g. I have been inundated with applications.
invade: /inveydh/(v) 1. gelid dal si loo qabsado (xoog ku qabsasho milateri). e.g. Kuwait was invaded by Iraq. 2. tiro badan meel ku gelid.e.g. Reporters invaded the city.
invalid: /invaalidh/(adj) aan la isticmaali karin, aan soconayn, aan shaqaynayn (aan qiimo lahayn). e.g.invalid passports.
invalidate: /invaaladheyt/ wax aan la isticmaali karin ka dhigid (wax aan soconayn ka dhigid), burin.
invariable: /inveriyabal/(adj) ma-doorsoome (aan is beddelin, markasta hal si ah).
invasion: /inveyshan/(n) xoog milatari waddan ku qabsasho. e.g. Iraq's invasion of Kuwait.
invent: /invent/invention; (v) 1. soo saarid wax cusub (ikhtiraacid). e.g. the man who invented computers. 2. allifid (sheeko iwm).
inventory: /inventari/(n) liiska ama tirada alaab meel taal (ama bakhaar ku jirta).
inverse: /invers/(adj) 1. dhanka kale u rogan (la kala qalibo). 2. saami, lid ah (caksi ah) (laba tiro oo mid markuu bato kan kale yaraado).
inverted comma: /(n) faasilooyin ama hakadyo qoraalada geesaha looga xiro sida /” “/.
invest: /invest/(v) maalgelin (la maal-geliyo). e.g. She had invested a lot of time and money in this project.
investigate: /investageyt/(v) baarid (baaritaan samayn si runta loo gaaro). e.g. This case was investigated by the police.
invincible: /invinsabal/(adj) aan la jabin karin (ciidan ama koox aan laga adkaan karin).
invisible: /invisabal/(adj) aan la arki karin (aan ishu qaban karin).
invite: /invayt/(v) casuumid (marti-qaad u fidin). e.g. He invited me to the party.
inviting: /invaytin/(adj) kusoo jiidanaya (soo jiidasho leh), ku niyad gelinaya.
invoice: /invoys/(n) qaansheeg lugu xuso tirada iyo qiimaha alaabta ~ biil. e.g. Our company sent him an invoice a month ago.
invoke: /invowk/(v) 1. awood sare tuugid (ilaah baryid). 2. baryid (caawimaad weydiisasho). e.g. He invoked her help.
involuntary: /involanteri/involuntarily; (adj) wax aadan kas u samayn. (aadan ikhyaar kaaga u samayn, laakiin adoon is ogeyn kaa dhacay). e.g. She smiled involuntarily.
involve: /involv/involved;(v) 1. dhex-gelin ku-darid (ku-xirid). e.g. Don't involve other boys in your mistakes. 2. ka mid ah ama ku lug-leh (ku jira). e.g. My job involves a lot of travelling. 3. ka qayb-qaato (ku dhex-jira). e.g. He is involved in community affairs. 4. dhib badan (jumlo ama wax aan la fahmi karin). e.g. What an involved sentence.
iodine: /ayadin/(n) saliid-naar (daawo loo isticmaalo nabarada iyo masawirda caddayntooda).
iota: /ayota/(n) aad iyo aad wax u yar. e.g. I don't think there is an iota of truth in that.
IOU: /ay-ow-yuu/(n) 'I owe you' oo la soo gaabiyey 'waxaad igu leedahay'. (qofka deynta lugu leeyahay ayaa qora). e.g. I can't pay you now. Can I write you an IOU for $50?
IQ: /ay-kiyuu/(n) intelligence quotient' oo lasoo gaabiyey (imtixaan lugu ogaado qofka caqligiisa). e.g. She had an IQ of 50.
irk: /erk/ (v) dhibid (ka xanaajin) e.g. Such behaviour clearly irked Bashiir.
irksome: /erksam/(adj) wax dhibaato iyo xanaaq abuuraya. e.g. It seems to me that his methods are irksome.
iron: /ayran/(n) 1. xadiid (birta xadiidka ah). e.g. It is made from iron. 2. macdan cuntada qaarkeed ku jirta. 3. kaawiyad (feero). e.g. She can't iron my shirt. 4. qof ad-adag (xadiid lugu matalay).
irony: /ayrani/(n) kajan (hadal kajan iyo ciyaar ah), jeesjees. e.g. He said with irony, 'You are very beautiful.'
irrational: /irraashanal/ (adj) tasarufaad ama fal aan macquul ahayn (aan maskax ku dhisnayn).
irreconcilable: /irrekansaylabal/ (adj) aad u kala fog, wax aan marna lugu heshiin karin (aan laysku keeni karin).
irreducible: /irridhiyuusabal/ (adj) aan la dhimi karin (aan la yarayn karin).
irregular: /irregular/(adj) 1. aan caadi ahayn. 2. lid ku ah sharciga. 3. naxwe ahaan (ficilka qoraarlkiisu isbeddalo).
irrelevant: /irrelavant/(adj) hadal aan mawduuca laga hadlayo khusayn (khaarij mawduuc).
irreligious: /irrilijas/(adj) aan diin haysan (aan qof diimeed ahayn).
irreparable: /irreperabal/(adj) aan la hagaajin karin (aan dib loo samayn karin).
irreplaceable: /irripleysabal/ (adj) wax aan baddalkiisa la heli karin (wax u dhigma aysan jirin).
irrespective of: /irrispektiv of/ (prep) aan tixgelin la siin (aan ahmiyad la siin).
irrevocable: /irrevakabal/(adj) aan la beddeli karin. e.g. an irrevocable decision.
irritable: /irratabal/ (adj) qofka wax kasta ka xanaaqa (car i taabo, xanaaqa fudud).
irritant: /irratant/(adj) 1. waxa qof ka caraysiiya (xanaajiya). 2. wax jirka cun-cun u keena.
irritate: /irrateyt/(v) 1. ka xanaajin (ka caraysiin). 2. cun-cun abuurid (wax cun-cun kuu keena).
isolate: /aysaleyt/(v) gooni u takooran (meel cidla' ah kali ku ah).
isolated: /aysaleytidh/(adj) 1. geeri go'an ah 2. cidla' ah (kali ah).
issue: /ishyuu/(n) 1. soo bixid joornaal, iwm. (daabacaad la soo saaro), soo saarid. e.g. I bought the newspaper the day after its issue.(n) 2. mawduuc ama qodob muhiim ah. e.g. Don't make it a big issue.(v) 3. la siiyo (qof si sharci ah wax loogu sameeyo). e.g. I'll issue a passport for you.
isthmus: /ismas/(n) meel yar oo isku xirta laba dhul oo weyn.
it: /it/(pron) magac u yaalka mannoolaha iyo xayawaanka.
italics: /itaaliks/(n) xarfo ku qoran far yar-yar oo jiifta.
itch: /ij/(n) 1. cun-cun jirka ah (xoq-xoq rabid). e.g. An itch must be scratched. 2. wax aad deg-deg u rabtid inaad samayso (aadan dhowri karin). e.g. The students were itching for the lesson to end.
itinerant: /aytinarant/(adj) hadba meel u safra (had iyo jeer safra)
itinerary: /aytinareri/(n) faahfaahin safar ku saabsan (meelaha la booqan doono, dariiqa la mari doono, waqtiga iwm).
ivy: /ayvi/(n) geed ka dhex baxa darbiyada iyo geedaha kale oo caleemo dhalaalaya leh (saar)
jab: /jaab/(v) 1. ku mudid (juq ku siin) (n) 2. irbad ku durid (durmo) e.g. She jabbed the knife into the fruit.
jabber: /jaabar/(v) hadal daldalid (si dhakhso ah oo aan la fahmi karin u hadlid). e.g. They were jabbering at each other in French.
jack: /jaak/(n) 1. giriig (qalab alaabta culculus lugu qaado siiba baabuurta) 2. warqadaha turubka midda ninku ku sawiran yahay (qulaan) 3. shakhsi (qof).
jacket: /jaakit/(n) 1. jaakeet (koor shaatiga laga dul gashado). e.g. I have two sports jackets. 2. diirka baradhada (qubka bataatada).
jack-knife: /jaak-nayf/(n) 1. mindida galka leh (00 laysku laabo).(v) 2. kala jiirayn (baabuur dhakso u kala wareega waddada dhexdeeda).
jack pot: /jaackpot/(n) lacagta ugu badan ee gof ku guuleysto (khamaar ama bakhtiyaa-nasiib).
jack up: /jaak ap/(v) giriig ku dallicid (giriig ku qaadid). e.g. Could you jack up the car please?
jade: /jeydh/(adj) dhagax cagaaran oo qaali ah (laga sameeyo almaasta iwm).
jagged: /jaagidh/(adj) shay girgirro leh (aan lahayn qar siman ama sulub ah).
jaguar: /jaagwar/(n) bahal haramcadka u eg oo laga helo Ameerika oo dheereeya.
jail: /jeyl.(n) xabsi. e.g. He spent three years in jail.
jam: /jaam/(n) 1. malmalaado (rootiga la marsado) 2. ku ciriirin (meel aad u buuxda xoog ku gelin) e.g. Nothing else can be jammed into this bag. 3. si xoog ah oo dhakhsa ah u riixid. (dhakhsa u cadaadin). e.g. I had to stop quickly, so I jammed on the brakes. 4. meel saxmad ah oo aad loo buuxo. e.g. Traffic jam.
jamboree: /jaambarii/(n) xaflad weyn oo dad badan isugu yimaadeen.
jam packed: /(adj) buux dhaaftay (meel buuxsantay oo aan boos ka bannaanayn).
jangle: /jaangal/(v) dhawaq qalalaw leh (dhawaaq sida laba bir oo isku dhacaya samayn).
jar: /jar/(n) 1. dhalo (qullada malmalaadada laga isticmaalo oo kale) e.g jar of jam. 2. wax jiriirica leh (kaa nixiya).
jargon: /jargan/(n) hadal xirfad ama cilmi gaar ah loo isticmaalo (erey-bixin cilmiyeed). e.g. They use a lot of professional jargon.
javelin: /jaavalin/(n) murjis (waran af dhuuban oo isboortiga lugu ciyaaro).
jay walk: /jeywook/(v) si aan taxadar lahayn waddo u goyn.
jazz: /jaas/(n) muusigga jaaska (muusig hal mar laysla garaaco qof kasta iskiis); qoobka ciyaar.
jazzy: /jaasi/(adj) 1. jaas oo kale ah 2. soo jiidasho leh oo midabo badan lugu qurxiyey.
jeer: /jiir/(v) 1. qosol jees-jees ah 2. qosol dheer-dheer (si xoog ah u qoslid).
jelly: /jeli/(n) 1. macmacaan aad u jiljilicsan 2. shay kasta oo u dhexeeya dareere iyo adke.
jerk: /jerk/(v) 1. xoog usoo siibid (dhakhso usoo bixin) 2. dhakhso u bixid (u dhaqaaqid).
jet: /jet/(n) 1. burqad (biyo ama dareere dhuun yar xoog uga soo butaacaya) e.g He directed a jet stream of water into the air.2. diyaarad yar.
jewellery: /juulari/ (n) majoowharaad (alaab qaali ah oo dumarku isku qurxiyo sida, silsiladda, dhegaha, burshaleetada iwm).
jilt: /jilt/ (v) iska-dirid, (iska-cayrin, siiba laba qof oo jacayl ka dhaxeeyey) eg. After being her boyfriend for five years, he suddenly jilted her.
job lot: /jab lot/(n) alaab kala nooc ah oo laysku gado.
jockey: /joki/(n) 1. qofka fardaha ku tartama 2. gofka jago ama shaqo u qabta si xirfad badni ah.
jog: /jog/(v) 1. hantaatiqin (riixid ama jagayn) 2. aayar u dhaqaaqid.
join: /jooyn/(v) 1. isku xirid (ku dhejin) 2. ku darsamid (ka mid noqosho).
joint: /jooynt/(n) 1. guntin (meesha wax isaga xirmaan ama iska-galaan). 2. kalagoys (meesha xubnaha jirku iska galaan) 3. wax dad ka dhexeeya (wadajir).
joker: /jookar/(n) 1. qofka maadeeya ama kaftama 2. warqada turubka ee meel kasta geli karta (ciyaarta).
jot: /jot/jot down;(n) 1. wax aad u yar (in yar).(v) 2. dhakhso wax u qorid (qoraal boobta ah).
journal: /joornal/(n) wargeys (joornaal urur ama dad gaar ah soo saaraan).
journalist: /joornalist/(n) qofka weriyaha ah ama wargeysyada qora (suxufi).
jubilant: /jubalant/(adj) farxad ka muugato (aad u faraxsan); rayrayn leh) e.g. A jubilant man.
judgment: /jajmant/ (n) 1. go'aan maxkamadeed (xukun soo saarid) 2. guddoomin (ka talin) (ka gar-niqid).
judgement day: /jajmant dhey/ day of judgement; (n) maalinta lays xukumayo (maalinta aakhiro).
judiciary: /judhishiyeri/(n) nidaamka sharciga iyo garsooridda ee waddan.
jug: /jag/(n) garaafo (weel dheg leh oo wax lugu shubto).
jumbo: /jambo/(adj) ka weyn waxyaabaha kale oo la nooca ah.
junior: /junyar/(n) 1. yaraan (da' yari)(adj) 2. darajo hoose (heer biloow ah).
juror: /jurar/(n) qof loo doortay inuu ka mid noqdo garsoorayaal dadweyne (xeer-beege).
jury: /juuri/(n) dad loo dhaarshay inay noqdaan garsoore dadweyne (xeerbeeg).
just: /jast/(adj) 1. caaddil, caddaalad (adv) 2. sidaas laftigeeda eg. That is just my idea. 3. isla markaas (isla-haddeer) e.g. I'm going just now? 4. in yar (kaliya). e.g. Just a minute. 5. aan ka badnayn.e.g. Just what do you want to tell me?
justify: /jastafay/(v) sabab sheegid; caddayn sabab fiican u yeelid.
jute: /juut/(n) mayrax laga sameeyo xargo iyo shiraacyo waaweyn.
K,k: /key/ xarafka kow iyo tobnaad ee alifbeetada ingiriisiga.
kale: /keyl/(n) nooc kaabajk'a ka mid ah (khudrad caleemeheeda la karsado).
kaleidoscope: /kalaydhaskowb/(n) 1. tuubbo markii la wareejiyo midabbo indha sarcaad ah leh. 2. wax kasta oo markii la wareejiyo midabbo sameeya.
kangaroo: / kaangaruu/(n) kira ngewe (xayawaan ustareeliya ku nool oo ku booda lugaha dambe, dhaddiguna carruurta caloosha ku qaato).
karate: /karatii/(n) karateega (dagaalka gacmaha, suxulada iyo lugaha lugu dagaalo)
kebab: /kabab/(n) hilib qori lugu mudo oo lugu dubo, iyo qudaar (cunto Carbeed).
keel: /kiil/on an even keel;(n) 1. birta dhexe oo doontu ku dhisan tahay (udub dhexaadka doonta). 2. wax dagan oo sidii la rabay u socda (si miisaaman u socda).
keel over: /kiil ovar/(v) gees ka dhicid (dhan ka dhicid).
keen: /kiin/(adj) 1. aad u danaynaya; usoo jeeda (niyad fiican u haya). e.g. Most girls are not keen on football. 2. af wax gooya leh; fiiqan (mindida, sakiinta iwm).
keep: /kiip/ keeping, kept;(v) 1. hayn; gacan ku hayn (sii hayn) e.g. Can you keep these books for me? (v) 2. xafidid; xajin (sidii ballanku ahaa u fulin).e.g. He kept his promise.
keep back: /kiip baak/(v) wax la harid (dib wax u haysasho). e.g. He decided to keep back all the information.
keep down: /kiip dhawn/(v) hoos u hayn (horukac u diidid); koontaroolid. e.g. It is very important to keep costs down.
keep on: /kiip on/(v) ku soco (hakala joojin); ku wad. e.g. Keep on doing this.
keep up: /kiip ap/(v) 1. kor u hayn (meeshiisa ku hayn). 2. hawl sare hayn (heer sare wax u samayn) e.g. Keep up the good work! 3. la qabsad (sida wax yihiin ula socosho). e.g. He can't keep up with you when you are running.
keeper: /kiipar/(n) ilaaliye (qofka xil gaar ah haya). e.g. The keeper is feeding the animals in the zoo.
kennel: /Kenal/(n) xero eeyga lugu xereeyo (00 cariish u eg)
kernel: /kernal/(n) 1. iniinta miraha ku dhex jirta (iniinta hoose) 2. nuxurka ama dhumucda (arini leedahay)
ketchup: /kejab/(n) yaanyo shiidan oo la meceeyey (00 cuntada lugu cuno). e.g. Could you give me some ketchup for my hot dog?
key: /kii/(n) 1. fure; muftaax e.g. Have you seen my keys? 2. xal u ah (fure u ah) e.g. A key to this problem. 3. badhanka la garaaco (botoonka teebka iwm). e.g. You have to press the return key. 4. muhiim ah (ugu muhiim san). e.g. Education is the key to success.
kg: / (abbr) kilo-gram oo la soo gaabiyey (hal kiilo)
kick: /kik/kicking, kicked, kicks;(v) 1. laad (lugta ku hardiyid); laadid. 2. farxad iyo raaxo ka helid. e.g. He drives fast just for kicks.
kick off: /kik of/(v) darbada ciyaartu ku bilaabanto (laadka ugu horreeya)
kick out: /kik awt/(v) cayrin (laad ku saarid); dibadda u laadid.
kid: /kidh/ (infl)(n) 1. cunug, ilmo yar e.g. How many kids do you have? 2. dhalinyaro. 2. ceesaan, neef ari ah oo dhalin yar.
kidnap: /kidhnaab/(v) af-duubid (qafaalid) e.g. She was kidnapped last night.
kill: /kil/(v) 1. dil (gudha ka jarid) 2. waqti dilid (waqti dhumin) e.g. kill time. 3. laba shimbirood hal dhagax ku dilid (laba natiijo hal ficil ka helid). e.g. Kill two birds with one stone.
kilowatt: /kilo waat/(n) hal kiilowaat (= 1000 waat), korontada ayaa lugu cabbiraa).
kin: /kin/(n) qaraabo; ehel (xigaalo) e.g. Who is your next of kin?
kind: /kayndhi/(n) 1. nooc; jaad e.g. Do you have any other kind? 2. naxariis badan. e.g. My mother was very kind to me.
kindergarten: /kindhar gardhan/ (n) dugsiga barbaarinta carruurta yar-yar. (4 jir-ilaa 6 jir)
kindle: /kindhal/(v) 1. shidid; dab ku dhajin (daarid) e.g. The wood is wet and would not kindle easily. 2. sii kicin; sii hurin (sii xoojin arin ama ra'yi iwm). e.g. His interest was kindled.
kindly: /kayndhali/(adj) 1. si naxariis leh (raxmad leh). e.g. You have to treat your neighbours kindly. 2. min-fadlag (bilisxaanag). e.g. Will you kindly close the window?
kindred: /kidh rid/(n) 1. qaraabo; ehel e.g. None of my kindred were present at my party. 2. isku mid ah, isku dabeecad ah (laba qof oo isku dad ah). e.g. She and I are kindred spirits.
kingdom: /king dham/(n) 1. boqortooyo. e.g. United Kingdom of Saudi Arabia. 2. nimcooleyda xoolaha (ama xayawaanka iyo dhirta). e.g. Animal kingdom.
king-size: /king says/(adj) cabbirka boqorka (waxa ugu weyn). e.g. king-size bed.
kinky: /kinki/(adj) qof yaab leh, cajiib ah (siiba galmada aan caadi ku ahayn ama mayiiko qaba). e.g. There must be something kinky going on here.
kiosk: /kiyoski/(n) 1. dabakaayo (joornaalada, sigaarka iwm lugu gado) 2. meel taleefoon laga dirsado (oo dadweynaha u dhex ah).
kiss: /kis/(n) 1. shumis; dhunkasho (v) 2. shumin, la dhunkado. e.g. They kissed each other when they first met.
kit: /kit/(n) 1. xirmo qalab ah ama qodobo ah oo wax gaar ah loogu tala galay. e.g. This is my first aid kit. 2. yunifoomka ciyaartooyda, askarta iwm. e.g. Have you bought your sports kit?
kite: /kayt/(n) aabuteey (warqadda cirka loo diro oo xariga leh).
kitty: /kitii/(n) 1. bisad; mukulaal 2. lacagta dad badan laga aruuriyo (00 ay wada jir u isticmaalaan).
kiwi: /kiwii/(n) 1. shimbir aan duulin oo Niyuu-siilaan laga helo 2. miro la cuno oo kafee u eg dhexdana ka cagaaran.
kleptomania: /kleptameyniya/ (n) cudur maskaxda gala oo qofku uusan tuuganimo deyn karin.
knack: /naak/(n) xirfad u leh (hibo u leh inuu wax sahal ku qabto). e.g. She has the knack for making friends.
knap-sack: /naap saak/(n) boorsada la xambaarsado (dhabarka lugu qaato)
knave: /neyv/(n) 1. nin daacad daran (aan sharaf lahayn). 2. qulaan turub.
kneed: /niidh/(v) 1. cajimid (bur iyo biyo laysku cajimo) 2. duugid (muruqa iwm).
knickers: /nikars/(n) surweel daba gaab (badanaa midka duluca ama laastiiga leh).
knight: /nayt/(n) 1. ninka billad geesiga ku qaata dagaalka fardooleyda (waagii hore). 2. darajo sare oo bogor bixiyo (oo dadaal lugu mutaysto).
knob: /nob/(n) 1. dhegta la qabsado qataarka albaabka, daaqadaha iwm. 2. botoon wareegsan oo wax laga daaro (sida kan raadyaha, telefishinka iwm).
knock: /nok/(n) 1. garaac. e.g. Please knock on the door before you enter. (v) 2. ridid ama legdid. e.g. He knocked the cup off the table.
knock off: / (v) 1. dhammayn e.g. I start my job early but I'll knock off at noon. 2. ka gooyn (xisaab ka naaqusin). e.g. I'll knock $20 off the price.
knock out: / (v) 1. feer la tuurid (dhulka ku tuurid ilaa heer uu soo kici waayo). eg. He hit him so hard and knocked him out. 2. ka rayn (ka guuleysasho). e.g. That team was knocked out in the first round.
knot: /not/(v) 1. guntin; isku xirid 2. dad aad isugu xiran.
know: /now/(v) garasho, fahmid, ogaansho. e.g. We know the problem.
knowledgeable: /nolijabal/(adj) aqoon u leh (aqoon yahan ku ah).
L,l: /el/ xarafka laba iyo tobnaad ee alifbeetada Ingiriisiga.
lab: /laab/(n) shaybaar (laboratory oo la soo gaabiyey). e.g. I have to take my urine sample to the lab.
label: /leybal/(n) warqad ama calaamad yar oo lugu dhejiyo shay, si looga akhristo wuxu waxay yihiin (sida loo isticmaalayo iwm). e.g. I don't know what is in this bottle because it has no label. e.g. His neighbours labelled him a thief.
labor: /leybar/labour (bre)(n) 1.shaqo; shaqaale (siiba shaqada muruga u baahan) e g. I hate a heavy labor job. 2. foosha (waqtiga naagtu umulayso). e.g. She was in labor for ten hours.
laboratory: /laab ratoori/(n) shaybaar; laab (qolka baarista saamiyada caafimaadka iyo cilmi baarista).
labor union: /leybar yuuniyan/labour union (n) ururka shaqaalaha (u dooda xuquuqda shaqaalaha).
lace: /leys/(n) 1. xarig yar oo wax lugu xiro (lugu dhuujiyo siiba xariga kabaha). e.g. She spent 5 minutes tying the laces of her shoes. 2. in yar oo khamri ah cunto ku darid (ku daarid). e.g. She tried to give me a pepsi laced with alcohol.
lace up: /leys ap/(v) xarig ku dhuujin (xarig ku adkayn). e.g. He bent to lace up his shoes.
lacerate: /laasareyt/(n) dillaacin; kala jeexid (jirka qofka meel ka mid ah).
lack: /laak/(n) la'aan; aan lahayn (aan ku filnayn). e.g. There is lack of food in this village.
lacking: /laakin/(adj) aan haysan; la' (aan lahayn; aan ku filnayn)
lacquer: /laakar/(v) 1. dhalaalin (siiba timaha oo la mariyo wax dhalaaliya oo sidooda ku haya in muddo ah). e.g. Hair lacquer. 2. sharxid, qurxin. e.g. She lacquered the tables.
lactic: /laak tik/(adj) ee caano ah (caana leh; caana la xiriira.
lad: /laadh/ (bre)(n) wiil yar, kuray. e.g. He used to play football all day when he was a lad.
laden: /leydhan/(adj) aad u xammuulan (xammuul ama culays badan saaran yahay).
ladle: /leydhal/(n) malgacad weyn (qaaddo weyn oo dabo leh). e.g. a soup ladle.
lagoon: /laguun/(n) haro badda bacaad ka gooyey (biyo badda gaar ugu soocmay)
lake: /leyk/(n) haro (ama war biyo badan ku jiraan) e.g. Lake ontario.
lamb: /laam/(n) nayl (naysha ama ilmaha yar ee idaha)
lame: /leym/lamely; (adj) 1. jiis; laangare (qofka dhutiya). e.g. She walks with a stick because she is lame. 2. hadal daciif ah (oo aan la rumaysan karin). e.g. a lame excuse.
lampoon: /laampuun/(n) qoraal cid lugu cambaareynayo (qof ama dowlad iwm).
lamp post: /laam powst/(n) baalle (birta dheer ee nalalka dariiqa lagu xiro).
landing: /laandhin/(n) 1. soo caga dhiganaya (soo degaya). e.g. The plane will be landing in ten minutes. 2. dhulka jaran-jarada ka korreeya (ee qolalka loo maro).

landlocked: /laandh lakt/(adj) waddan ama dhul aan xeeb lahayn (badda xudduud la lahayn) e.g. Is your country landlocked?

landmark: /laandh maark/(n) 1. shay sida dhagax ama geed oo wax lagu calaamadsado 2. marxalad ama dhacdo horumar isbaddal wayn ah samaysa. e.g. this book is a landmark in modern history.
landscape: /laandh skeyb/(n) 1. muuqaalka dhirta iyo dabiiciga kale ee dhulka e.g. I like to watch the beauty of the landscape. (v) 2. qurxinta iyo simidda dhirta iyo ku beeridda dhir kale oo qurxisa.
landslide: /laandh slaydh/(n) 1. meel taag ah oo buur ama meel dheer kasoo foororta 2. doorasho ku guuleysasho (codka ugu badan helid). e.g. He should win by a landslide.
lane: /leyn/(n) 1. dariiq yar (wadiiqo) 2. layn ama dariiq ka mid ah waddo weyn (oo calaamadsan).
language: /laanguwij/(n) 1. luqad; af 2. wax kasta oo leysku af garto (sida faraha)
languish: /laang wish/(v) 1. awood yarayn (tabar darrayn) 2. dacdarro (rafaad iyo si xun ku noolaansho)
lanky: /laanki/(adj) qalya-yax (qof dheer oo caato lafallafo ah).
lantern: /laantarn/ (n) feynuus. lap/laap/laps;(n) 1.dhabta qofka (inta u dhaxaysa cajirka iyo xuddunta) e.g. You can sit on my lap.(v) 2. hal wareeg samayn, sida wareegga tartamada. e.g. The dog lapped up the water.
lapel: /lapel/(n) kulleetiga jaakadda oo gadaal u laaban. (sida kuwa garabka gadaal ugu laaban)
lapse: /laaps/(n) 1. khalad yar (gef yar oo dhacay)(n) 2. muddo; ayaan; waa (in waqti ah) e.g. The lapse of time.(v) 3. dib ugu noqosho (dib ugu dhicid). e.g. He has lapsed into his old bad habits.(v) 4. joojin; burin (hishiis ganacsi iwm).
larder: /lardhar/(adj) armaajo ama qol yar oo wax lugu xafito.
large-scale: /larj skeel/(adj) cabbir-weyn (wax aad u weyn marka la eego. cabbirka caadiga ah). e.g. A large- scale business operation.

yacht: /yot/(n) doonni yar, oo badanaa tartanka lugu galo.
yap: /yaap/ (v) xoog u qaylin, siiba qaylada eyda.
yard: /yardh/ (n) 1.waar, yaardi (cabbir la mid ah saddex fiid) 2. deyr, deyd.
yarn: /yarn/ (n) 1. liilan, dun.(infl) 2. sheeko dhacaanla' ( sheeko dheer oo badanaa been ah).
yawn: /yon/ (n) 1. halaaqo, hamaansi (v) 2. hamaansasho. e.g. She yawned all during his lecture.
yearn: /yeern/ (v) 1. boholyoobid, sugi waayid (dheeray-sasho). e.g. He yearned for his home. 2. u beerjilcid, u nixid. e.g. to yearn for the oppressed.
yeast: /yiisti/(n) qamiir ~ khamiir. e.g. That bread is rising too much; You've put too much yeast in it.
yellow pages: /yelowpeyjis/(n) diiwaanka liiska taleefoonada ganacsatada daliil-hayaha taleefoonada.
yen: /yen/ (n) 1. lacagta jabbaanka (v) 2. jamasho, aad u rabid.
yield: /yiildh/ (v) 1. dhalid, miro-dhalid (bixin). e.g. That farm yielded a good crop of tomatoes last year. (v) 2. is-dhiibid (v) 3. siin, bixin.
yoke: /yowk/ (n) 1. qori laba dibi ama xayawaan kale layskula xiro siiba marka beeraha lagu falayo 2. addoonsi 3. isku xirnaansho
Z,z: /zedh, zii / xarafka labaatan iyo lixaad ee alifbeetada ingiriisiga.
zany: /zayni/(adj) jaajaale (qofka yara nacaska ah ee iska faraxsan).
zealous: /zelas/ (adj) xamaasad leh; qiiro rabitaan u qaba.
zest: /zest/ (n) 1. farxad sare 2. diirka liinta ama oronjiga.
zigzag: /zigzaag/ (n) sag-saag (dun ama wax kale oo qalqalloocan).
zip: /zip/ (n) 1. jiin-yeer; jiin-yeer furid ama xirid (v) 2. shangarta ka yeerta rasaasta ama wax la kala jeexay. e.g. I heard the zip of a flying bullet.
zodiac: /zowdhiyaak/ (n) burji (xiddiga ama nasiibka qofka, oo qof walba laga qiyaaso dhalashadiisa).
zoo: /zuu/ (n) beerta xayawaanka la daawado lugu xannaaneeyo. e.g. Let's take the children to the zoo.
Zulu: /zuuluu/(n) qabiil Afrikaan ah oo Koonfur Afrika daga ~ Suuluu.
